title: trio bars
directions: Spread grahams with peanut butter.
Place grahams, peanut butter side up, in an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan, cutting to fit; set aside.
In small bowl with electric mixer at high speed, beat margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy. Mix flour, cocoa and baking soda, blend into margarine mixture. Stir in raisins.
Spread batter over peanut butter layer.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into 24 bars.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix jello and water together.
Stir and set aside.
Mix cake mix, eggs and Wesson oil together.
Beat on medium speed until mixed good.
Add jello last and beat until dissolved good.
Pour into tube pan which has been well-greased with Wesson oil. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done when tested with toothpick.

title: chicken-wild rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Cut into small pieces.
Cook wild rice without seasoning pack.
Set each aside.
Saute large onion in butter until soft, but not brown.
Stir in flour, soup and stock.
In a 9 x 13-inch (approximately) glass casserole, layer sauce, rice, chicken, cheese, sauce, rice, chicken, sauce and cheese.
Top with paprika.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and bananas.
Sift dry ingredients and add a little at a time with nuts and vanilla. Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: In
mixer
bowl, beat eggs until frothy.
In a separate bowl, combine the sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt; then add to the
eggs and
blend.
Add
the corn syrup, melted butter and vanilla; blend
again.
Mix
in the oatmeal and pour into the crusts.
Bake for
minutes, or until well set.
(This can take over an hour, especially when baking more than one pie in an oven.)

title: meat loaf with sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine meat, cereal, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Spread into casserole dish.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together cheese, sugar and peanut butter.
Add milk gradually, then fold in Cool Whip.
Spread into shell.
Sprinkle with crushed peanuts or chocolate chips if desired.
Freeze, then serve.

title: tweedy's crispy cucumbers
directions: Marinate cucumbers and onions in salt in the refrigerator for 2 hours.
Drain.
Dissolve over medium heat sugar and vinegar. Pour
hot mixture over drained cucumbers and onions. Sprinkle celery seed.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: banana pudding
directions: Use vanilla pudding mix.
Pour into pan and mix with 1 cup of milk.
Then add other 3 cups of milk.
Cook as directed on box, except add 3 beaten egg yolks and cook a little longer.
Pudding will be thicker (save egg whites).

title: chocolate kiss peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour with baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter and peanut butter until well blended.
Add 1 cup sugar and brown sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Stir in flour mixture until well combined.
Using level tablespoonful for each, shape into 5 dozen balls.
Roll each in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes and remove from oven. Press an unwrapped chocolate kiss on each; bake 2 minutes longer.

title: smoked brisket
directions: Sprinkle brisket with the liquid smoke, garlic powder and onion salt.
Let stand, covered, overnight.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Brush with Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and bake 5 hours at 275°.
Drain grease, if any.

title: yams hawaiian style
directions: Slice sweet potatoes into 1/2 inch thick pieces, or mash. Combine with pineapple, butter, sugar and cinnamon in 2 qt. casserole. Microwave at high 2 to 4 minutes. If dish is not hot and topping melted after 2 minutes, rotate dish 1/4 turn before continuing to microwave.

title: puppy chow
directions: Heat first three ingredients until melted; place cereal in large bowl and pour melted mixture over cereal; stir thoroughly. Place powdered sugar in paper bag.
Add cereal mix and shake until well coated.

title: brown sugar squares
directions: Cream the shortening with 1/2 cup of the brown sugar. Continue to beat until well blended.
Add 1 cup of flour, working mixture with a wooden spoon.
Spread in an ungreased 8 x 8-inch cake pan, pressing down evenly.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes or until light brown.
Remove from oven and set aside.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix together dry ingredients.
Then add remaining ingredients and mix until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed with electric mixer.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan in 350° oven for 35 minutes or until done. Cool.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and sour cream. Add dry ingredients. Add vanilla. Pour in well-greased tube pan, lightly floured. Bake 1 hour, until toothpick comes out clean at 350°. Sift confectioners sugar lightly on top.

title: sweetheart cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Form into balls (about the circumference of a quarter).
Press down with an English walnut half or half a maraschino cherry.
Bake at 325° about 20 minutes.
Watch closely. Cook until not too brown or until golden brown on the bottom only.
Use an ungreased cookie sheet.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen cookies.

title: coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Add flour to melted butter.
Mix well. Combine eggs and butter mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 25 minutes more or until knife, inserted in center, comes out clean.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage.
Put in bottom of dish.
Do not cook.
Layer cabbage, sauce and cheese.
Microwave 10 minutes on High.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: almond legend cake
directions: Grease a 9-inch Bundt pan heavily with 2 tablespoons.
Sprinkle with chopped almonds.
Re-sift flour with baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream the shortening with 1 1/4 cups sugar and flavorings. Beat in egg yolks.
Blend in flour mixture, milk, lemon and peel. Beat egg whites with cream of tartar.
Gradually beat in remaining 1/4 cup sugar, beating to stiff meringue.
Fold into batter.
Turn into pan.
Press whole almond just below surface of batter.
Bake at 300° (below oven center) 1 hour and 20 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes, then invert on wire rack to cool.
Brush with Apricot Glaze when cool.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Prepare broccoli, cauliflower and onion.
Fry bacon; drain well and allow to cool.
Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar; blend well.
Pour over broccoli-cauliflower mixture.
Add cheese and bacon bits just before serving.
Serves a bunch.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as package directs.
Brown ground chuck, sausage, onions and garlic in large skillet.
Pour off excess fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, oregano, basil, salt and pepper.
Boil gently uncovered 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour 1/3 of sauce in bottom of 8-inch square casserole.
Place a layer of half of the noodles over sauce.
Spread half of the cottage cheese over the noodles.
Top with half remaining sauce and half the Jack and other cheeses.
Add noodles and rest of sauce.
Add Parmesan before baking.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: prune cake
directions: Melt, in saucepan, over low heat, butter or margarine.
Add brown sugar.
Cook and stir over low heat 2 minutes.
Stir in milk.
Cook and stir, over low heat, until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool to lukewarm or until the hand can be comfortably held on the bottom of pan.
Stir in, about 1/2 cup at a time, powdered sugar.
Beat until smooth and creamy.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookie pie
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk; let cool.
Stir in 1 cup whipped topping.
Mix chocolate pudding in 2 cups milk.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups lite Cool Whip. Spoon this in crust.
Place cookies over pudding.
Spread marshmallow mix over cookies.
Let stand and cool in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin pecan pie squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and butter in small mixer bowl. Beat at low speed for 1 to 2 minutes or until crumbly. Press on bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake for 15 minutes.

title: california sushi in a pan
directions: Cook rice.
Let cool slightly and put into mixing bowl.
Add sushi powder as directed on package and mix in.
Put half of rice in a 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Spread a layer of mayonnaise on rice. Shred imitation crab and place over mayonnaise.
Place the avocado over the crab.
Add the second layer of the remaining rice. Sprinkle with Furikake.
Cut into squares.

title: easy potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Slice and layer in casserole dish with pats of butter and seasoned salt.
Add whipping cream (not whipped).
May bake in 300° oven for 1 hour or microwave for 30 minutes.

title: mushroom and cheddar soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes. Add mushrooms. Cook over high heat until browned and liquid has evaporated. Sprinkle flour over mushrooms.
Cook until flour is lightly browned.
Add stock and milk.
Bring to a boil. Add salt and pepper. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes. Puree soup. Return to pot.
Add Cheddar. Cook gently until cheese has just melted.
Serve, sprinkled with parsley and cheese.

title: corn pudding
directions: Grease casserole.
Mix flour and corn.
Add eggs, oleo and add milk gradually.
Add salt and pepper.
Top with buttered crumbs and sprinkle with paprika.
Pour in casserole.
Then place in shallow pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.
Must put in pan of water so it will not stick when baking.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer all ingredients except mayonnaise.
Spread mayonnaise over the top.
Cover and refrigerate.
Toss before serving.

title: cherry torte
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy. Add cream of tartar and beat until stiff. Add sugar slowly and continue beating. Fold in soda crackers, nut meats and vanilla. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool in refrigerator. Make 2 packages Dream Whip and spread on top.
Top with one can cherry pie filling. May be made ahead of time.

title: no work chicken
directions: Mix together except chicken.
Pour over chicken.
Marinate 6 hours or overnight.
Cover chicken with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour; then bake 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: pineapple congealed salad
directions: Heat pineapple; mix in jello.
Let cool.
Stir in buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Chill.
(Can use sugar-free jello and lite Cool Whip.)

title: hash brown omelet
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Leave drippings in skillet.
Drain bacon and crumble.
Mix next 3 ingredients; pat into skillet.
Cook over low hat until underside is crisp and brown.
Blend eggs, milk, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper; pour over potatoes.
Top with cheese and bacon.
Cover.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Loosen omelet.
Makes 4 wedges.

title: gram's salad dressing(makes about 16 ounces)
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and mix until well blended. Refrigerate in tightly covered jar.
Let stand at room temperature for 10 to 15 minutes before using.
Shake well.

title: lavanda burns cheese cake
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water and let slightly thicken.
Cream cream cheese, sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Whip chilled milk and add Jell-O and cheese mixture.
Crush graham crackers, add powdered sugar and melted butter.
Put 1/2 of cracker mixture on bottom of oblong pan.
Pour cream cheese mixture on that and then top with graham cracker mixture.

title: black jack barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and simmer 25 minutes. Strain or puree in a blender or food processor.
Refrigerate between uses.
Makes 5 cups.

title: chicken-artichoke salad
directions: Reserve 4 egg wedges for garnish. Place remaining eggs, artichokes, chicken, tomatoes and cheese in a medium bowl.
In a small bowl beat remaining ingredients except lettuce leaves.
Pour over egg mixture and toss gently until evenly coated.
Chill to blend flavors.
Serve on lettuce leaves; garnish with reserved egg wedges.

title: oreo cream pie
directions: Take a can of biscuits out of the refrigerator. Peel back flap to open.
Hit the counter top edge and open can of biscuits.
Lay on a greased baking pan. Put in oven and bake as directed on can. Serve hot with white soup.

title: lamb chops
directions: Combine all ingredients except lamb chops and mix well in blender, then marinate lamb chops for at least 4 hours, preferably overnight.
Grill or broil.
(We prefer them pink.)

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut hot baked potatoes in half.
Scoop out insides.
Reserve shells.
In large bowl with electric mixer, beat potatoes and butter until creamy.
Gradually add milk.
Stir in onion, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into reserved shells.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve.

title: party salami
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into 4 or 5 (2-inch) logs.
Wrap each log separately in foil.
Chill for 24 to 36 hours.

title: kohrt kid's cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Mix all remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yummy and quick!

title: almond chicken
directions: Place breasts in pan.
Mix sour cream and soup; place over breasts.
Melt butter; pour over crushed Ritz crackers.
Place over chicken.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry hamburger, onions and peppers together.
Drain off oil. Pour into 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Pour on corn, then mashed potatoes on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding the raisins and nuts last. Mix until batter is smooth and drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears, peppers and onions in food chopper. Add remaining ingredients with 1 cup of juice from grinding. Cook slowly for 1 hour, then put in hot sterilized jars. Seal at once.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute green pepper, onion, celery and garlic in 1/3 cup chicken broth for 5 to 7 minutes.
Add shrimp and simmer until fully cooked (5 minutes).
Add 1/3 cup more broth if needed.
Add other meats and set aside.
Heat oil in a heavy frypan; brown the rice.
In large Dutch oven, place remaining broth, tomatoes, bay leaves, thyme, rice and red pepper sauce.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes.
Combine all ingredients and heat through. Makes 6 servings.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning mix and simmer.
Set aside.
Mix 1 can chicken rice soup and sour cream in a saucepan.
Heat through.
In a casserole dish, layer tortillas, meat, sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry ice cream pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour in graham cracker pie crust and freeze.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies(icebox dough)
directions: Beat by hand, or mix, the oil, melted chocolate and sugar. Blend one egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt and baking powder that had been sifted together.
Then chill at least 6 hours or overnight.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Pare and chop apples.
Pour sugar over apples; let stand 1/2 hour.
Mix eggs and oil.
Add to apples.
Add sifted dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Can serve with ice cream, powdered sugar or plain.

title: beef rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Prepare the rice with the water in standard manner. (I do not use salt or margarine in the preparation of the rice.) While the rice is cooking, chop the onions and garlic. Saute slowly until onions are just tender. Add the ground beef and brown. Cook onions and ground beef about 7 minutes. Drain off the fat. Return to medium heat. Separately mix the broccoli cheese soup and milk. Stir until creamy in texture. At this point, test for taste. I usually add table grind black pepper and salt (less than 1/2 teaspoon). When the ground beef is ready, add the rice and broccoli and soup mixture, tossing carefully. Put the mixture into a 9 x 9 or 9 x 13 casserole dish. Sometimes I top this with seasoned bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Bake about 35 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook on stove until clear.
Add a few drops of food coloring while mixture is cooking. Dissolve Jell-O in mixture.
Arrange strawberries in pie shell. Pour mixture over strawberries.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Top with whipped cream you've prebeaten and sweetened.

title: cheese balls or roll
directions: Put all ingredients in blender, mixing well.
Season with salt, red pepper, lemon juice, chopped or grated onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Shape in roll or balls.
Roll in paprika. Wrap and chill.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: risotta
directions: Into a saucepan saute onion in butter until lightly browned. Slowly pour in rice, stirring often.
Cook on very
low heat. Stir in chicken broth and marsala.
Put saffron in hot water. Also add to rice.
Cover with lid.
Allow to sit about 15 to 20 minutes until rice gets soft and absorbs liquid.
After 20 minutes, strain grated cheese.
If using mushrooms, saute when doing onions.

title: citrus slush punch
directions: Bring sugar and 3 cups water to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves. Remove from heat. Stir in frozen juices until melted. Stir in pineapple juice and 3 cups cold water. Pour into 2 (9 x 13) pans, cover and freeze at least overnight. Cut each pan of frozen punch into 24 squares. Place in freezer bags and store in freezer until ready to use. Makes 2 gallons.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Boil rapidly for 2 minutes.
Add 3 cups sugar.
Boil rapidly for 3 minutes.
Set aside to cool, stirring occasionally until cool.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: new york cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a bowl, place graham cracker crumbs, butter and 2 tablespoons sugar; blend well.
Press mixture into bottom and sides of a greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill in freezer while preparing filling.

title: new england baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain and pick out "bad" beans.
Boil the beans for 5 minutes with 1 tablespoon baking soda.
Drain again, then combine all ingredients in a crock-pot or slow cooker. Bake at 225° to 250° for 5 to 6 hours.

title: baked breaded pork chops
directions: Use margarine to coat a 9 x 13 baking pan. In a shallow bowl mix eggs & milk. Coat chops with crumb mixture then dip into egg mixture, then into crumbs again. Arrange in pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes, carefully turn chops & bake 30 minutes longer.

title: spam casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 9 x 13 baking dish. Cook at 350° for 10 - 15 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef across the grain into very thin strips.
In skillet over high heat in 1 tablespoon of margarine, cook half of the beef and half the onion.
Cook until beef is no longer pink and onion is tender; set aside.
Repeat with remaining margarine, beef and onion.
Return all meat mixture to skillet.
Stir in soup and paprika.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to very low.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Use an electric mixer or food processor.
Mix butter with jam until well blended.
Serve with biscuits.
Yields 2 cups.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry pudding with pineapple.
Add rest of ingredients and mix thoroughly.

title: date nut tarts
directions: Mix together softened cream cheese and butter with flour in bowl.
Chill, covered, for 1 hour.
Shape into 24 (1-inch) balls. Press each dough ball over bottom and up the sides of an ungreased miniature muffin pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.

title: mediterranean roast chicken
directions: Combine the olive oil, lemon juice and zest, garlic, rosemary, salt and pepper in a large bowl. Coat the whole chickens well with the marinade and refrigerate, covered, overnight.

title: tart cherry salad
directions: Drain fruits, reserving juices.
Add enough water to cherry and pineapple juice to make 3 1/4 cups.
Add sugar.
Bring to a boil and add Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Add fruit and ginger ale.
Chill until very thick but not set.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Pour into a 2-quart ring mold.
Chill until set.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and bone chicken; place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together undiluted soups and pour over chicken.
Blend celery, onion and margarine; pour over soups.
Mix 3/4 teaspoon sage and 2 cups broth; pour on top.
Layer with dry dressing mix.
Mix 3/4 teaspoon sage and 2 cups broth; pour over dressing mix.
Let stand 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cocoa squares
directions: Blend and set aside.

title: heath bar cookies
directions: Melt sugar and butter in saucepan; bring this to a boil for 5 minutes.
Pour mixture over saltine crackers.
Then bake in 400° oven (preheated oven).
Bake exactly 5 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle chocolate chips over and then spread with a knife over the baked mixture.
Sprinkle ground nuts over chocolate.
When cooled, may cut or break into pieces.

title: fried rice
directions: In a skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil.
Scramble eggs and remove.
Heat
another
tablespoon oil and stir-fry meat until done.
If
you
are
using dried mushrooms, cook them with the meat.
When meat is done, remove from pan.
Heat 4 tablespoons oil and fry the green onion.
Add the rice, mixing constantly, until rice
is
thoroughly
heated.
Add the eggs, meat, mushrooms and peas.
Add soy and salt or pepper to taste.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together, except crackers and oleo.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Melt the oleo; pour onto crackers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and cream cheese.
Add vanilla. Spread filling between and on top of layers.

title: beef stick(like hickory farms)
directions: Mix together.
Cover in an airtight container.
Mix 5 minutes a day for an additional 4 days (total of 5 days).
On the fifth day, make 6 rolls.
Bake for 5 hours at 200° on rack over cookie sheet.
Refrigerate or can freeze.
Great for Christmas gifts.

title: broccoli marinade
directions: Combine chopped vegetables.
In separate bowl, combine oil and vinegar. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Pour over vegetables and toss. Refrigerate.

title: beef and chicken soup
directions: Put ingredients into a 4-quart pot and cover with water. Bring to boil, then add paprika.
Simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, then add Lipton chicken soup broth.
Simmer for another 5 minutes. If soup is too strong, add some more water.
Strain soup and place carrots back in.

title: sour cream fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl, mixing gently.
Chill.

title: grilled turkey steaks(low-fat)
directions: Rub the steaks on all sides with the mustard.
Sprinkle on the tarragon and pepper.
Grill for 5 minutes on each side until cooked.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flavoring and egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat well.
Mix soda in flour.
Pour 2 1/2 cups flour over nuts and candied fruits in a large pan.
Pour your batter over the nut and candied fruit mix into the pan.
Mix well.
Beat the egg whites and fold in mixture.
Bake 4 hours at 225° in a large tube pan.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: green beans with hazelnuts
directions: Cook beans in boiling water 3 to 8 minutes. Drain. Toss in bowl with rest of ingredients.

title: snacks on a string
directions: You will also need button thread and a large blunt tapestry needle.

title: brisket
directions: Rub brisket with celery salt, garlic salt and onion salt.
Put in Pyrex and pour liquid smoke over it.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Pour off liquid.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Sprinkle with Worcestershire.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours, covered.
Turn and cover with barbecue sauce.
Cook at 250° for 1 hour.

title: seven layer candy
directions: Place each of the ingredients in layers in 7 x 11-inch oblong baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand well.
Drain thoroughly mandarin orange sections and pineapple.
Cut orange sections in small pieces.
Add to the mixture.
Last add lemon juice.
Mix well. Makes 2 pies.

title: okra lover's omelet
directions: Fry okra and onions (scallions) in 2 tablespoons bacon grease until onions are clear and okra is still bright green (overcook and it will be slimy).
Remove okra and onions.

In same skillet stir eggs until they start thickening, then return okra and onions and carefully work mixture to desired doneness (about 5 to 9 minutes). Serves 4 to 5. Very good served with cornbread.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Put ribs in cake pan, meaty side up.
On each piece place a slice of onion and a bit of lemon juice.
Roast in hot oven at 450° for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and pour over ribs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Baste sauce every 15 minutes.
Add more water if sauce gets too thick.

title: egg and sausage bake
directions: Night before:
Grease a 9 x 13-inch or 10 x 14-inch pan.
Layer all bread cubes on the bottom of the dish and then the sausage. Next, layer all of the shredded cheese.
In a bowl, mix together 2 1/2 cups milk, eggs and the mustard.
Pour all of the mixture over the bread/cheese/sausage dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: eggplant parmazine
directions: Peel and slice eggplant, lengthwise.
Roll in egg and flour. Place in pan with oil and fry until browned.
Drain and alternate with cooked and drained hamburger, cheese and sauce in large baking dish.
Place in 350° oven 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool slightly and serve.
Serve with garlic bread and tossed salad.

title: ricardo's chili con carne
directions: Brown meat in a heavy skillet; break up with a spoon or fork as it cooks.
Add onion and pepper; cook until soft.
Add tomatoes, salt, chili powder, hot pepper sauce and paprika.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add hot water, if necessary, to keep mixture from thickening too much.
Add beans; heat thoroughly.
Cool, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, heat until bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: english pea salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer the following.
On the bottom, tear lettuce into bite sizes.
Pour peas, then layer celery and 1/2 cup onion.
Spread mayonnaise to cover like icing.
Sprinkle with cheese and red pepper.
Repeat the layers once more.
Cover and refrigerate. Serves 10 to 12.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Mix with a fork until
mixture resembles coarse meal.
Spread half the mixture in pastry shell.
Set remaining mixture aside.
Combine remaining ingredients, except egg whites, in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Spoon filling over peanut butter layer in pastry shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Spread over filling.
Sprinkle remaining peanut butter mixture over meringue. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until meringue is firm and lightly browned.
Let cool before serving.

title: tropical orange-coconut cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar, oleo, eggs, baking powder, salt, vanilla and orange extract.
Beat at low speed, scraping bowl often, until well mixed, 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in flour and coconut until well mixed, 2 to 3 minutes.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 12 minutes at 350° or until edges are lightly browned. Remove from pan immediately.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chips, margarine and peanut butter and pour over cereal. Stir until coated.
Put sugar in plastic bag and pour cereal mixture in; shake well.

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: Cook until thickened and pour over cooked carrots.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Serves 6 or 7.

title: aunt joan's ham
directions: Cut off skin and as much fat as possible.
Face cut side facing down in pan.
Add 2 cups water.
Cover.
Put in cold oven.
Heat oven to 400°, turn off heat immediately.
Wait 2 hours.
Turn back on and when temperature reaches 400°, time for 20 minutes.
Turn off and leave in oven overnight.
Do not open or remove top until next morning.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Melt butter, cheese and crab in saucepan until it all mixes together.
Should be easy to dip with crackers.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Marinate with meat overnight in refrigerator.
May be used as barbecue sauce.

title: crazy crust pie
directions: Lightly grease and flour bottom and sides of 9-inch metal or 10-inch glass pie pan.

title: reduced calorie cajun fish roll-up
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In skillet, melt 1 teaspoon margarine, add celery and onion and saute over medium heat stirring occasionally for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add crabmeat, breadcrumbs, egg white, green onions, parsley and red pepper mixing until combined.
Spoon half of crabmeat mixture onto center of each fillet and roll fish to enclose filling.
Transfer rolls, seam side down, to 1-quart casserole.
Set aside.
In pan, melt remaining margarine, stir in lemon juice and dash of red pepper.
Pour lemon mixture over rolls and sprinkle with dash of pepper and paprika.
Bake about 15 minutes.
Makes 2 servings, 250 calories each.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix the water and sugar together.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute. Take off burner. Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix until smooth.
Put into a buttered greased pan.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
Serving:
3 teaspoons per cup.

title: creamy chicken noodle supper
directions: In large saucepan over medium heat, cook onion in hot butter until tender, stirring often.
Stir in soup, milk, sage and pepper until well mixed.
Stir in noodles, chicken and vegetables just until mixed.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Stir casserole; sprinkle with almonds.
Bake for 5 minutes more.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and the butter for 2 minutes.
Add Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Add vanilla.
Pour into buttered 7 x 11-inch pan.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Mix artichoke hearts with remaining ingredients.
Spoon into 8-inch round pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with bread or fresh vegetables.

title: warel's coffeecake
directions: Cream oleo and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add egg, sour cream, vanilla, flour, baking soda or powder and salt.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and chopped nuts.

title: biscuit topped italian casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Stir in water, pepper, tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Boil until it forms soft ball in cold water.
Add salt, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Pour on buttered platter.
Slice into squares.

title: connie's microwave french onion soup
directions: Place sliced onions and butter in 2-quart casserole dish. Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes, stirring once until onions are translucent.
Pour beef and chicken bouillon into 1-quart measuring cup and add water to make 1 quart.
Pour liquids over onions and microwave on High 5 to 8 minutes, until heated through.
Place soup in individual soup bowls.
Cover with croutons and place sliced cheese over top.
Microwave 3 to 5 minutes, until cheese melts. Rotate soup bowls at least once.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in greased, floured baking pan 11x7.
Bake at 375
degrees for 18 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: monkey bread
directions: Shake sugar and cinnamon in bag.
Cut biscuits in quarters and coat with sugar and cinnamon.
Spray a tube pan.
Place biscuit pieces in pan. Sprinkle with nuts.
Melt the margarine, add brown sugar; let come to boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.

title: charlie's beef stroganoff
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in a saucepan.
Add garlic, shallots, onion, mushrooms and bay leaf.
Saute vegetables until tender, but not browned.
Discard bay leaf.
Stir in flour until well blended.
Add tomato sauce and hot broth.
Stir until well blended.
Cook until smooth and slightly thickened.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients raw in a large bowl, then put into 9 x 13-inch pan and cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours (maybe more depending on your oven). Stir 2 to 3 times during cooking. Cover to cook.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine dressing, vinegar and sugar in a jar or blender.
Toss together with vegetables.
When ready to serve, garnish with bacon and onions.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat oil, butter and sugar until light and creamy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time; beat well.
Add baking powder, salt and flour; mix with milk and beat well.
Grease and flour tube or Bundt pan. Start in cold oven at 350°.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream sugar & oil; beat in eggs one at a time; add water & pumpkin alternately with dry ingredients.
Add raisins & nuts.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 - 2 hours or half the time in 2 loaf pans.

title: fruit salad
directions: Whip 6 tablespoons of pineapple juice with cream cheese.
Add 3 tablespoons of cherry juice and beat.
Add 5 heaping tablespoons of Cool Whip.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Will be stiff.
Spray pizza pan or jelly roll pan with Pam.
Spread dough in pan for 1 large cookie.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Warm potatoes; drain juice.
Cream margarine, eggs and sugar. Add milk and cinnamon.
After potatoes warm, add ingredients. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken sopa
directions: Layer tortillas, chicken, chilies, Velveeta and chicken soup. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions on box.
Fold Cool Whip, sour cream and vanilla into pudding mixture.
Layer wafers, pudding and bananas in a glass container until all ingredients are used up.
Chill 3 or 4 hours.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar; then blend in milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour, candied cherries and nuts.
Form into 8 inch long rolls, 8 inch in diameter.
Roll in coconut.
Wrap in wax paper and chill overnight.
Cut into 1/4 inch slices and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Mix broccoli, 1/2 of cheese, 1/2 of soup and 1/2 of milk with chicken.
Spread on shells and roll.
Place on baking dish (seam side down).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, covered.
Uncover and pour remaining (mixed together) soup, milk and cheese over baked shells.
Put broken onion rings over all.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: sausage, rice and noodle hot dish
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pour soup mix from both envelopes into 2-quart casserole.
Stir in boiling water; let stand 20 minutes.

title: play doh
directions: Cook in Teflon pan over medium heat.
Stir and stir.
Will pull from sides.
Pour on tray (cookie sheet).
Add food coloring. Also flavoring if desired.

title: drop fruit cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add enough flour to make it stiff enough to drop from a spoon (3 1/2 cups or more).
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: homemade lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Boil noodles according to package directions.
Add Ragu sauce to ground beef.
In separate bowl, mix Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese together.
Layer ground beef, cheese mixture and noodles in casserole dish.
End with cheese mixture on top.
Bake in oven at 350° until cheese melts.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into logs.
Wrap in wax paper. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Next day, remove wax paper and place logs on cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.
After cooking, wrap sausage in foil and refrigerate.

title: dry jello
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Add drained pineapple. Stir in dry Jell-O and refrigerate.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Blend ingredients together, mixing one cup of flour in at a time, until all is well mixed.
Flour surface and rolling pin. Knead a ball of dough slightly, then roll out onto flat surface, using cookie cutters to make designs.
Continue until all dough is used.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
They will be light in color.
Decorate with sprinkles or icing.

title: overnight salad
directions: Fry and crumble bacon.
Layer the ingredients in this order: lettuce, cauliflower, onion, bacon, cheese, peas, sugar and salad dressing.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight. Stir immediately before serving.

title: norma's dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in a closed container in refrigerator.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; add mayonnaise.
Cut up onions (green and all).
Add dry Ranch mix thoroughly.
Form into a ball and roll into cut up pieces of beef.
Chill before serving.
Will stay soft.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add soda to sour cream; add to eggs.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add flour and mix.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until light brown.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in loaf pan or baking dish. Top meat loaf with ketchup and brown.

title: green grape salad
directions: Make white sauce by melting butter in medium saucepan over medium heat.
Add flour and mix until no lumps remain.
Add milk all at once and stir until mixture thickens.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Mix grapes, pineapple and pecans together in medium mixing bowl.
Pour mixture into bottom of large casserole.
Pour white sauce over mixture and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: my own apple pie
directions: Make crust for 9-inch double-crust pie.
Slice apples.
Fill crust with half of the apples and sprinkle with half the sugar, butter, cinnamon and flour.
Use the rest of the apples and ingredients and salt.
Put on top crust and make a few slashes in crust to let steam escape.
Bake at 350° about 55 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple in medium saucepan, then add Jell-O to dissolve. Cool.
Add buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts. Whip together the above ingredients.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan and chill 2 hours.

title: coconut cake icing(aunt cleo casey)
directions: Mix sugar, water and syrup together and cook until makes a string (thin as a hair).
Beat egg whites stiff.
Gradually pour sugar mixture over egg whites and beat.

title: spinach-artichoke casserole
directions: Cook spinach as directed on box. Drain. Saute onion in butter. Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole. Stir Parmesan cheese into casserole and also some on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: mexican pie
directions: Layer in a 10-inch quiche dish the beans, avocado, mixed with half of sour cream and 1/2 to 3/4 packet of seasoning, scallions, tomatoes, olives and cheese.
Top with the rest of the sour cream. Dip Tostitos into pie.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Pour over Rice Chex.
Stir well.
Pour powdered sugar in brown bag.
Add Chex and shake well.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together good.
Make into small balls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until brown.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni; drain and let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: play dough
directions: Mix, cooking until mixture comes away from sides of pan and sticks to the spoon.
Stir constantly 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Knead until smooth.
Give to kids to enjoy.
Use food color if wanted.

title: cherry bars
directions: Mix together sugar and butter; cream them then add the dry ingredients.
Spread part of dough on a greased cookie sheet, cover dough with cherry pie filling.
Top with the rest of dough. (Hard to spread but little spoonfuls will melt together while cooking.)
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: easy ray pleaser sausage supper
directions: Take a large deep dish and peel and cut potatoes.
Place in the dish with the chopped onion.
Put 4 to 5 pats of butter, salt and pepper.
Then put the frozen corn on top.
Then on top of that, place your sausage, cut up in 2-inch strips.
Put about 3 to 4 tablespoons of water and you can slow cook in the oven or on the stove top.
When the potatoes are cooked, it's ready.
The juices from the meat soak through the corn and the potatoes.
You might need to add a little more butter, salt and pepper to your desire.

title: diabetic pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Drain
pineapple slices, reserving juice.
Arrange four pineapple slices in lightly greased and wax paper lined 8-inch round
pan.
Fill
center of each pineapple slice with chopped pecans
and
sprinkle
remaining pecans in center of cake pan. Mix cake
mix
with
cup pineapple juice for 3 minutes in mixer. Add
1/3 cup water and mix 1 minute.
Pour batter over pineapple and pecans.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes; cool slightly. Loosen
cake
around
sides.
Invert
onto	serving plate.	Remove wax
paper.
Makes
one
8-inch cake.
Makes 8 servings at 137 calories per serving.

title: carrots
directions: Cook on high for 9 to 11 minutes the carrots, sugar and butter.
Mix water and cornstarch and add.
Add pecans, cover and cook on High 2 to 4 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pineapple yum yum cake
directions: Mix and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook until done at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Grease large casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 of stuffing mix on bottom.
Combine all other ingredients.
Pour over stuffing.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: fabulous fruit bread
directions: Combine bananas, eggs, vanilla, spice, honey and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Stir soda into flour and add to mixture.
Add nuts, raisins and apples.
Pour into loaf pan and bake 40 minutes at 375°.
Serve warm.

title: grape slush
directions: Mix all together and freeze.
Stir occasionally.
Can substitute grape juice for other juice.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Blend with corn and seasonings.
Add milk gradually to mixture.
Pour into lightly greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter and place in 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir 3 or 4 times while baking.
Mixture will "set" to pudding firmness.
Serve at once.

title: pink cloud pineapple salad
directions: First, drain pineapple.
Add jello.
Mix, then add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Place in large bowl and refrigerate. Salad will keep well for about 1 week.

title: easy cherry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9-inch square pan or baking dish.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar and milk until smooth.
Pour over melted butter.
Pour can of cherries (undrained) over batter; sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes, or until browned.

title: mother's fruit cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in saucepan.
Boil gently for 3 minutes.
Cool in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, fruit and nuts. Sift dry ingredients.
Add gradually to first mixture, beating well after each addition.
Pour into 9-inch tube pan, lined with greased wax paper.
Bake in slow oven (275°) for 2 1/2 hours or until tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan and cool thoroughly.
Wrap securely in aluminum foil.
Store in an airtight container.
Age 3 to 4 weeks to improve flavor.
Will store well for 6 weeks.
Makes about 4 to 4 1/2 pounds.
A good, dark fruitcake.
The longer you store it the better it tastes.
A tradition in our family for Christmas.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix all together and pack down in baking dish 3 inches deep and 5 x 10-inches.
Let stand 24 hours before cutting.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook noodles, drain; brown meat, stir in tomato sauce and remove from heat.
Combine cheese, sour cream, onion and pepper. Layer noodles and then cheese, and then another layer of each.
Add butter and then meat mixture.
Chill several hours or make day before.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Enjoy!

title: brownies from tillie
directions: Melt unsweetened chocolate and shortening/butter together. Put remaining ingredients in a large bowl and beat together for 2 minutes. Add melted chocolate and shortening/butter mixture. Beat 1 minute. Add 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla and beat until mixed. Add 1 cup halved pecans or pecan pieces and blend with spoon. Pour in greased and floured long pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Do not overbake or brownies will not be chewy. Frost, if desired.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients. Spoon into prepared pie crust. Cover with top crust. Crimp edges to seal. Slit top crust and brush with egg. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese. Blend in rest of the ingredients. Cut cake in 3 layers. Put ingredients between layers. Cover sides, top and inside. Put pie filling on top and let run down sides. Chill for 24 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses, onion, pepper and mayonnaise.
Put in jello (Bundt-style) mold.
Refrigerate two hours.
Unmold onto plate; sprinkle with pecans.
Put strawberry preserves in center of cheese ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: wiener bean bake
directions: Cook limas; drain.
Mix with pork and beans.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover; stir.
Bake 30 minutes more.

title: pizza
directions: Cut the French bread lengthwise, making two slices.
Place on cookie sheet.
Mix the hamburger and tomato paste.
Add the chopped onion, oregano, salt and pepper.
Mix well, then spread over the bread.
Sprinkle the grated cheese over the top.
Bake 15 minutes in 400° oven.
Take from oven and cover with slices of cheese, cut diagonally and lapping point over each slice.
Return to oven and bake for 5 more minutes.
Will serve 4 to 6 people.

title: barbecue chicken (diet)
directions: Mix well and pour over chicken pieces.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Beat half of cake mix, water, peanut butter and eggs in large bowl with electric mixer. Stir in remaining cake mix. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonful about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten in crisscross pattern with fork dipped in sugar. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: barbecue seagull
directions: Start fire in barbecue range.
Set red brick over fire.
Lay seagull on brick.
Lay shingle on seagull.
Put on barbecue sauce. When fork can be stuck through brick with ease, throw away seagull and eat the shingle.

title: ale 8 cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar; set aside.
Mix and bring to a boil the margarine, cocoa and Ale 8.
Pour over the flour and sugar while hot; mix well.
Mix together soda and buttermilk; add along with beaten eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add small marshmallows while beating on low speed.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in prepared 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and onion. Boil until tender.
Drain.
In a large bowl, mix soup, egg, stuffing mix, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Add squash and fold together.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cover with cheese. Bake until brown.

title: frozen daiquiri
directions: Mix a small amount of the limeade with powdered sugar so that it dissolves well. Add rest of ingredients.
Make a double batch and keep in freezer to use as desired. Will not freeze solid.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Beat together the first 3 ingredients; add food coloring to give the mixture a pleasant yellow color.
Pour into a prepared Graham Cracker Crust and chill for at least 4 hours before serving.
Keep leftover pie in the refrigerator.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Put everything in a large pan; bring to a boil.
Simmer for 1 hour; stir often.

title: grits casserole(freezes well, before or after baking.)
directions: Bring water to a boil; add grits.
Stir in cheese which has been cut into pieces.
Beat eggs; add to grits.
Add margarine and all the remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour grits into a greased 3-quart casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° to 375°.

title: caramel pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Then stir in egg yolks, preserves, vanilla and salt.
Carefully fold in beaten egg whites. Divide between 2 baked shells.
Bake in a slow 300° to 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: avocado salad dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients except mayonnaise.
Mix in the mayonnaise and blend until smooth.
Fill avocado center with mixture or pour over avocado, grapefruit and orange slices for salads.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, water and salt.
Stir until sugar is almost dissolved.
Place on top of stove on high heat.
Peel potatoes.
Slice in half, then slice 3 or 4 long pieces.
As you cut potatoes, drop them in the water and sugar mixture.
Cook on high heat about 10 minutes and then to medium heat for about 20 minutes or until tender.
Cook these uncovered, the juice will boil down and thicken.
(Do not worry if syrup mixture does not cover potatoes when put in pot.
They wil soon cook down into syrup.) Add butter and when syrup has cooked down about half, add flavoring and pour into shallow baking dish, 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inches.
Sprinkle 2 or 3 teaspoons of sugar over potatoes and run under broiler, about 5 to 10 minutes to glaze and brown a bit.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rhubarb jam or topping
directions: Cook rhubarb, sugar and cherries with juice until rhubarb is tender (about 10 minutes).
Add 1 can crushed pineapple.
Boil again.
Remove from the heat.
Add raspberry jello and stir well. Cool.
Put in jars and refrigerate or freeze.
Good over ice cream or on toast or over pancakes.

title: christmas morning pancakes
directions: Fold liquid into dry mixture until blended.
Add 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Cook on grill.
Makes 18 large pancakes.
Batter looks thick and heavy, but pancakes are very light.
Serve with the best New York state maple syrup.

title: chicken crescent pockets
directions: Mix chicken, cream cheese, milk, seasonings and sesame seeds. Divide crescent rolls into 8 triangles or 4 squares. Fill with mixture and fold tops over and press to seal around edges. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: caramel squares
directions: Mix brown sugar and butter.
Let boil a few minutes.
When cool, add egg and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Will be soft.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes, covered, for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cool, then peel and cube.
Cover with Italian dressing, then toss lightly. Let marinate for a while, then drain off the dressing.
Combine other ingredients. Mix well and add to potatoes.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook vegetables in 3/4 cup water until tender.
Drain.
Add mushrooms, pimentos and a little Parmesan cheese.
Add Hidden Valley dressing.
Pour all ingredients into Pam sprayed baking dish.
Lightly shake a little more cheese over the top.
Bake at 375° until browned on top.

title: chicken dish
directions: Mix all together and top with grated cheese and crushed potato chips.
Heat 10 minutes at 450° and serve.
Serves 6.

title: banana sherbet
directions: Puree all ingredients in a blender until smooth.
Pour mixture into paper cups and freeze until slushy.
Insert plastic spoons or clean craft sticks, then freeze until solid.
To serve, turn cup upside down and run under hot water just until frozen sherbet pop slides out.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook hen; boil to make broth.
Simmer onion, green chilies, enchilada sauce and chicken broth.
Add chicken (diced), shredded cheese and cream.
Place in baking dish, one layer of sauce, then a layer of tortillas torn in pieces.
Repeat until all tortillas and sauce are used up.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: seafood dip
directions: Melt butter (low heat or in microwave). Cream the cream cheese into the butter.
(Keep on low heat or 1 minute in microwave at 50% power).
Add mayonnaise and seafood.
Add garlic salt (or garlic powder) to taste.
Hollow out bread.
Cut up pieces of bread which were removed from loaf.
Pour dip into hollowed out bread. Dunk pieces of bread into dip.
Serve dip warm.

title: aunt myrtle's fudge balls
directions: Melt over hot water the chips, butter and milk. Remove from heat and add the flour, nuts and vanilla. Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt butter in dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk; pour over butter.
Do not stir. Add fruit; do not stir.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger-rice dish
directions: Saute onion and celery in shortening of your choice.
Add hamburg and cook until no red is showing.
In casserole, empty both soups and one can of water; add the soy sauce.
Add the meat mixture and rice; mix well.
Cover and bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
Remove; sprinkle the noodles evenly and return to oven to cook 20 to 30 minutes more (do not add salt).
Bake, uncovered, after the noodles are added.

title: elvis cake
directions: Cream all ingredients (except nuts). Stir in nuts, then apply to cooled cake. This cake is better if allowed to sit in refrigerator for a day before serving.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease bottom only of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows in cake pan.
In a mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, shortening, baking powder, eggs, milk, vanilla and salt.
Beat at medium for 3 minutes.
Pour over marshmallows.
Mix strawberries and gelatin in a bowl; spread evenly over batter.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown beef in oil over medium-high heat.
Add onion and garlic. Cook until tender.

title: liver casserole
directions: Brown onions and bacon; drain.
Flour liver and brown in bacon grease.
Place in baking dish; top with bacon and onions.
Add milk to bacon grease; stir until thickened.
Pour over liver, onions and bacon.
Melt butter; crumble crackers into butter.
Add onto liver mixture in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Cool in pan for 1 hour.

title: pork chop and lima beans
directions: Cook beans until almost tender.
Add seasonings and place in baking dish.
Add liquid to cover.
Place pork chops on top.
Bake in hot oven until chops sear.
Turn over and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Pack firmly into loaf pan. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Drain off grease and let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: missy potatoes
directions: Combine first seven ingredients.
Spoon into lightly
greased 13 x 9 x 3-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until bubbly.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: fruit and nut breakfast bars
directions: Combine dry ingredients; stir.
In a small bowl, beat eggs, honey and oil with a whisk; add to dry ingredients and mix.
Bake in a 10 x 15-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in mixing bowl.
Set aside.
Heat cocoa, oleo and Coca-Cola to boiling, then pour over flour and sugar, mixing well.
Beat eggs, add buttermilk, soda, vanilla and marshmallows and mix well.
The batter will be thin with marshmallows floating on top.
Bake in a long pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Beat egg with 1 teaspoon lemon juice.
Combine garlic powder, paprika and flour.
Dip chicken in egg, then flour mixture.
Brown chicken in margarine.
Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water; add 2 teaspoons lemon juice.
Add to skillet with chicken.
Cover; let simmer for 20 minutes.

title: vanilla sauce for apple dumplings
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Gradually stir in water.
Boil 1 minute stirring constantly.
Stir in butter and flavoring.
Makes 2 cups.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together well and put into greased casserole.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine.
Add 1/2 box Ritz crackers (crushed) and put on top of vegetables.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: hot dog surprise
directions: Brown the hot dogs.
Saute onion and pepper.
Add tomatoes and simmer 45 minutes.

title: tomato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix Bisquick, water and softened butter.
Press into an 8 or 9-inch pie pan.
Layer tomato slices over dough.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over tomatoes. In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, scallions, parsley and basil. Spread mixture over cheese.
Bake in lower half of oven for 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: ham and macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in 2 1/2 quarts of boiling water and 2 teaspoons of salt.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Chill.
Chop green pepper.
Combine green pepper, celery, ham, onion and macaroni. Add mustard, vinegar and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt to mayonnaise.
Add this to macaroni mixture.
Let stand in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.

title: rhubarb dessert #2
directions: Mix. Pat in 8 inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: steamed herbed potatoes
directions: Layer potato slices and garlic in a steamer; steam over boiling water until potatoes are tender (perhaps 30 minutes or more; test for doneness). In a large mixing bowl, cut up the margarine and put steamed potato slices on top. Sprinkle with the fresh herbs, salt and pepper and toss gently so as to avoid breaking the potatoes up too much. Serve immediately.

title: corn dish
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 12-inch pan or baking dish.
Mix all ingredients in baking dish.
Spread cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: white chili
directions: Saute chicken and onion in skillet.
Reserve 1/2 c. broth.
In soup pan, add beans, broth, chillies, cumin and chicken.
Take the 1/2 cup broth and add with the white gravy mix.
Add to the soup pan and heat.
Serve with corn bread or tortilla chips.
Top with sour cream and colby cheese.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add beaten eggs; beat well. Add spices with flour and add milk.
Add jam, nuts and raisins. Bake at 300°.

title: overnight bacon casserole
directions: Cut bacon strips crosswise into 1/2-inch pieces.
In skillet cook bacon until crisp; remove.
Drain and crumble on paper towel. Remove crusts from bread and reserve.
Cut bread slices in cubes; set aside.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Arrange rhubarb in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Add marshmallows and 3/4 cup sugar.
Thoroughly cream shortening and 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs; beat thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Pour over rhubarb. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Loosen edge with knife.
Invert serving plate or attractive durable tray over pan; turn cake upside down and remove pan.
Serve with whipped cream. Serves 8.

title: easter bunny salad
directions: Place lettuce leaves on plate, arrange pears on lettuce.
Cut sides down with narrow end of each pear toward center of plate. Place 2 raisins on each pear half for eyes, 1 piece of candy for nose.
Use 2 almonds for ears.
Shape tail with 1 teaspoon of cottage cheese.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add applesauce and nuts.
Mix until well blended.
Pour in pan and let stand for 20 minutes, then bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Press triangles into lightly oiled 12-inch pizza pan, covering it completely.
Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.

title: salmon stew
directions: Remove bones and skin from salmon.
Place in saucepan with pepper, butter, Worcestershire sauce, Texas Pete and paprika. Simmer for about 3 minutes.
Add milk and bring to just boiling. Remove from heat and serve with oyster crackers.

title: babe ruth bars
directions: Put first 2 ingredients into a large greased bowl.
Combine the next 4 ingredients in pan over low heat, stirring constantly with wooden spoon until shiny.
Pour over flakes and nuts and mix. Press gently into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Dampen or oil hands to prevent sticking.) Break up the Hershey bars over cookie base. Heat briefly in oven to soften; spread.
Cut into pieces while base is still warm.
Freezes well.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and serve with sliced apples, pears and grapes.

title: fruit special
directions: Mix together peach pie filling, strawberries with juice, oranges and pineapple chunks. Add bananas just before serving. (Colorful when served in a crystal bowl on a buffet table.)

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream, oregano, garlic powder and cayenne pepper to form bottom layer.
Then layer pizza sauce, green onions, green pepper, sliced pepperoni and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.
(A favorite with my tennis team.)

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Crush crackers; add oleo and sugar.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Soften cream cheese; mix with butter and powdered sugar. Mix until creamy; beat.
Slowly add Cool Whip.
Pour on top of crust.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: bread or rolls
directions: Mix in large bowl warm water and yeast.
Stir until foamy; add small amount of sugar to help dissolve yeast.
Add egg, butter, salt and remaining sugar.
Stir well.
Add flour and mix until dough comes free of hands.
Let stand to rise in bowl 2 hours. Roll dough into loaves or rolls (rolling just enough to form into shape).
If making rolls, put 3 round balls in each muffin space on pan.
Let rise another hour, then bake.
Yields 3 loaves.
Bake at 420° for 25 minutes or 25 to 30 rolls at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: pie-dough dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and 3/4 teaspoon salt into a large bowl.
Using your fingers, work the butter into the dry ingredients, then add enough milk to make a stiff batter.
Turn the dough out onto a heavily floured board and roll to 1/2 inch thick. Cut into 2 inch squares.
Bring the water to a boil, add 2 teaspoons salt and drop in dumplings.
Lower the heat and cook the dumplings at a low boil, covered, for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding, Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip together.
Layer vanilla wafers and bananas as usual.
Cover each layer with mix. Top last layer with crumbled wafers (3 or 4).
Makes a large bowl.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add mushrooms with juice, mushroom soup and green beans. Pour into a 7 x 11-inch baking dish and cover with Tater Tots. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: red wine marinated lamb chops
directions: Mince the garlic.
Combine it with the wine in a shallow baking dish.
Add the chops; turn them to coat with the marinade.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Heat the broiler.
Remove the chops from the marinade and scrape off the garlic.
Put the chops on a rack in a broiler pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Broil until brown, about 5 minutes on each side.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix and roll into balls the size of marbles.
Melt 2 packages dipping chocolate and 1 package paraffin.
Dip balls in chocolate and drop on wax paper.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: low cholesterol cream cheese pound cake
directions: No milk, baking powder, baking soda or salt needed.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Place in greased casserole. Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: molasses spice cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light.
Beat in egg and molasses.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Chill several hours.
Shape into balls size of walnuts or larger; roll in granulated sugar.
Put on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: apple pie
directions: Pour apple pie filling into one of the pie crusts.
Add cinnamon and sugar on top.
Cut pieces of butter and place over apples.
Take other pie crust and cut into strips.
Place on top of apples.
Pinch sides together.
Take fork and punch a couple of places in top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: meat ball appetizers
directions: Place all ingredients in large crock-pot and cook until warm. Serve.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add 2 cups cold water.
Pour into desired containers and freeze.
Serves 6.

title: party-time popcorn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine popcorn, pretzels, crackers and peanuts in large roasting pan.
Stir butter, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce in a small cup.
Pour over popcorn mixture, stirring to coat evenly.
Bake 15 minutes or until heated through. Yields 10 cups.

title: scones
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Cut in shortening. Add buttermilk and mix.
Roll dough out 1/2-inch thick and cut into about 2 1/2-inch rounds. Cook on well-greased moderately hot griddle for 4 to 5 minutes on each side or bake them at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: microwave bread and butter pickles
directions: Place all ingredients in glass cake pan.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 7 minutes.
Uncover and stir. Re-cover and let cool.
Put in sterilized jar.
Makes 1 pint.

title: beef ball
directions: Chop fine onion and
half
of
the green tops; chop fine beef. Save 1 package
for the
ball.
Beef
and onions should look like confetti.
Do
not
use the blender or food processor on the onion.
Mix
cheese, Accent and the Worcestershire sauce until blended.
Add
onions
and
packages
of chopped beef. After thoroughly mixed form
the ball and roll in the remainder of the beef.
This
makes
one
large or two medium size balls. Serve or freeze for later use.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Put everything in blender.
Beat 3 minutes.
Pour into deep 10-inch dish, greased well.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes own crust.

title: tomato scallop
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes, then at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry treats
directions: Mix 2 boxes of gelatin, 3/4 cup condensed milk, pecans and coconut together well.
(Chill 2 hours.)
Mold in hands, small spoonfuls, and form in berry shape.
Roll in remaining gelatin and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add red food coloring; mix well.
(Make sugar mixture early to dry for rolling.)
Add green food coloring to almond slivers; stir.
Lay on paper towel to dry.
Put in top of berry for stem.
Chill.

title: domino sugar pound cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream margarine and sugar. Add vanilla and eggs (one at a time), beating after each is added.
Alternately add flour
mixture and milk.

title: fat-free texas bean soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 5-quart crock-pot.
Cover and cook for 10 to 12 hours on low heat or 4 to 5 hours on high heat.
Add water from time to time, if necessary.
This can be done in the oven at 250° with cover.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Place chicken between waxed paper and pound until 1/8-inch thick.
Melt butter in frying pan; add chicken and cook uncovered over medium-high heat until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add lemon juice and stir gently.
Remove chicken with slotted spoon to serving dish and keep warm.
Return frying pan to high heat and add cream and mustard.
Boil rapidly, uncovered, stirring until large shiny bubbles form.
Drain any juice from chicken into sauce.
Spoon sauce over chicken and serve with buttered noodles or rice.

title: bean hot dish
directions: Fry hamburger with small pieces of bacon.
Drain.
Place this and remaining ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: lemony no-bake cheese cake
directions: In small bowl dissolve gelatin in boiling water, set aside. In medium bowl beat cream cheese with electric mixer until smooth. Gradually beat in dissolved gelatin.
Fold whipped topping into cheese mixture.
Pour into crust.
Chill 4 hours.
Serve with favorite pie filling if desired.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: In large dutch water, seasonings and beef.
Cook until beef is done but still firm.
Add remainder of ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce to low heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: lemon baked alaska
directions: Melt butter and add juice, salt and sugar.
Beat egg with egg yolks and add to butter mixture.
Cook until thick, cool.
Spread 1 pint ice cream in crust and freeze.
Cover with half sauce.
Freeze and then repeat the ice cream and sauce layers.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar and gradually add sugar.
Spread over pie and bake in very hot oven until brown.
Freeze until ready to use. Will keep well for a couple of weeks in freezer.

title: british light carrot soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter. Add carrots and spices. Saute a bit longer. Add stock. Simmer 25 minutes. Cool. Put in blender. Return to pot and add milk when reheating. Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and pudding according to package directions. Bake cake in 2 (9-inch) round pans.
Layer into a large punch bowl.
Layer yellow cake, 1/2 vanilla pudding, 1/2 quart strawberries with glaze, 1/2 pineapple with juice, 1/2 Cool Whip and 1/2 cup nuts.
Repeat layers.
Chill and serve.

title: pineapple waldorf salad(adapted from "dole" pineapple recipe.)
directions: Combine pineapple, apples, nuts and celery.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mash 1 pint of strawberries until juice is well extracted, bring to boil.
Add sugar mixed with cornstarch and cook until clear and thick.
Place 1 pint of whole berries in the baked pastry shell.
Pour over these the hot cooked berries, then place in refrigerator until very cold.
Top with sweetened whipped cream before serving.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Split wings at the joint and throw away the tips.
Fry wings in deep fryer until they are brown and crispy.
In the microwave or in a small saucepan, melt together the butter and hot sauce. Pour the mixture over the cooked chicken wings and stir until all are coated.
Serve with celery sticks and Blue Cheese dressing.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Have more flour to be added later.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together sugars and oil; add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients and lastly, add apples and nuts.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13 inch greased pan.
Batter will be thick.
Sprinkle with mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Bake approximately 45 minutes to an hour in a 375°F oven.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all together.
Put in graham cracker crust and chill.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add milk, lemon and vanilla gradually.
Put in crust and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: quick pickled vegetables
directions: Separate cauliflower into small florets.
Cut red pepper into wide strips.
Cut zucchini into spears.
Put vegetables in one 3-quart jar or smaller jars.
Combine mustard seeds, peppercorns, coriander seeds, red pepper flakes, salt and sugar in large saucepan with 1 1/2 quarts water.
Bring to a boil and cook until sugar and salt have dissolved, about 5 minutes.
Pour hot liquid, the vinegar and 1/2 quart water over vegetables.
Let cool.
Cover and chill at least 3 days before serving.
Store in refrigerator. Makes 3 quarts.

title: perfectly easy dinner rolls
directions: Combine the warm water and yeast in a large bowl.
Let the mixture stand until yeast is foamy, about 5 minutes.

title: cherry pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth. Spread on top and sides of cake.

title: carolyn's chicken
directions: Line casserole with bacon strips; add rice, salt, pepper, chicken and place over rice.
Sprinkle lightly with oregano or paprika.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix crackers with melted butter and poppy seed.
Line 9 x 13-inch
glass
pan with 2/3 cracker mixture.
Place chopped chicken breasts
over cracker crust.
Mix soup and sour cream. Place remaining cracker mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend sugar, eggs, vanilla and oil.
Sift dry ingredients together and blend with sugar mixture.
Add chopped apples.
Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add dry ingredients with milk, alternately, then add flavoring.
Bake at 300°.
Start in a cold oven.
Bake 1 1/2 hours until done.

title: cinnamon ornaments(non-edible)
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then knead until mixture turns into a firm clay.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: twice-baked squash
directions: Line a large baking pan with foil. Halve squash lengthwise.
Remove seeds.
Place squash, cut side down, in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn cut side up. Bake, covered, 20 to 25 minutes or until nearly tender.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with cracker crumbs.
Use 1/2 in bottom of pan.
Beat milk, cool whip, sugar and cheese.
Spread 1/2 on crumbs.
Pour 2 can cherry pie filling mix on that.
Add remaining cool whip.
Top with rest of crumbs.
Chill overnight.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Brown onion and ham in margarine.
Add soup, cheese and milk.
Stir in cooked macaroni. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs. Dot with margarine (about 2 tablespoons).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dirt pie
directions: Freeze Oreo cookies.
Crumb cookies in blender or food processor into fine crumbs.
Place 1/3 of crumbs into pail or flowerpot.
Next mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and oleo; mix well.
Add the pudding and milk; mix well.
Let set 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place pudding mixture on top of cookie crumbs, then the rest of the cookie crumbs.

title: crab cheese muffins
directions: Rinse crab with water and drain.
Mix all ingredients together, except muffins, adding crab meat last.
Cut muffins in quarters.
Spread mixture on muffins.
Freeze muffins on a try for 30 minutes.
Broil until lightly browned or bubbly.
Freeze extra crab cheese muffins.
Store in plastic bag.

title: wild rice and chicken hot dish
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand overnight.
Add grated cheese and crushed potato chips on top before baking.
Bake at 300° 1 hour.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Day before (or earlier in day, since it needs to cool), make filling.
In saucepan, mix undrained pineapple with sugar.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup cold water. Add to mixture, then cook and stir one to two minutes longer. Remove from heat and cool.

title: scalloped corn
directions: With the exception of the butter and approximately 1/4 c. of the cracker crumbs, mix all other ingredients in a well greased casserole dish.
Use balance of the cracker crumbs to top casserole and pour the butter over this.
Bake at 350 degrees approximately 45 minutes.

title: abby's cheesecake
directions: Melt butter and add to graham cracker crumbs and sugar.
Line bottom of a spring-form pan, packing firmly.

title: potato pierogi casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Saute onions.
Make mashed potatoes and add cream cheese.
Layer noodles, then potatoes.
Put sauteed onions on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Preheat oven according to brownie package directions.
Bake brownies according to package directions; let cool.
Meanwhile, prepare chocolate mousse according to package directions.
Break candy bars into small pieces.
Break up half the brownies into small pieces and place in bottom of large glass bowl.
Cover with 1/2 mousse, then 1/2 candy and then 1/2 Cool Whip.
Repeat layers.

title: hamburger surprise
directions: Cook noodles with bouillon cubes.
Drain and spread in buttered 9 x 13 pan.
Cook ground beef with onion, drain.
Mix with tomato paste, garlic salt, pepper, and water.
Cook 3 minutes then spoon over noodles.
Beat cream cheese.
Add cream of mushroom soup and sour cream until blended.
Pour over mixture. Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes until heated through.
Top with shredded cheddar cheese.
Bake 5 minutes until cheese is melted. Yields 8 servings.

title: cheesecake supreme
directions: Mix and press into greased pie pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.

title: oven fried chicken #1
directions: You will also need cooking spray and a shaker bag.

title: fruit punch
directions: Chill ginger ale until ice crystals form.
Add the frozen fruit punch.
Mix well and enjoy.
Easy to transport and tasty, too.

title: death by chocolate
directions: After brownies cool, use fork to punch holes in brownies. Pour Kahlua or extract over brownies.
Allow time to soak in.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions. Drain. Mix with soup until well blended. Pour into a 9x13 pan. Place cheese slices on top, covering all areas. Top with tater tots, making sure to spread evenly and covering as much area as possible. Bake at 350° until tater tots are golden brown.

title: jello pie
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water.
Add ice cubes.
Stir constantly until it sets (won't be solid).
After it thickens, take out remaining ice cubes.
Add Cool Whip.
Blend well.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Chill until firm.

title: poached pears
directions: Pare, quarter
and
core apples and pears.
Brush fruit with lemon
juice.
Combine
orange juice rind, sugar and salt in a large
skillet.
Heat to boiling point.
Add fruit; cover and simmer until just tender, about 15 minutes.
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cajun dirty rice
directions: Add onion, bell pepper and garlic to roux; stir, then put in large pot.
Stir in water.
Add meats and stir.
Cook 1 1/2 hours over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Stir in parsley, then green onion.
Add cooked rice to meat mixture, a little at a time.
Mix well until all rice is added.
Eat hot or cold.
Freezes well. Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: pork chop and sauerkraut
