directions: Flour chops and brown in oil.
Remove from pan; set aside. Add next ingredients in same pan; mix gently together.
Add potatoes; add chops on top.
Cover and cook over medium heat. Simmer 30 minutes.	Add apple wedges and cook for 10 minutes or until apple and chops are tender.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger. Drain until very dry. Add taco seasoning and mix well with meat. In bowl, mix lettuce, tomatoes, onion and cheese. Add hamburger. Pour dressing over this. It won't take the whole bottle. When ready to serve, crush bag of Doritos and add to salad.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer in casserole:
eggs, bacon, sour cream, and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: beef-chicken magnificent
directions: Spread beef in greased baking dish.
Wrap each chicken breast in slice of bacon.
Place on top of beef.
Combine cheese, soup, and water; pour over chicken.
Cover & bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°. Uncover and bake 1 hour.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except crust and pie filling) together. Beat on low speed until well blended.
Put into already made pie crust.
Chill for 1 hour.
Top with pie filling and chill another hour.

title: chicken pot pie made easy
directions: Take one can of croissants and layer it in 9 X 12 Pyrex dish. Dice up chicken - put it on

top of croissants. Bring the 2 cans of soup and whipping cream to a boil and let simmer until it thickens. Pour it over chicken. Then put the last can of croissants on top of that. Bake on 350° until the top browns - about 20 minutes.

title: chewy ginger cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat. Remove from heat and cool 10 minutes. Add sugar, molasses and egg and beat well. Sift together next 6 ingredients. Add to butter/sugar mixture and mix well. Chill 1 hour. Form into 1-inch balls. Roll in sugar and place on greased cookie sheet 2-inches apart. Bake 7 to 8 minutes at 350°. Do not overbake. Yield: 36.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Melt cheese over hot water.
Add milk and blend well.
Add pimentos, mayonnaise, sugar and salt to taste.
If too thick, add some pickle juice.

title: impossible pie cake
directions: Blend in blender and pour into 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Can top with Cool Whip.
Delicious.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Melt butter in deep (1 1/2-quart) casserole.
Place blintzes down flat.
Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and sour cream together until smooth.
Pour over blintzes.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour. Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: pineapple side dish
directions: Spray 9x13-inch pyrex dish with Pam.
Pour in pineapple. Sprinkle with sugar and flour.
Add cheese.
Mix melted oleo, crushed ritz crackers and spread over cheese.
Bake uncovered 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ice cream pumpkin pie
directions: In large bowl mix pumpkin, milk, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Beat well.
Stir in softened ice cream.
Spoon into crust. Freeze 5 hours or until firm.
Let pie stand at room temperature 10 minutes before serving.
Garnish with whipped cream and nuts.

title: scalloped corn(pudding)
directions: Mix all ingredients evenly.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: butterfly leg of lamb curry
directions: Make marinade and marinate lamb for at least one hour or more. Cook on grill until medium.
Check after 15 minutes on each side.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Peel eggplant, if desired.
Slice crosswise in 1/4-inch slices.
Brush lightly with oil.
Dip each slice in bread crumbs or breading mixture.
Bake on oiled cookie sheet in a 400° oven, turning once when brown.
Delicious when eaten as is.

title: no fail pie crust(for a double crust pie)
directions: Mix.
Knead just a little.
Roll out on flour.
Will make a 9-inch pie.

title: caramel icing
directions: Combine all but butter and cook at high heat until brown and spins a thread.
Add butter and stir well.
Pour over Jam Cake (recipe in this book).

title: bow tie pasta with chicken and sun-dried tomatoes
directions: In frying pan, saute oil and garlic and add chicken.
Saute more and push chicken to side of pan.
Add broccoli, sun-dried tomatoes and seasonings.
Add wine, broth and butter.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over cooked bow tie pasta.

title: marshmallow truffles
directions: Put marshmallows on cookie sheet and freeze 15 minutes. Microwave chocolate chips on High for 2 1/2 minutes, until smooth, stirring every minute.
Using a skewer or fondue fork, dip each marshmallow in the melted chocolate until completely coated.
Roll in coconut or candies.
Use another fork or metal spatula to put marshmallows on waxed paper.
Chill or keep in a cool place. Makes 38 to 40 truffles.

title: chicken divan
directions: Combine soup, mayo, lemon juice, onion, salt and pepper.
Lay broccoli in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place chicken breasts on top of broccoli.
Pour soup mixture over and sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Put soup, water, potatoes and pepper in large pot.
Lightly brown ground beef.
Drain off grease.
Add onions and cook until clear.
Add to soup.
Bring to boil.
Cover and cook on medium heat until potatoes are done.

title: strawberry angel pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups boiling water; chill until mixture is partially set.
Fold in Cool Whip, then add strawberries.
Chill until it starts to gel, then spoon into pie shell and chill overnight.

title: coconut broiled frosting cake
directions: Make cake mix as directed and bake in 9X13-inch pan.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, milk, butter and Karo to a soft ball stage (234°).
Take off heat, add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Cut when ready.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, nutmeg and butter.
Add eggs; beat smooth. Pour over rhubarb in a 9-inch pastry shell.
Top pie with pastry shapes or crumbs.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: italian meat casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Melt 1/4 cup of butter in skillet; saute onions and beef with seasonings until meat is brown, stirring often with fork.
Add 1 1/3 cups of cheese to meat mixture; stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Mix 2 tablespoons of butter with macaroni.
Add meat mixture, 1 1/2 cans tomato sauce and mushrooms and mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining tomato sauce and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin dessert(low-fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray individual glass baking dishes with a no-stick cooking spray.
Fill dishes with equal amounts of mixture and bake at 425° until knife comes out clean. Less than 1 gram of fat per serving.

title: hot pepper rings
directions: Mix solution of water, oil, vinegar, oregano, garlic and pickling salt.
Pour over pepper rings and soak in refrigerator overnight.
Remove peppers from solution.
Boil solution.
Pack pepper rings in jars.
Pour hot solution in jars over pepper rings.
Seal.

title: barbecued corned beef
directions: Brown hamburger and onion and drain.
Add flour and mix.
Add all other ingredients and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and cocoa.
Add milk, oil, nuts and vanilla; mix only until smooth.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: "party food" armadillo eggs
directions: Remove jalapeno seeds after cutting in half lengthwise; dry with paper towel.
Mix pan sausage with 1 cup shredded cheese and biscuit mix.
Place a strip of Monterey Jack cheese the length of the jalapeno.
With hands, wrap piece of jalapeno completely with the sausage mixture in an egg shape.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam. Place completed armadillo eggs on cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pleasin' pea salad
directions: Combine peas, celery, cheese, olives and onion in a medium mixing bowl.
In a small bowl blend remaining ingredients until smooth.
Add to pea mixture.
Stir to combine.
Serve chilled. Serves 4.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Stir together dry ingredients.
Add zucchini, nuts and raisins.
Beat eggs and oil together.
Add to flour mixture and stir until moistened.
Turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mrs. ollie lombard's cake recipe
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and Crisco well. Gradually add milk and flour alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Add eggs last, one at a time, then flavoring of your choice.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes to 2 hours, according to your oven.

title: cinnamon cookies(diabetic)
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour and baking powder.
Mix together.
Mix Sucaryl, vanilla and milk. Stir into flour mixture and mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle cinnamon over dough and knead.
Shape dough into balls about 1/2-inch in diameter and arrange on a cookie sheet.
Flatten balls with a fork dipped in cold water.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: cheese ring - "plains special"
directions: Mix and mold in ring.
Place in refrigerator until chilled. Unmold onto plate and fill center with strawberry preserves. Serve with Waverly crackers.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: chicken or turkey 5 can casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Spread crumbled potato chips on top.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: dill weed dip
directions: This dip is good in a solid loaf of rye or pumpernickel bread, hollowed out.
Dip in the hollow and pieces of bread around outside to use for dipping.
Real good.

title: jeanie's potato delight
directions: Peel, cook and mash potatoes.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, margarine, salt and pepper to taste.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in chives.
Put mixture in casserole.
Dot with margarine or sprinkle with paprika.
Heat in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: bread pudding
directions: Pour melted butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs and add milk, vanilla and sugar.
Add bread crumbs and raisins.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Yield: Approximately 12 servings.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Place ribs in shallow pan, meaty side up.
Toothpick slice of unpeeled lemon and slice of onion on each rib; roast in hot 450° oven 30 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients; heat to boiling; pour over ribs; continue baking at about 350° until tender, about 1 hour.
Baste ribs with sauce every 15 minutes.
Serve with hot biscuits!

title: 3 layer fudge cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar together, then add eggs, one at a time. Keep beating until fluffy.
Beat in vanilla.
In 4-cup measure, mix flour and salt.
In another bowl, mix buttermilk and soda well.
Melt chocolate in the water (2 minutes in microwave) to the creamed mix.
Pour in flour alternately with buttermilk mixture. Whip smooth, then add warm chocolate; mix well, scraping bowl several times, while mixing.
Pour into 3 greased and floured pans (9-inch) for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: slovak beet horseradish
directions: Grate beets and add to horseradish.
Combine vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and water.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over grated beets and horseradish.
Mix thoroughly.
Store in jar in refrigerator and serve with meat.

title: easy seafood fettucine
directions: In large pot, saute onion, garlic, celery and green pepper in oleo.
Add flour.
Let cook; add half and half and cook until blended.
Add cheese; cook until melted.
Add seafood and cook 20 to 25 minutes; season to taste.
Cook noodles until tender in another pot.
When done, drain and add noodles to seafood mixture and cook 20 minutes.
Serve.
Great with French bread and salad!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend oil and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add zucchini.
Sift together the flour, cinnamon, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add to first mixture and beat well.
Pour in loaf pans (greased and floured).
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: corn bread pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain and add soup, water, corn, chili powder and salt.
Place mixture in a large iron skillet or 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: nut roll
directions: Mix well by hand. Roll in coconut.
Makes 4 rolls.
Put in foil and let stay overnight.

title: water chestnut appetizers
directions: Mix ketchup and brown sugar together.
Cut each slice of bacon into 4 (4-inch) strips.
Wrap strip around water chestnut.
Secure with toothpick.
Place in baking dish.
Drizzle with ketchup and brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 to 35 minutes. May be kept warm in crock-pot.

title: fluffy fruit dip
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Whip with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Serve chilled with your favorite fruit.

title: apricot pork chops
directions: Drain apricots, reserving 1/4 cup syrup.
Set aside.
Brown pork chops in skillet.
Pour off excess fat.
Stir in soup, sour cream, reserved syrup and green onions.
Cover.
Simmer 25 minutes or until done, stirring occasionally.
Add apricots.
Cook 5 more minutes.
Serve with pasta.
Serves 4.

title: coconut pie(filling for 2 pies.)
directions: Mix and put in unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° until filling is firm and brown (approximately 40 minutes).

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Bring to a boil the sauerkraut in a small amount of water. Cook about 15 minutes.
To this mixture, add cabbage and cook about 10 minutes until cabbage is wilted.
Add more water if needed.
Drain in colander.
Make sure all water is gone.

title: microwave chicken or chops
directions: Make
a slit and fill with favorite stuffing.
Place on grooved
meat tray.
Spread with apricot preserves.
Place wax paper loosely on top.
Microwave full power for eight minutes. Turn
and
spread
with
apricot
preserves
and microwave for additional seven minutes.
Let stand five minutes and serve.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, oleo, oatmeal, salt, vanilla and syrup.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. This tastes just like pecan pie.

title: peppermint cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream shortening, sugar, egg and flavorings.
Mix in flour and salt.
Divide dough in half.
Blend food coloring into one portion.
Roll 1 teaspoon each of colored and plain dough into two 4-inch strips.
Twist the two strips together and curve top to form a cane.
Bake about 9 minutes. While warm, sprinkle cookies with combination of candy and sugar.

title: baked chocolate pudding
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Combine Crisco, vanilla and milk.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts and mix.
Pour into greased baking dish (5 x 9-inch or 8-inch square).
Cover with this mixture.
Mix together 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter in dish.
Pour 1 cup water over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.
If you use a glass dish, bake at 325°.
Tastes best while warm and you can add ice cream if desired.

title: walnut onion bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart round casserole.
In a medium bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda. Stir in walnuts.
With a fork blend in buttermilk, butter and onion until moist.
Turn onto lightly floured surface.
Knead 2 to 3 minutes, until dough forms a ball, adding more flour if necessary.
Dough will be slightly sticky.
Place in a casserole; score top with an "X".
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Remove from casserole and cool on a wire rack.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour and baking powder.
Add rest.
Don't handle dough more than is necessary.
Roll to one-half inch thickness.
Cut and pat milk on top of each.
Bake in hot oven, 450°, for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: christmas chapel cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter, and add 1 beaten egg.
Cool. Fold in 3 cups miniature marshmallows.
Form into a roll.
Roll in nuts or coconut, and wrap in foil to refrigerate.
Slice when firm.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain and rinse.
Combine spaghetti and vegetables in a large bowl.
Add salad dressing and mix.
Add salad seasoning and mix thoroughly. Chill and serve.
Makes large amount.
It is good for potlucks. Stores well in the refrigerator.

title: chicken with wild rice
directions: Pour packet of rice into baking pan. Cut chicken into pieces (you may skin, if desired).
Place chicken on top of rice.
Pour soup on chicken.
Mix water and wild rice seasoning.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: lime sherbet punch
directions: Have your punch and ginger ale cold and pour into large punch bowl with ice and lime sherbet.
Stir until mixed well.
Serves about 20.

title: mama's snow ice cream
directions: Mix and eat immediately.
If runny, add more snow until you achieve the desire texture.
Note:
Never use snow from the first snow of season.
It's full of pollutants.
Use any snow after the first snow.

title: italian potato salad
directions: Peel and chop cooked potatoes.
Place in a large bowl.
Add dressing and toss to coat.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Add eggs, celery, onion, cucumbers and green peppers.
Mix well.
In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream and horseradish; mix well.
Pour over potato mixture and toss.
Chill at least 1 hour. Top with chopped tomatoes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, Karo, salt, margarine and vanilla.
Put pecans in bottom of pie shell.
Pour mixture over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until brown.

title: corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Combine together all ingredients in large
mixing bowl.
Generously grease muffin pan with corn oil. Pour batter into muffin cups.
Bake until golden brown.

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook beef with salt and pepper and add a little into frying pan until done. Add 1 cup of chili sauce, set aside. Cook tortillas in oil until soft. Fill each tortilla with meat then put into shallow baking pan. Cover with cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: veal marsala
directions: Dredge veal scallops in flour.
Salt and pepper to taste. Melt 3 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Brown 1 clove garlic.
Add veal, browning quickly.
Remove veal to shallow baking pan.
Add 1 tablespoon butter to skillet and brown mushrooms.
Add Marsala cooking wine and bring to a boil.
Simmer about 2 minutes to blend flavors.
Pour wine and mushroom sauce over veal.
Cover and bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: concord grape pie
directions: Slip skins from grapes.
Bring pulp to boiling; press through sieve to remove seeds; add skins.
Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add to grapes; fill 9-inch pastry-lined pie pan, dot with small pieces of butter.
Cover with lattice top crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: banana pudding for diabetics
directions: Make pudding as directed on box.
Layer in dish the wafers, pudding and bananas, ending with the pudding on top.
Can substitute sugar-free chocolate pudding.
Pineapple in its own syrup can be added to vanilla pudding to make a refreshing dessert.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Bottom Layer:
Dissolve Knox gelatine in the 1/4 cup hot water; set aside.
Stir the sugar into the unwhipped heavy cream. Heat sugar and cream until it bubbles, then add to gelatine mixture.
Add vanilla and sour cream; stir until lumps disappear. Place into mold.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: rhoda's yorkshire pudding
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Mix eggs and milk briefly.
Combine both mixtures in blender for 3 to 5 seconds, just until mixed.
(May mix by hand.)
Pour hot beef drippings in pan.
Pour mix on top. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil for 5 minutes, then cool to lukewarm.
Add 2 pints fresh strawberries and fold into the syrupy mixture.
Pour into baked pie shells.

title: sigma sigma sigma bean casserole
directions: Mix beans and mushrooms then sprinkle with cheese in a casserole dish.
Drizzle with butter, add the tomato and mix well. Bake in a preheated oven at approximately 325° for about 25 to 30 minutes.
(This casserole will adjust easily to whatever else is in the oven.)

title: pineapple-zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, sugar and flavorings.
Beat until foamy. Stir in zucchini and drained pineapple.
Combine remaining ingredients and blend well.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans and divide batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix together flour and salt and add 2 1/2 cups water.
Beat until smooth and gradually add 2 cups hot water.
Boil until clear.
Beat until smooth.
Add food coloring; store in jars.

title: white sauce
directions: Mix Kraft barbecue sauce as a base.
Add Catalina dressing, Dale's sauce, Worcestershire sauce, a touch of Tabasco, seasoned salt and pepper and anything else that sounds good.
Mix it all up. Marinate meat in sauce and use during cooking.

title: sweet and sour salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegars together.
Add all other ingredients to bowl; mix together well.
Chill at least 1 to 2 hours.
Delicious!

title: tuna casserole
directions: Add all ingredients. Mix and place in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Shape mixture into 1-inch balls. Place 2-inches apart on a lightly greased or sprayed jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch). Place in a preheated 350° oven and bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown. Remove from pan immediately and serve warm.
Makes about 7 dozen balls.

title: fabulous fudge dip
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients except vanilla, liqueur and fruit.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture comes to a full boil, 18 to 20 minutes.
Boil, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and liqueur. Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes 3 cups.

title: chocolate-covered cherry cookies
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flour, cocoa powder, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
In mixer bowl, beat together butter or margarine and sugar on low speed of electric mixer until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture; beat until well blended.

title: easy sombrero roll-ups
directions: Stir garlic powder and Tabasco in dip.
Spoon 1/4 of dip over each tortilla, spreading to edges.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of chicken on each tortilla.
Roll up.
Place seam side down in flat dish; cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Cut each roll into 6 (1-inch) pieces.
Serve with picante sauce.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: russian chicken
directions: Marinate the chicken with all ingredients listed.
Place in the refrigerator for one day. (The longer it marinates the better!)
Bake, slowly, in oven at about 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: stuffed "ponce"
directions: Clean ponce well.
(Use pliers to remove inner film.)
Put raw ground pork and other ingredients into bowl.
Work well with hands until well mixed.
Add seasoning.
Stuff mixture into ponce.
Sew it up.
Place in a thick pot with enough oil to keep from sticking and cook over low heat.
Add a little water from time to time and be careful not to break skin while handling.
Cook, covered, for about 2 hours.

title: peppermint brownies
directions: Melt chocolate with butter.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar and eggs into chocolate-peppermint extract.
Add flour and the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in a 9-inch square pan.
Cool.

title: cheese and bacon quiche
directions: Cube Swiss cheese and Cheddar cheese to
cover bottom of unbaked pie shell.	Mix all ingredients together
and
bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Sprinkle crumbs in the bottom of a baking dish.
Mix cheese with well seasoned white sauce.
Place alternate layers of sliced eggs, asparagus and sauce in the dish.
Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper and cover the top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mexican plate dip
directions: Place in pie plate in order given.
Cover top with cheese. Leave in refrigerator to set.

title: melissa's southwestern black bean salsa
directions: Gently mix together and serve with tortilla chips.

title: baked corn chips
directions: Scrape each tortilla with a small amount of soft margarine. Cut tortillas, several at a time, into pie-shaped wedges, using kitchen shears.
Arrange in a single layer on a cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until crisp and slightly browned (10 minutes).
Store in an airtight container.
Yield:
8 cups.
Contains 114 calories per cup (21% fat).

title: party cheese ball
directions: Cream together and shape into ball.
Roll in chopped pecans or chopped parsley.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Slice tops off pepper, remove seeds.
Place in boiling water for 5 minutes, drain.
Combine other ingredients.
Fill peppers. Top each with Sauce Topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease bottom only of loaf pan 9 x 5 x 3 in.

title: hot meat dip
directions: Brown meats; drain all fat.
Add cheese, soup and tomatoes. Heat until melted and bubbling.
Put in crock-pot to keep warm. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: grandma's pound cake
directions: Cream together Crisco, butter, sugar, sour cream and eggs; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into prepared Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese; mix altogether.
Roll in nuts.

title: marinated cucumbers and onions
directions: Mix water, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Cut cucumbers and onions and stir into mixture.
Sprinkle parsley and chives on top.
Chill for 4 hours.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and Crisco with knives or pastry blender. Mix water, egg and vinegar. Pour into flour mixture and mix with fork into a ball. Makes 3 pie crusts.

title: chili con carne
directions: Grind steak and put in kettle with enough cold water to cover; start to boil slowly.
Grind bacon, green pepper, red pepper and onion together.
Fry slowly until tender.
Mix with cooking round steak.
Add tomatoes and salt to taste.
Boil slowly for about an hour, then add kidney beans.
Cook a few minutes more.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: venison tips with gravy
directions: Cut venison steak into small cubes. Saute chopped onions, meat, garlic, and season salt into 1 tablespoon butter until meat becomes brown. Pour mixture of 1/2 cup flour and hot water into skillet to form gravy. Salt and pepper to taste. Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until meat becomes tender.

title: one-step biscuits
directions: Combine sour cream and egg in a large mixing bowl; beat until well blended. Add pancake mix; stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with poppy seeds. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 1 dozen.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in a baking dish.
Combine soup, milk and half of the cheese; pour over chicken.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top; bake 15 minutes longer or until cheese is melted. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve lemon Jell-O in boiling water. Let cool. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, Cool Whip and dissolved Jell-O. Dissolve raspberry Jell-O in boiling water. Add to raspberries and pour over first mixture.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Reserve cheese and cracker crumbs for topping.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: grilled antipasto salad
directions: You will need 4 skewers, metal or wooden.
If using wooden skewers, soak in water for an hour before using.
On each skewer, alternate all ingredients, except Italian dressing and romaine lettuce.
Brush skewers liberally with dressing.
Place over hot coals and grill, turning often, for 8 to 10 minutes, until vegetables are nicely browned.
Serve each skewered salad on a leaf of romaine.
Serves 4.

title: microwave raisin bread pudding with bourbon sauce
directions: Spread cubes in 10 x 6-inch glass dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and salt.
In separate container, microwave milk and butter on High until hot.
Whisk in eggs and pour over bread.
Cook on High for 9 minutes or more until knife is clean.
Rotate once.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Roll crescent rolls into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Fry sausage in skillet and drain.
Crumble and pour over crescent rolls.
Fry hash browns, onion and bell pepper in skillet.
Pour over sausage.
Beat eggs and pour over potatoes.
Top with cheese. Put Polish sausage slices on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Pour salsa on top when serving, if desired.

title: oven bbq pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet over medium high heat 1 teaspoonful of vegetable oil, add pork chops and brown them on both sides.
Place in a casserole dish.
In a bowl mix together chopped onion, 2 Tbsp. vegetable oil, water, vinegar, chili sauce, brown sugar, dry mustard, and hot pepper sauce; pour mixture over chops.
Cover and cook for 40 minutes.
Uncover casserole dish and cook for 20 minutes more.
Serve.

title: bread salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Serve on bed of lettuce.

title: bierocks
directions: Dough:
Buy frozen rolls (Rhodes) dough.
Thaw in refrigerator overnight.
Let stand at room temperature while preparing filling (will rise and make bag tight).
Roll with a rolling pin; spoon filling in center.
Roll out another roll and place on top.
With finger wet edge and pinch edges to seal.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Combine ingredients and place in 2 well-greased 1 pound coffee cans or 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sausage-potato bake
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet and cook; drain.
Mix together soup, milk, onion, pimento, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Place half of potatoes in greased, 2-quart casserole.
Add half of sausage, then half of soup mixture.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Remove cover; sprinkle with cheese and bake another 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: pork pie
directions: Cook
potatoes
and
onion
in
very little water until partly cooked.
Put
meat
on
top
and
do not mix in.
Cook slowly for
about 1 hour.
Add salt and pepper while cooking. Drain excess juice and mash together.
Season to taste, adding cloves and a little poultry seasoning.
Add a little seasoned bread crumbs
to hold
together.
Place
mixing
unbaked
pie shell. Cover with top crust and
bake
at 350° for 45 minutes until crust is baked.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla in mixing bowl until fluffy. Mix flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add to first mixture and stir until blended.
Stir in zucchini and nuts.
Turn into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: christmas nut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together but powdered sugar.
Shape into balls about the size of a quarter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Repeat again when cool.

title: cheese strata
directions: Butter and quarter bread (leaving crusts on); spread quarters overlapping slightly in the bottom of a greased casserole, 9 x 13 x 2-inch.
Sprinkle all the cheese over the bread.
Pour beaten mixture of eggs, milk, salt and pepper over.
Let stand at least 30 minutes (up to 12 hours).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: granny hester's white fruitcake
directions: Grease a tube pan well.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Chop raisins, pineapple and cherries.
Toss with 1/2 cup of the required flour. Separate egg yolks; set whites aside.
Beat yolks until light golden yellow.
Stir in sugar gradually and beat well.
Cream butter; add remaining flour gradually until mixture is smooth. Add egg and sugar mixture.
Add well beaten egg whites.
Gradually add floured fruit.
Add wine; mix thoroughly.
Stir in almonds and pecans.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 250° for 8 hours. Remove and cool on wire rack.

title: cappuccino mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Store in airtight container.

title: chocolate birthday cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a heavy saucepan and cook to a soft ball stage.
Cool and beat until creamy.
Put first layer of frosting on cake real thin.
When frosting is spreadable, finish spreading on cake.
Very good.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown sausage.
Push sausage aside in pot.
Saute onion, bell pepper and celery.
Mix together. Add Lipton onion soup mix, uncooked rice and water.
Cover. Cook over low heat until rice is done. Serve with chicken or pork chops.

title: sands cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour and salt; blend into sugar mixture.
Add nuts.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: creole shrimp
directions: Cook fresh vegetables in olive oil until slightly wilted.
Add all seasonings.
Add red wine and tomatoes. Add cleaned and shelled uncooked prawns.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve with steamed rice.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare and bake brownies according to package directions. Cool.
Prepare mousse, break candy bars into small pieces.
Use large glass bowl (trifle bowl).
Break up 1/2 brownies into small pieces and place in bottom of bowl.
Cover with 1/2 the mousse then 1/2 the candy, then 1/2 the whipped topping.
Repeat layers. Yields up to 24 servings or 1 serious chocoholic!

title: cracker jack cookies
directions: Cream sugars and oleo; add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients; add to egg mixture.
Add oats, cereal and coconut. Bake by heaping teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove at once.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray heavy 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Spread coconut and pecans in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as directed.
Pour over coconut and pecans.
Beat until fluffy and smooth the cream cheese and oleo.
Add powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
While hot, turn out on cookie sheet. Rich and delicious.

title: angel chip cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Stir in egg and vanilla. Sift together flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar and then mix well into creamed ingredients.
Chill overnight in refrigerator or for few hours.
Roll in small balls about the size of hickory nut. Press down little with fork.
Bake in a 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes to a delicate brown.
Loosen from pan while still warm.

title: chili dip
directions: In a medium, microwave safe bowl, mix cream cheese, chili and diced tomatoes.
Microwave on high for 1 minute.
Remove from microwave, stir and repeat until the mixture is hot and thoroughly blended.

title: pineapple chutney
directions: Peel, seed and dice cucumber.
Add cucumber and pineapple with juice to a	4 cup glass measure.
Microwave on High 5 to 7 minutes.
Mix
cornstarch
with
1 tablespoon water until smooth. Stir into
pineapple mixture.
Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes, until
mixture
thickens.
Coarsely chop nuts; stir nuts and mint into
the
hot
chutney.
Great
with poultry or pork.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Let butter set until room temperature.
Add peanut butter, vanilla, corn syrup and powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Add milk and stir.
Crush wafers and 2 1/2 cups and mix.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in the remainder of wafers.
Makes about 40 peanut butter balls.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Mix together the pretzels, sugar and margarine.
Spread in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Add Cool Whip and dash of lemon juice.
Put in refrigerator 2 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Blend bananas, milk, egg and salad oil in large mixing bowl until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 12-inch Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans, sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Chop pepper and onion.
Brown meat; drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer for a couple of hours.
Serve on hamburger rolls, open faced.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
This is a must!
The next day, bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Saute celery and onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients; put in greased casserole dish.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove cover. Top with grated cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and mold into loaf shape.
Bake on cookie sheet about 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Cut up and skin chicken.
Place in baking pan and add salt and pepper.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour mixture of pineapple juice, honey, soy and steak sauce over chicken.
Return to oven and bake 25 minutes, basting with sauce occasionally.
Remove and top chicken with pineapple slices. Return to oven for 10 minutes.
Serve with sauce over chicken.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix well.
Stir in 2 cups shredded peeled zucchini.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with Baker's Joy.
Spread cake mix into pan. Sprinkle 2 to 6 ounces of chocolate chips on top of cake.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: three layer bars
directions: First Layer:
Mix sugar, 1/2 cup margarine and egg in a saucepan over low heat.
Cook until egg is done.
Add to graham cracker crumbs, coconut and nuts.
Stir and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix and beat cake mix, pudding mix, oil, egg and 7-Up for 2 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: peanut butter pie(a 5 star recipe)
directions: Combine
egg
yolks,
cup sugar, 1/4 cup water and salt in top of double boiler; blend.
Add gelatin.
Place over boiling water; beat constantly with rotary beater until thick and fluffy (about 5 minutes).	Cool.

title: mountain pie
directions: Melt oleo in a loaf pan.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar well before adding the milk.
Pour on top of that melted oleo.
Add fruit sweetened to taste.
My favorite is strawberries, rhubarb and raspberries.
Peaches can be used.
Bake 15 minutes in a 400° oven.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 35 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Combine butter, ketchup, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce in pan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken in casserole dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sour cream jello
directions: Mix everything together except the sour cream.
Spread half of the mixture in an 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish and jell.
Spread sour cream over it, then add the remaining mixture on top and refrigerate until set.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together and serve with Hawaiian bread or crackers.

title: wafer cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add 1 egg at a time until 6 have been added.
Put all other ingredients in with the pecans being last. Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 250°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until soft.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Skin and bone chicken.
Break into pieces into a large baking dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup, milk and broth.
Pour over chicken with can of peas.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine; add cocoa.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar and eggs; mix well.
Add flour, salt, nuts and vanilla.
Spoon batter into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons of
margarine until smooth.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, garlic, milk, and onion.
Mix well.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 large rectangles.
Firmly press together seams to seal.
Spoon 1/4 of the mixture into each center.
Pull the sides of the roll over the mixture, overlapping them, and seal.
Brush tops with melted margarine and sprinkle with breadcrumbs.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for
20-25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the butter, sugar and soda.
Add well beaten egg and vanilla.
Blend in remaining ingredients. Place batter in well-buttered loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until it tests done.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Cream together the rind, shortening and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time, and milk; mix well.
Add sifted flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold in nut meats.
Pour into lightly greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 50 to 60 minutes, or until done.
After removing from oven and while bread is hot, pour over the following mixture of 1/3 cup sugar and the juice of 1 lemon.
Remove bread from pan after topping has thoroughly soaked in and bread has cooled somewhat.
Wrap in foil; store in refrigerator.

title: praline cheese cake
directions: Mix ingredients; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes; cool.

title: baked mashed potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes; add butter, sour cream and cream cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: calorie crush
directions: Place all but last 2 ingredients in blender.
Process with an on-off pulsing motion until melon chunks are crushed.
Spoon into individual 6-ounce glasses decorated with fresh strawberries and melon chunks threaded alternately on skewers kabob style.
Makes two 8-ounce glasses.

title: new england sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Use for basting chicken or pork.

title: jello salad
directions: Place Jell-O and crushed pineapple in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Set aside to cool.
Mix together Dream Whip, cream cheese and cold milk.
Add Jell-O mixture and whip.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: tostitos dip
directions: Fry ground chuck until done; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, mash kidney beans.
Add ketchup, chili powder and half the olives. Mix well.
Add bean mixture to ground chuck and mix well.
Pour mixture into crock-pot on low heat.
Take your cheeses and sprinkle on top, then sprinkle the remaining olives on top of cheeses. Serve with Tostitos chips.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in fourths. Roll in the sugar and cinnamon mixture and place in a greased Bundt pan. Melt margarine and pour over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cook 5 to 10 minutes and turn out on serving plate.

title: silk frosting recipe
directions: Mix ingredients together until texture preferred.

title: bean salad
directions: Heat ingredients together until sugar melts.
Do not boil! Add liquid mixture to beans.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cut beef into 1-inch pieces and brown in oil.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Pour over beef.
Simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Serve over rice or with rolls.

title: peaches and cream dessert
directions: Combine the flour, pudding and baking powder. Stir in the egg, milk and melted butter. Spread in greased 9-inch pan or double recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spoon the peaches over mixture. Combine the cream cheese, 9 teaspoons sugar and peach juice. Pour over peaches. Sprinkle the 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon over mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken supreme salad
directions: Mix
all ingredients together.	Chill.	Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to package directions.
When done and still hot, poke holes in cake with handle of wooden spoon. Pour over Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut that has been blended together.
When cool, spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix well oleo, salt, sugar, flour, milk, eggs and creamed corn.
Butter or spray casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until firm.

title: kielbasa casserole
directions: Cut kielbasa sausage into 2-inch pieces. Slash each piece with a sharp knife to cut through the skin and about 1/4-inch into meat.
Place sausage into a 10-inch skillet.
Arrange all of the peppers and onion rings around the sausage.
In a screw-top jar, combine the beer and prepared mustard. Cover and shake well. Pour mixture into skillet.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Serve sausage and onion with a slotted spoon.

title: good for you snack
directions: Mix together the first three ingredients.
Add nuts and raisins.
Roll into balls and roll in graham cracker crumbs.

title: herb biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients just until dry ingredients are moist. Turn out on floured surface and knead lightly four or five times. Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut into diamonds or rounds. Bake in a preheated 450° oven for 8 minutes or until brown.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending well after each addition.
Sift flour and add alternately with evaporated milk.
Blend well after each addition. Add flavorings and blend well.
Pour into well-greased tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with a layer of graham crackers.
Spread half pudding mixture on top.
Cover with another layer of graham crackers.
Spread remaining pudding mixture.
Top with a third layer of graham crackers.
Frost top layer with chocolate frosting.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Serve chilled.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain.
Place hamburger, onion, macaroni, salt, pepper, tomato sauce and Ranch Style beans in a casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: one pan pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch. Stir all ingredients except raisins in pan with fork until moistened.
Beat vigorously 1 minute.
Stir in raisins.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Turn knife or metal spatula around sides of loaf to loosen.
Remove from pan.
(If loaf sticks, press gently on sides of loaf with knife or metal spatula.)
Yields one loaf.

title: crock-pot shredded pork
directions: Put all ingredients into a crock-pot and cook on high for about 6 to 8 hours.
Pull meat apart with 2 forks until completely shredded.

title: couscous salad
directions: In large skillet, melt the margarine with the saffron/curry over moderate heat, stirring.
Add broth and bring liquid to boil. Stir in couscous, cover skillet and remove from heat.
Let mixture stand for 4 minutes and transfer it to a ceramic or glass bowl, breaking up any lumps with a fork.
Add celery, currants, scallions, pine nuts and parsley. Toss to combine.

title: rolls
directions: Melt the shortening and set aside to cool.
Mix yeast with the lukewarm water in mixing bowl and stir until completely dissolved. Add salt, sugar, cooled, melted shortening and beaten egg; stir. Add flour and mix.
Cover with wrap paper and let rise even with top of bowl.
After rising, roll dough using enough flour to keep from being sticky.
Cut out rolls with cutter and put in greased bread pan; let rise again.
Bake at 350° until done.
Pat butter on top while still warm.

title: ryan's bread
directions: Heat butter and water until warm (120°).
Mix into all the other ingredients; blend well.
Add 1 cup whole wheat flour; mix well again.
Knead well.
Place in a greased bowl.
Let rise. After about 2 hours of rising, punch it down and knead again. Place in a greased bread pan.
Let rise again.
Cook for 40 minutes in a 375° oven.
Cool on a rack.

title: crumb crust lemon cake
directions: In food processor bowl, chop 1/4 cup pecans with chopping blade; set aside.
With same blade, use on-off motion to process brown sugar and yellow peel from 1/4 of lemon until peel is finely chopped.
Add flours, salt and allspice and process until blended. Cut butter into pieces and add to mixture.
Process until it forms coarse crumbs.
Butter a 9-inch pie plate.
Remove 1 cup flour mixture from processor and press into pie plate.
To remaining mixture, add egg, soda, yogurt and 1 teaspoon lemon juice; process until blended.
Spoon mixture into crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until done.

title: pizza pasta casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef and onion until meat is done. Stir in spaghetti sauce and pasta. Transfer to two 9 x 13-inch baking dishes. Sprinkle with cheese and lay pepperoni over the top. You can cover and freeze one of the casseroles for up to 3 months. Bake the second one, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until well heated. To use frozen casserole, thaw in the refrigerator overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Bake potatoes in a 400° oven for 1 hr. Let cool. Scoop out pulp. Set aside, Melt butter in a saucepan over low heat. Add flour, stirring until smooth. Cook 1 minute. Gradually add milk cook over medium heat. Stir constantly until mixture is thickened. Add potatoes, salt and pepper, two tablespoons of green onion, 1/2 of bacon and 1 cup of cheese. Cook until heated well. Stir in sour cream; add extra milk if necessary. Serve with remaining green onion, bacon and cheese.

title: tasty pancakes
directions: If sweet milk is used, omit the soda and increase the baking powder to 3 teaspoons.
Whole wheat flour may be substituted for part of the white flour.
Beat eggs until light.
Add milk.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar.
Beat flour mixture into egg mixture.
Add melted butter and beat until smooth.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, adding sugar, a little at a time.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla. Add flour, one cup at a time, sifting flour all around the bowl as you are mixing.
Batter should be sort of stiff, but not too stiff.
Add milk, a small amount at a time.

title: country apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Stir in apples.
Turn into pastry-lined deep dish pie plate (9 x 1 1/2-inches) or regular pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inches).
Drizzle with 3 tablespoons of whipping cream.
Cover with top crust that has slits cut in it; seal and flute.
Brush with remaining whipping cream.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until crust is brown and juice begins to bubble through slits in crust.

title: marie's mexican fried bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into 6 balls.
Roll out each ball to 1/8 inch thickness.
Cut into wedges.
Fry quickly in hot grease.
Drain on towel.
This bread goes very well with vegetable soup or soup beans.

title: baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat beans.
Stir in molasses, onion, salt and mustard.
Pour into baking pan.
Arrange bacon strips over beans.
Bake until bacon is crisp.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage and onion; drain.
Pour into crock-pot.
Mix in soup; add Velveeta cheese (in chunks).
Cook on low, stirring often until cheese is melted.
Serve with party rye.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg, then bran.
Mix thoroughly.
Combine water and banana; add alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla and nut meats.
Bake in waxed lined 5 x 9-inch loaf pan in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Any type of bran may be used successfully.

title: cheesy corn chowder
directions: Coat a large saucepan with cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add green onions, celery and sweet red pepper; saute until tender.
Combine flour and 1/2 cup milk; stir until smooth.
Add flour mixture, remaining 4 cups milk, corn, bouillon granules and ground pepper to vegetable mixture.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, and simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Add cheese; cook, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Yield:
6 cups (181 calories per 1 cup serving, 20% from fat).

title: cherry pizza
directions: Bake crust in pizza pan at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, eggs, vanilla and pecans.
Add cream cheese mixture to crust and bake 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Add cherry filling and spread evenly.
Decorate top with Cool Whip.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain off all fruit juices.
Mix all together and chill.
May add 1 cup of English walnuts and 1 cup of black walnuts, if desired.

title: candied yams
directions: Boil syrup, sugars and butter. Pour over potatoes and sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Separate biscuits and cut each biscuit into quarters.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in a plastic bag.
Put biscuits in bag and shake to coat each piece.
Grease bundt pan.
Layer biscuits in pan (one on top of the other).
Melt butter in pot and pour in leftover sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Keep stirring until sugar dissolves. Sugar and butter will start to carmelize.
Pour biscuits in pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and invert into dish.
Serve at once.

title: lemon bars(low cholesterol)
directions: In medium
bowl, combine 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup sugar. Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Place crumbs on bottom
of greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: theresa shea's baked turnips
directions: Pare turnips and cut into cubes.
Place in baking dish with remaining ingredients.
Cover closely and bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 1 hour or until tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: english raspberry squares
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening, 6 tablespoons sugar and 1 egg until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture and thoroughly combine.
Spread in a 10 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch shallow pan and cover with raspberry jam.
Thoroughly combine the coconut, 1 egg and 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread this topping over raspberry jam.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: shaker bean soup
directions: Cover beans with water and bring to a boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand 1 hour.
Drain beans.
Put beans and ham hocks in 3 quarts of water.
Bring to boil, then simmer, covered for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove bones.
Then add onion, ham, celery, salt, pepper and thyme.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Add tomatoes and brown sugar.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Just before serving, add spinach.
Yield: 5 quarts.

title: tropical chicken salad
directions: Place chicken and celery in a large bowl. Combine mayonnaise and curry powder; add to chicken mixture and mix well. Cover and chill for at least 30 minutes.

title: key lime pie (low-fat variation)
directions: Mix milk, limeade, couple drops of food coloring, and 1/2 of the container of Cool Whip with a spoon and pour into pie crusts. Top with the other 1/2 of the container of Cool Whip. Refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: dessert grillers
directions: Arrange fruit on a plate.
Spread margarine evenly on both sides of pound cake.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl; sprinkle over cake.
Place cake on rack of broiler pan.
Heat on both sides until lightly toasted.
Cool.
Serve with Cool Whip and fruit kabobs.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pecan chess pie
directions: Mix together dry ingredients and add to melted butter.
Mix with a fork.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Whip with a fork.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans over top. Bake about 45 minutes in a 325° oven.
Allow to cool.
Top with whipped cream.
This is my favorite pie!

title: eggplant supreme
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Cook in boiling water 8 minutes or until tender.
Drain well and set aside.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter in large skillet until vegetables are tender.
Stir in eggplant, cheese, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and hot sauce.
Spoon eggplant mixture into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mushrooms
directions: Drain mushrooms; saute onion in butter until tender.
Add mushrooms and saute a few minutes.
Add parsley, cheese and pepper. Add enough bread crumbs to coat the whole mixture.
Put in casserole.
Dot butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: springerle
directions: All the ingredients should be at room temperature.
Baking sheets should be greased and floured.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add half of milk. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add salt, flavoring and half of flour; beat well.
Add balance of milk and remaining flour; beat well.
Place in tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove seeds and wash peppers.
Parboil 3 minutes.
Combine rice, salt, pepper, ground beef, egg, milk and onion.
Stuff peppers lightly and place in cooker on rack or large pot.
Add tomato soup and water.
Cover and cook very slowly about an hour.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mash beans well.
Use juice.
Beat eggs well.
Add all ingredients together and mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add other ingredients; simmer 30 minutes.

title: killer brownies or double fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a small saucepan, combine butter, sugar and water.
Bring just to a boil. Remove from heat and add chips and vanilla.
Stir until chips are melted.
Transfer to a large bowl. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, soda cracker crumbs and melted butter or oleo.
Put 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: roast beef with yorkshire pudding
directions: Cook roast beef.
Place empty greased muffin tin in a 450° oven until it is good and hot.
Combine eggs, flour, milk and salt.
Mix well and pour into hot muffin tins.
(It is important that tins are hot first.)
You can add a couple of drops of roast beef juice into each: separate Yorkshire, if desired.
Bake 30 minutes at 450°.
Yorkshires will be golden and puffy.
Serve with gravy over them.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine butter and shortening.
Sift 3 cups sugar twice and cream in butter and shortening.
Add 5 eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each one.
Add 3 cups Softasilk cake flour, sifted twice.
Add 1 cup milk, 1 tablespoon vanilla and 1 tablespoon lemon flavoring and beat well.
Pour into mold.
Cook at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: bacon crisps
directions: Place bacon on crackers.
Sprinkle heaps of cheese on top of each.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake for 2 hours in a 200° oven.
Makes a delicious appetizer.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13 cake pan. Spread coconut and nuts in bottom. Mix one box of German chocolate cake mix according to directions. Spread across nuts and coconut. Cream together till soft: margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Mix well. Drop by spoonfuls across the cake mix. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Cut and serve upside down. The bottom is the frosting.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli and drain; place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Add chicken.
Mix sour cream, lemon juice and soup in a bowl; pour over top of the chicken.
Add cheese.
Top with bread crumbs that have been mixed with the melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: linguine salad
directions: Break linguine in half and cook.
Drain until dry.
Chop onions, tomatoes, cucumbers and peppers.
Mix in with linguine and Viva Italian dressing and 1/2 bottle Salad Supreme seasoning.
Mix through.
Let stand a few hours (to season) in the refrigerator.

title: iddie's forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold in the pecans and chocolate chips. Add the vanilla.

title: oreo dessert
directions: You will need 3 bowls.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until light, after adding each egg.
Add buttermilk.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add to mixture, a little at a time. Last, fold in berries.
Bake in layer pans about 35 minutes at 350°.

title: witches stew
directions: Melt butter and salts in pan.
Add sauce. Mix.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix well. Cover and bake for 2 1/2 hours at 250°. Stir often.

title: tender baked turkey breast(it's baked while still frozen.)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Unwrap turkey breast and rewrap in 18 to 24 inches of heavy-duty foil.
Place turkey breast in baking pan and bake for 3 hours.
Remove from oven; carefully open top of foil and neatly fold it back out of the way.
Place margarine on top of breast; season with salt and pepper.
Return open turkey to oven for an additional 30 minutes to brown.
Cool slightly before carving.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°
Grease
9 x 13 in. pan. Prepare cake as directed on package. Pour into greased pan and bake for 20 minutes.

title: chewy peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Mix other ingredients together.
In a large bowl, combine both mixtures.
Chill dough. Roll into balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten balls in crisscross pattern with wet fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: "apple pie in a jar"
directions: Fill 7 quart jars tightly.
Cover with syrup.
Place lids and rings on jars and process 20 minutes in water bath.

title: healthful date bread(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Pour boiling water over combined dates and raisins.
Cool slightly.

In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Stir egg whites and vanilla into cooled date mixture. Add with almonds to flour; stir until well blended (mixture will be thick).
Spread evenly in pan. Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan. Cool thoroughly on wire rack.
Wrap and store overnight before serving.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, vanilla and milk.
Mix well. Drop from teaspoon onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove at once from cookie sheet.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Spread pie filling on bottom; scatter pineapple over this.
Sprinkle cake mix, drop sliced oleo, scatter walnuts and sprinkle coconut.
Do not mix. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done and lightly brown. Serve plain or with ice cream.

title: takuwan
directions: Peel and slice daikon and place in gallon jar.
Add all ingredients, close jar and shake bottle.
Place in refrigerator. The next day, you can add more daikon in jar and shake jar again to marinate daikon.
Add yellow food coloring and keep in refrigerator.
Ready to eat in 1 week.

title: walking taco
directions: Combine refried beans and enchilada mix.
On a large platter, make a bed of the refried beans.
Layer sour cream, then green onions, guacamole, black olives, Cheddar cheese and tomatoes and top with more green onions.
Prior to serving, place tortilla chips around the edge of platter.
Have extra chips on hand, as this recipe goes a long way.
If desired, add chopped Ortega green chilies (these are not hot) before layering black olives.

title: sweet pineapple chicken(1977 cookbook)
directions: Mix together onion soup mix, pineapple and brown sugar. Place chicken in a single
layer
in
large
pan
with
2-inch sides. Spoon marinade over and
bake
uncovered at 325° for 2 hours.

title: shenandoah valley apple cake
directions: Beat together oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla (about 3 minutes). Sift together 2 cups flour, salt and baking soda.
Add dry ingredients, beating well after each addition.
Stir in apples. Combine walnuts and 1 tablespoon flour; stir into batter.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan on rack.
Spread with caramel topping.
Makes 16 servings.

title: oatmeal crisp
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Cream margarine and sugars; add eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla and water; add oatmeal, flour mix, nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.
Keep in tight fitting cookie can.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1/3 cup sugar.
Stir in melted butter.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Beat 2 eggs, 3/4 cup sugar and the cream cheese until light and fluffy. Pour over the graham cracker crust.
Bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: lemony light cooler(makes about 7 cups)
directions: In pitcher, combine grape juice, sugar and ReaLemon brand; stir until sugar dissolves.
Just before serving, add club soda, fruit and ice.

title: mexican dip ole
directions: Brown sausage in a skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain and set aside.

title: german style spinach
directions: Place bacon in a 1-quart casserole.
Cover with paper towels and microwave on High until crisp, about 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove bacon and drain.
Reserve drippings in casserole.
Crumble bacon and set aside.

title: honey chicken
directions: In a small bowl, combine vegetable oil, honey, cider vinegar and chili sauce.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place chicken pieces in a shallow baking pan.
Pour sauce over chicken and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crock-pot pork chops
directions: In a skillet, brown the pork chops on both sides in the butter.
Transfer the pork chops to the crock-pot. Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook on low temperature for 5 to 6 hours, cooking a little longer for thicker chops.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple with juice into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread evenly; do the same with cherry pie filling.
Dump dry cake mix in, spreading evenly.
Cut stick of oleo in slices all over cake mix.
Bake 350° until oleo is melted and top browned, 30 minutes.

title: frozen slush
directions: Boil water and sugar until dissolved.
Steam tea bags in additional 2 cups water.
Cool.
Mix with sugar water.
Add brandy and orange juice.
Mix and freeze.
Mix occasionally until slushed up.
Serve mixed with 7-Up.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Top with Cool Whip.
(May top with chopped pecans.) Freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: holiday cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add brown and white sugars; cream.
Add eggs.
Add salt and soda to sifted flour and blend.
Divide dough. To one half, add 1 cup candied cherries and 1 cup coconut.
To other half, add 2 cups chopped dates and 2 cups chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 11 to 12 minutes.

title: no-cook peach cream pie
directions: Peel, pit and cut peaches into bite-sized pieces; place half of peaches in chocolate crumb crust.
In small bowl, beat at medium speed the cream until stiff peaks form.
In large bowl prepare instant pudding as label directs, except use only 1 cup milk. Gently fold whipped cream and lemon extract into pudding mixture. Spoon over peaches; top with remaining peaches.
Refrigerate and let pie set for 10 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: california cole slaw
directions: Mix chopped cabbage, sesame seed, Chinese noodles (crunched up), onions and almonds.
Mix liquids, sugar and flavoring.
Toss with cabbage.
Refrigerate.
Best made same day.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix as directed and set aside. Mix
rest of ingredients.
Fill cup 1/3 full with cake mix.
Drop 1 teaspoon (or more) of cheese mix.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: meal in a dish
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onions, peppers and celery; cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Add noodles that have been cooked in salty water, tomato sauce, chili powder, corn and pepper.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Bake 10 more minutes.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Add all ingredients to a large plastic bag.
Close bag and shake until evenly coated.
Empty potatoes into a shallow baking pan coated with Pam spray.
Bake for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: marvelous meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and place in a loaf pan.
Cover with reserved tomato sauce and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
This will slice easier if allowed to cool.

title: liptauer cheese(kotozot)
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except green pepper, together in a blender or food processor.
Spread on thinly sliced French or Italian bread rounds.
Decorate top of each round with a small diamond or square of fresh green pepper.
Serves 10.

title: creme doodles
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and honey, mixing with electric mixer or wire whisk until well blended.
Add chocolate, raisins and nuts; mix well.
Shape rounded teaspoon of mixture into 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Chill.

title: company crab casserole
directions: Cook and stir onion and garlic in oil in 3-quart saucepan until onion is tender.
Stir in next 7 ingredients.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Make Lemon Oven Rice. Stir crabmeat and cheese into tomato mixture.
Spoon over baked rice.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes more.
Garnish with parsley.
Yields 6 servings.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Stir flour, baking powder, cream of tartar, salt and sugar. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles crumbs.
Add milk all at once.
Stir until dough clings together.
Knead on a lightly floured surface for 10 to 12 strokes.
Pat to 1/2 inch thickness. Cut with a biscuit cutter.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes on an ungreased baking sheet.

title: strawberry yogurt drink
directions: Put strawberries, yogurt, pineapple juice and honey in blender and blend together.
Add optional wheat germ and blend again. Serve at once.

title: cathedral windows
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs. Cool slightly.
Add powdered sugar and marshmallows and nuts. Roll in coconut or nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese ball
directions: Make sure cream cheese is soft before starting.
Fork ingredients together well.
Roll into a ball.
Add pecans if desired.
Chill and serve.

title: eclair
directions: Combine pudding mix and 3 cups milk in bowl; mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Layer graham crackers and pudding 1/2 at a time in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine 3 tablespoons milk, butter and chocolate in saucepan.
Heat until butter and chocolate are melted, stirring to mix well.
Add confectioners sugar; mix well. Spoon evenly over top.
Chill until serving time.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: gingered chicken
directions: Mix chicken with spices and marinate for at least 15 minutes. Heat pan and add 2 tablespoons cooking oil.
Add chicken with spices over low heat until golden.
Add sugar to caramelize.
Add 1/2 cup water and cook, covered, 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: five pound fudge
directions: Use large heavy pot (I use a Magnalite Dutch oven) and cook on medium heat.
Cook first 3 ingredients to a soft ball stage (approximately 10 minutes).
Stir constantly as it starts to thicken.
Quickly add last 3 ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop with 2 spoons onto waxed paper.

title: uncle greg cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes approximately 70 cookies.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put in crock-pot sprayed with Pam. Cut several slices of cheese on top. Sprinkle with paprika. Cook 3 to 4 hours on low.

title: fun cocoa
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Put 2 teaspoons cocoa mix in mug.
Mix with water and small amount milk.
Put chocolate whipped cream on top and colored jimmies (great fun with children after cold day of sledding).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in greased casserole dish. Crumble Ritz crackers on top and place remaining 1/2 stick butter on crackers in pats.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chris' tomatoes au gratin
directions: Simmer tomatoes, onion and seasonings for 15 minutes.
Pour into baking dish and top with cheeses.
Broil in the oven until cheese is melted and turns golden brown.

title: payday bar
directions: Spray 2 cookie sheets with Pam.
Mix cereal and peanuts. Spread across the cookie sheets.
Put corn syrup and sugar in microwave for 30 seconds.
Stir until mixed well.
Heat in microwave for 4 minutes longer.
Mix peanut butter and vanilla into syrup and sugar mixture.
Pour over cereal and nut mixture. Cool.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix melted oleo, chicken broth, cream of celery soup and Veg-All in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay chicken on top, then mix flour and milk together.
Pour on top of chicken breast.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese thoroughly.
Then add sugar. Beat until real creamy.
Add eggs and flour alternately, beating after each addition.
Start with and end with flour.
Add flavoring.
After mixing, pour into a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Place in cold oven.
Turn temperature to 300° and bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: oven-easy beef and potato dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In an 8 x 12-inch baking dish, combine potatoes, oil and pepper.
Firmly press potato mixture evenly across bottom and sides of dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: banana pound cake
directions: Mix cake mix, vanilla pudding mix, eggs, banana and oil by hand.
Then 5 minutes with an electric mixer.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: vegetable cocktail
directions: Drain cooked tomatoes; save liquid.
Chop tomatoes finely and mix with celery, green pepper and onion.
Add tomato juice, horseradish, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Chill several hours.
Serve cold in sherbet glasses.
Eat with spoon.
Serves 6.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar
and
shortening.
Add
eggs and beat.
Add next 6 ingredients
and
mix
well.
Pour
into
greased
and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread marshmallows over the top.
Increase oven temperature to 350°
and
return cake to oven for 10 minutes. Cool 1 hour.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: simply delicious coconut pineapple pie
directions: Bake pastry shell according to directions on package. Let cool. Beat milk and pudding mix until thickened. Stir in coconut and pineapple. Pour into cooled pie shell.
Chill for 2 hours. Garnish with whipped topping.

title: eclairs
directions: In pan, melt margarine and add water.
Add flour so it forms a ball.
Let cool.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix with beater.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes (light brown).
Let cool.
(Spread mixture on cookie sheet to bake, greased.)

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Combine chocolate and water; bring to a boil.
Stir until chocolate melts.
Cool; stir in vanilla and set aside.
Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add chocolate mixture; beat until blended.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into batter.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and let cool completely on wire racks. Frost with Coconut-Pecan Frosting.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add garlic powder and chili powder.
Add 1 large can Hunt's tomato sauce and 1 large can Bush's red hot chili beans.
Simmer.

title: blueberry-apple jam with cinnamon
directions: Peel apple and grate into a large saucepan.
Grate yellow zest from the lemon into pan and squeeze in juice.
Add blueberries and sugar.
Lightly crush berries.
Bring to a simmer over medium-high heat, stirring constantly.
Skim any foam that rises to the surface while cooking.
Reduce heat and simmer until jam reaches the sheeting stage (220°), about 35 minutes.
To test, dip a spoon into the jam and hold over the pan; two drops that start at opposite sides of the spoon should meet before they fall off. Remove from heat and stir in cinnamon.
Cool to room temperature and pour into jars.
Chill.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: peach torte
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add crushed crackers, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into well-buttered 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
After cool, pour 1 can peach pie filling over top.
Top with whipped cream.

title: cholesterol free fruit loaf
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Add enough water to Coffee Rich to equal 1 cup.
Add to flour mixture with bananas, egg whites and oil.
Mix to blend.
Fold in cereal, raisins and dates.
Bake in 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix fruit cocktail, sugar, eggs, flour, soda and vanilla in bowl together. Pour in well greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan. Sprinkle brown sugar, coconut and nuts on top. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: baked pork chops with dressing
directions: Brown pork chops and place in shallow pan.

title: cajun cheese dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on bottom of 9 x 11-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with chopped scallions.
Spread chili on top. Sprinkle the Monterey Jack and jalapeno cheeses on top.
Sprinkle with Cajun spice.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: beef buffet casserole
directions: Brown beef in a skillet.
Add onion and cook 10 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and seasoning, simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles according to package directions. Drain and rinse.
Blend cheese and sour cream.
Add olives and mix with noodles.
Spread about 1/2 the mixture in a greased 3 quart baking dish.
Top with 1/2 the meat sauce then add remaining noodles and meat sauce mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves:

title: oatmeal squares
directions: Cream margarine or butter and sugar.
Add eggs, oats, flour, cinnamon, vanilla and nuts (if you use nuts); mix together.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 25 to 40 minutes, until light brown.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut into squares; roll in confectioners sugar.

title: pumpkin cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Stir in all dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in an ungreased pan, 15 x 10-inch or 14 x 11-inch.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: upside down ham loaf
directions: Mix brown sugar, dry mustard and vinegar.
Pour into bottom of large greased loaf pan or 2-quart Pyrex dish.
Place pineapple rings on top.
Mix first 7 ingredients well and pack meat mixture on top of pineapple rings.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 375°.
Invert on platter.

title: layered pie
