directions: Have ready a baked 9-inch pastry shell or a rich crumb crust. Soak gelatin in cold water.
Scald milk.
Mix sugar and cornstarch together, then add egg yolks and beat well.
Stir this mixture into scalded milk; cook over low heat or hot water until the custard coats the spoon.
Stir constantly.
Take out 1 cup custard and add it to the melted chocolate.
Beat with rotary beater until cool, then add the teaspoon of vanilla.
Pour into the pie shell and chill.

title: combination rolls
directions: Let milk come to boil, then cool before adding yeast.
Mix as you would for bread.
After the dough has risen three times, shape into rolls.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Brush well with melted fat; cover and let rise again.
Then bake in a moderate oven (400° to 450°) for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: party ham sandwiches
directions: Melt margarine in skillet over medium heat.
Add chopped onion, mustard and poppy seed.
Stir until well mixed.
Remove from heat; add ham and set aside.
Put ham mixture into buns and add cheese.
Heat 15 minutes or until browned.

title: shepherd's beef pie
directions: Saute very lightly mushrooms and add them with their juice to ground beef in a bowl.
Mix gently with bread crumbs, egg, catsup, soy sauce and mustard.
Then transfer to a baking pan or casserole.
Add a topping of mashed potatoes, well buttered, about 1/2-inch thick.
Bake 1 hour in a preheated 350° oven.
Potato topping should be crisp and golden.
If necessary, raise temperature for the last 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: banana pineapple cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients; stir in rest.
Mix with spoon, no mixer.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in bread pans.
Cool and frost.

title: simmering potpourri
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in a glass jar or pretty tin, tightly covered.

title: pineapple carrot bread
directions: In a bowl, combine the dry ingredients.
In a mixing bowl, beat the eggs, sugar and oil.
Add carrot, pineapple and vanilla. Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fold in nuts. Pour into two greased loaf pans.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Will need Reynolds oven cooking bag.

title: little pizzas
directions: Brown sausage; drain, then add cheese.
Heat until cheese blends in with sausage.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir until blended and remove from heat.

title: oyster stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and Tabasco with a little of oyster liquid.
Stir into oysters and rest of liquid.
Simmer over low heat until edges curl.
Pour scalded milk into oysters.
Heat to almost boiling.
Remove from stove and add butter, pepper and paprika.
Let stand for 15 minutes to mallow the flavor.
Do not boil at any time!

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Crush
crackers and mix with butter and powdered sugar. Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water, add pineapple.
Cool until syrupy.
Cream
together cream cheese and sugar.
Whip chilled Pet milk,
add
cheese mix to whipped Pet milk and beat.
Pour into lined
pan
of
graham crackers and add 1/2 cup of graham crackers on
top.
Chill
at
least
1/2 hour before serving.

title: german potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes.
Boil potatoes until slightly firm; do not overcook.
Drain water off potatoes and dice potatoes while still hot.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix together.
Serve while hot.
You may serve cold, if you prefer.

title: stew chicken and dumplings
directions: In a 5-quart saucepan, heat oil. Brown chicken. Drain off fat. Add water, celery rib, lemon, salt, thyme, pepper, bay leaf and onion. Bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, 45 minutes or until chicken is tender. Remove chicken.
Discard chicken skin, lemon, celery rib and bay leaf. Bring broth to a boil. Add uncooked dumplings, carrots and celery.
Boil, uncovered, 10 minutes. Remove chicken from bones. Cut into pieces. Add to dumpling mixture.
Makes about 6 to 8 servings.

title: deep fried fish
directions: Add sugar and yeast to warm water.
Stir and let stand 10 minutes, until frothy.
Add salt, flour and oil.
Stir and let sit 1/2 to 1 hour before using.
Make sure fish is dry.
Shake in flour.
Stir batter before using.
Dip fish in batter.
Deep fry at 360° for 5 to 6 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Will stay crisp in warm oven.

title: baked water chestnuts
directions: Wrap each chestnut in 1/2 strip raw bacon.
Secure with toothpick.
Place on broiler tray.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bacon is crisp.
(Bake; do not broil.) While chestnuts are baking, mix sugar and ketchup in a small bowl.
Remove wrapped chestnuts from pan.
(Do not remove toothpicks.)
Place in baking dish.
Pour ketchup mixture over chestnuts.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: shrimp and artichokes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In bottom of buttered casserole, arrange artichoke hearts.
Spread shrimp over artichokes.
Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons of butter for 6 minutes.
Layer over shrimp.
Melt remaining 4 tablespoons butter in a saucepan.
Whisk in flour, stirring until well blended and smooth.
Pour in milk, whisking constantly until mixture has thickened.
Season with salt and pepper, then add Worcestershire sauce and sherry.
Pour over casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot, garnished with an extra sprinkling of paprika and chopped fresh parsley.
Chicken may be substituted for shrimp.

title: italian sausage spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown sausage in olive oil (about half cook it).
Remove from pan and put aside.
Add flour to oil that was used and make roux (see my recipe).
Add onions, celery and bell pepper.
Stir and cook until tender or clear.
Add water and stir until smooth. Add wine, parsley and garlic.
Pour in red pepper, Lea & Perrins, dried mint and tomato sauce; stir really well.
Bring to a bubbly boil and add salt to taste.
Add sausage.
Bring back to a boil. Turn heat down to simmer.
Cook for about 3 or 4 hours.
Serve over spaghetti topped with cheese.
Should serve 8.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in bananas and eggs.
Stir in flour and soda.
Add cherries and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit cake(england)
directions: Line 8 bread pans with wax paper.
Cream shortening and sugar. Add spices, molasses and beaten eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Add currants and raisins.
Cut up candied fruit and add; chop walnuts and add.
Add salt and baking soda.
Alternately add coffee and flour, using only enough coffee to make mixture moist.
Bake in a 250° oven for 2 hours or until toothpick comes out dry.
Yields 8 loaves.

title: banana bread (1)
directions: Mix bananas and water; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients except pecans; add bananas; add pecans last.
Put in two large or three small greased and floured bread pans.
Bake 45 min. at 350°F.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Wear rubber gloves to seed and coarsely chop the peppers. Place the bell peppers into blender or food processor and chop until fine.
You should have about 3/4 cup.
Process the hot peppers until finely chopped.
You should have 1/4 cup.
In a large pot, combine the peppers with the sugar and vinegar.
Over high heat, bring to a boil and add the Certo.
Add food coloring if you are using it.
Pour into 7 (1/2-pint) jars and seal or refrigerate.

title: paradise salad
directions: Cream cheese and whip with 1 heaping tablespoon mayonnaise. Whip 2/3 cup whipping cream. When jello is cool, add other ingredients. Pour in dish or mold and place in refrigerate.

title: banana-grape slush
directions: Fill blender 1/2 full with ice.
Mix all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Enjoy!

title: southern corn fritters
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add to melted butter and corn.
Beat well and drop by teaspoonfuls in hot, deep fat.
When brown, remove and serve with butter, syrup or honey.

title: holiday inn strawberry pie
directions: Cook 7-Up, cornstarch and food coloring until thick.
When cool, put in strawberries and pour into crust.
Top with whipped cream.

title: astronaut drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender. Blend until smooth.

title: company broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare frozen broccoli according to package directions and place in a 3-quart casserole.
In a separate bowl, combine mayonnaise, eggs, soup and most of the cheese.
Add mixture to the broccoli and mix together.
Pour crushed crackers and remaining cheese over top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: don't peek stew
directions: Mix together in big roaster.
Put 2 slices of bread on top; cover.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Line a 9-inch pan with pastry.
Cover with cheese.
Fry bacon until crisp, crumble and arrange on top of cheese.
Beat eggs with flour, salt, cayenne and nutmeg.
Add milk and melted butter. Pour custard over bacon and cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 40 minutes, until set.
Cut into wedges.
Serve warm as an hors d'oeuvre.

title: nutmeg cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, nutmeg and salt.
Add to creamed mixture with buttermilk.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13 baking dish at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: ham and cheese balls
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Shape into balls and chill.
Better to let set overnight before serving.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Saute onion, celery, meat and Worcestershire sauce.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Drain excess fat.
Remove tops and seeds from peppers and cook in boiling water for about 5 minutes. Drain.
Add rice and 1/2 the tomato sauce to the meat mixture and stir thoroughly.
Spoon meat mixture into peppers and stand peppers in baking dish.
Add about 1/2-inch water to the baking dish.
Spoon remaining tomato sauce over stuffed peppers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes uncovered.
Garnish with grated cheese and bake for 5 more minutes.
Serves 4.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mash bananas.
Add sugar and melted butter.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° in greased muffin tin. Makes 12 muffins.

title: cowboy cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, eggs, milk, soda, salt, corn and butter; set aside.
Cook meat, onion and pepper.
Pour 1/2 of cornmeal batter into greased casserole dish.
Add meat mixture; sprinkle with cheese.
Pour remaining batter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot herb bread
directions: You will need foil for this recipe.

title: szabo's depression dinner
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on the bag; drain and set aside.
Cook bacon in a frying pan or in the microwave until crispy.
Crumble the bacon.
Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender and drain.
Mash potatoes and add the 1/4 cup milk. Put mashed potatoes, bacon and noodles into a large frying pan with a little bacon drippings and fry until brown on all sides (like hash brown potatoes).
Serve hot.
Very good.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: oven rice
directions: Bring water to boil; add butter and crumble beef bouillon cubes.
Let it melt; mix in onion soup and rice.
Pour into casserole dish and bake in oven for about 35 to 40 minutes.
This is delicious and easy.

title: pajama party pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Split bagels.
Place on cookie sheet. Spread about 2 tablespoons of sauce on each bagel.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and oregano to taste.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and some more oregano. Bake about 10 minutes until cheese is melted and begins to brown. Let cool a bit before eating!
Enough for four silly kids at midnight!

title: pig in the blankets
directions: Cut hot dogs in half.
Roll each half into a biscuit.
Bake in oven at 350° until biscuits are done.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix the yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased baking pan.
Let rise for 2 hours. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: jiffy cobbler
directions: Drain fruit (save juice).
Melt butter in a baking dish; add flour, sugar, milk and fruit and mix thoroughly.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour juice over cobbler.
Return to oven and bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes.
Suitable to freeze.

title: cracker pie
directions: Break soda crackers in an unbaked pie crust.
Then put in a pan:
sugar, water, cream of tartar, oleo and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over crackers.
Add top crust. (Save 2 tablespoons of liquid and spread over top crust.)
Tastes like apple pie.
Bake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients,
except
crackers, and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Top with crushed crackers and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crust:
Mix 1 stick of margarine and graham crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: breaded fried pork chops
directions: Beat eggs and water.
Heat oil in skillet.
Shake pork chops in a bag with flour, coating chops completely. Shake off excess flour. Dip floured chops in beaten eggs.
Drain off excess egg. Coat chops with seasoned bread crumbs. Fry in hot oil until edges are browned.
Turn and fry the other side until brown.
No need for applesauce!
Bread can be dipped in leftover eggs and bread crumbs and fried to accompany pork chops.

title: scallop newburg
directions: Rinse scallops; drain. In small-medium saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Stir in flour, salt and paprika. Cook 1 minute, stirring. Gradually add milk; cook 4 to 5 minutes until thickened (stirring constantly). Add sherry and scallops; reduce heat to low. Cook 3 minutes until scallops are opaque and firm.

title: chicken potato salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt, mustard, pepper, chopped eggs, potatoes, celery, green pepper, onion and cooked chicken.
Mix well and chill.
Serve on lettuce; garnish with egg slices and paprika.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: company chicken and mushrooms
directions: Remove skin from chicken, rinse and pat dry.
In a small bowl mix salt, pepper and paprika.
Rub into surface of chicken using all the mixture.
In a crockpot, alternate layers of chicken, bouillon granules, mushrooms and green onions.
Pour wine slowly over top.
Do not stir.
Cover and cook on high for 2 1/2 -3 hours or on low 5-6 hours or until chicken is tender, but not falling off the bone, basting only once.
With a slotted spoon, remove chicken and vegetables to a serving platter.
Cover with foil and keep warm.	In a small saucepan, stir evaporated milk and cornstarch until smooth.
Gradually stir in 2 c. of cooking liquid from the crockpot.	Stirring over medium heat, bring to a boil and boil for 1 to 2 minutes until thickened.
Spoon some of the sauce over chicken and garnish with parsley.
Serve remaining sauce separately.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt 5 candy bars and one stick of butter.
Cream one stick of butter with sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour then add nuts if desired.
Add buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Fold in Milky Way mixture.
Spray 2 round cake pans (or 1 - 9 x 13) with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° until done.
Let cool.

title: stuffed squash(yellow or zucchini)
directions: Carefully scoop out pulp and seeds from squash.
Mix other ingredients together with 1/3 of tomato paste and 1/2 cup water. Fill squash with mixture.
Mix remaining tomato paste with water and pour over squash.
Cook, covered, on low heat 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken etti
directions: Mix together.
Save 1 cup cheese for top of casserole.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until pretty and golden brown on top. Do not overcook.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except ketchup.
Shape in baking pan.
Put ketchup over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: cheesy vegetable enchiladas
directions: In large pot, over medium heat, in hot oil, cook peppers, carrot and half the green onions with garlic, chili powder and salt until tender, stirring often.
Stir in beans, corn, olives and tomato.
Heat through.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Place pumpkin in the milk or chicken broth.
Knead together and add butter and flour.
Add sugar, salt, pepper, ginger and cinnamon.
Also add the light cream if you used the chicken broth. Heat, but do not boil!
Serve at once.

title: rice pudding
directions: Heat the oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients in a 1-quart casserole.
Bake about 2 hours.
When pudding has baked 30 minutes, stir in the brown upper crust.
Stir in the crust twice more during baking.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl (by hand). Place heaping teaspoonfuls of dough onto a greased cookie sheet. Place in a 350° oven for 9 to 11 minutes or until golden brown.

title: banana salad
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour.
Add to water, vinegar, butter, mustard and egg yolks.
Cook until thick.
Cool and add cream.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: Marinate 6 to 8 hours overnight in refrigerator.
Turn a couple times while marinating.
(The longer marinated, the stronger the flavor.)
Grill or broil.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Cook gizzards, liver and neck.
Pick off bone.
Mix all ingredients.
Add turkey broth to keep from being dry.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs that have been beaten until lemon color.
Sift flour and baking powder; add to mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in extracts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool for 20 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill overnight before serving.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat sugar with Cool Whip and strawberries.
Frost all 4 layers.
Refrigerate.

title: onion soup
directions: In saucepan, combine soup and water; heat.
In individual serving bowls, place a slice of French bread; top with cheese. Pour in soup.

title: friendship dessert
directions: Combine.
Bake in 8 x 12-inch pan for 15 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans; mix with soup, water chestnuts and 1/2 can onions in flat baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining onions over beans and bake about 15 more minutes.

title: louise wilson's apricot salad
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients until sugar and jello dissolve. Remove from heat and stir in cream cheese.
Add baby food and pineapple, undrained.
Set aside to cool.
Add whipped topping and pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish to set.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, or until done.

title: quick beef soup
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in Dutch oven until beef is brown, drain.
Stir in sauce mix, water, bay leaf, salt, pepper, tomatoes and mixed vegetables.
Break up any whole tomatoes with fork.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes or longer.
Makes about 9 cups of soup.

title: chocolate fettuccine
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Heat frypan that has very thin coat of oil, preferably a paper towel that has oil on it.
Make crepes as thin as possible.
Cook both sides.
Let cool individually.
Cut crepes into 1/4-inch wide strips. Toss fettuccine with sweetened whipped cream and top with chocolate sauce.

title: tid bits
directions: Mix oil, Ranch dressing and dill weed.
When dressing is thoroughly mixed, pour over oyster crackers, coating all of them.

title: brown beef and gravy
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Add mushrooms, pepper and celery.
Cook until tender.
Add enough water to cover beef mixture.
Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: chicken in almond sauce
directions: Cut the chicken in 4 or 6 parts.
In the pot, mix chicken, water, vinegar, garlic and salt.
Cook for 45 minutes or until chicken is soft.
In a separate pan, fry the almonds in oil. Remove from the oil, chop with a clove of garlic.
Pour over the meat.
Cover the pot for 10 minutes, the juices must thicken. Serve over white rice or with French fries.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet and saute broccoli and small onion. Combine with other ingredients in separate baking dish.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: garlic potato wedges
directions: Boil scrubbed potatoes with jackets on until almost done. Remove from water and let cool slightly.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise, then cut each half into 3 or 4 wedges.
Arrange wedges in a single layer in baking dish.
Pour over melted butter. Sprinkle with garlic salt and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 60 minutes, turning occasionally.
They're best when crispy. Preparation time: 25 minutes; cooking time: 1 hour.
Easy.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hershey's chocolate cake
directions: *Or 1 cup self- rising flour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces and roll each piece.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in large Baggie.
Shake biscuit pieces in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Drop pieces into greased Bundt pan. Sprinkle remaining sugar and cinnamon over the top of the pieces in the Bundt pan.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes in colander and drain excess water.
Melt margarine in 2 quart casserole (9 x 13-inch pan).
Add soup, sour cream, salt, onions, cheese and sausage.
Mix well.
Add potatoes. Sprinkle with buttered corn flakes and bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until golden and bubbly.

title: quick and easy spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together; drain.
Mix ground beef with other ingredients and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes. Serve over spaghetti.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix onion mix and sour cream.
Roll chicken in mixture, then roll in stuffing.
Place in baking dish.
Dribble margarine over chicken.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: cranberry fruit punch
directions: Blend juices and concentrates and refrigerate.
Add club soda at serving time.
An ice ring with citrus fruits adds a nice touch.
Yields fifty 8-ounce servings.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix the Crisco into the flour until crumbly.
Add milk.
Knead for about 1 minute on floured wax paper until the dough is no longer sticky.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet for 8 to 10 minutes at 450°.

title: apricot gelatin salad
directions: Heat crushed pineapple in heavy saucepan.
Add gelatin; simmer until gelatin dissolves.
Cool until soft pudding stage.
Mix together the cream cheese, dry Dream Whip, sugar and baby food. Whip until light and creamy.
Combine cream cheese mixture with cooled, slightly thickened gelatin in mixture.
Pour into molds or 9 x 13-inch salad pan.
Chill overnight before serving.
Serves 15.

title: good-for-you muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine oats, flours, brown sugar, oat bran, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Add currants or raisins, banana chips, dates and nuts.
Stir to coat with flour mixture.
*Stir just until moistened (batter should be lumpy).
Lightly grease 12 muffin cups or line with paper bake cups.
Spoon batter into cups, filling cups full.
Bake in 400° oven for 18 to 20 minutes or until done.
Cool slightly on wire rack.
Serve warm or cool.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: white mountain cake icing
directions: Boil sugar, Karo and water rapidly until 6 to 8 inch thread forms.
Beat 2 egg whites until stiff.
Pour hot syrup into beaten egg whites, beating constantly until icing stands in stiff peaks. Add vanilla.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Mix all ingredients together (cheese may be melted in microwave before adding).
Grease casserole dish with butter; add mixture.
Microwave on High (covered) for 20 minutes. Let cool 15 to 20 minutes.

title: oven porcupines
directions: Combine beef, rice, 1/2 cup of water, onion, garlic powder, celery salt, salt and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Shape into balls. Place in baking dish.
Combine tomato sauce, 1 cup water and Worcestershire in bowl; mix well.
Spoon over meat balls.
Bake, covered with foil, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover; bake 15 more minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Rinse spaghetti with cold water after cooking.
Add dry seasoning then Italian dressing.
Add tomatoes, green peppers, onions and cucumber if desired.

title: chocolate chip cookie mix
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, salt and both sugars in a very large bowl.
Mix in shortening with fingers.
Stir in pecans and chocolate chips.
Store in airtight container in cool, dry place. May be kept for 6 months.
For longer storage, refrigerate or freeze.
Yields 28 cups.

title: creamy dill meatballs
directions: Step 1:
Place frozen meatballs in 1 1/2-quart microwave- safe casserole.
Cover with casserole lid.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions together until tender.
Drain off water and mash until fine.
Add salt, pepper, cheese, margarine, egg yolks and crackers (crumbled fine).
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake in buttered casserole dish until brown.
Serve hot.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Mix and cook everything except popcorn.
Cook on medium heat until mixture bubbles on edge.
Cook for 5 minutes longer.
Take off heat.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Mixture will foam. Put popcorn in roasting pan.
Pour mixture over popcorn.
Mix well.
Bake in oven at 200° for 1 hour; mix every 15 minutes.

title: calamondin supreme cake
directions: *Calamondins are small sour oranges that grow in many Florida yards -- they can be substituted with kumquats, sour oranges or other orange varieties, if unavailable.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Fritos.
Add Fritos just before serving.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cook cake as on box in long pan. Mix sugar, butter, vanilla, milk and black walnuts. Cook (boil) for 1 minute; pour over cake.

title: jerome bars
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Over low heat, melt margarine.
Add sugar; beat egg with 1/2 cup Pet milk. Add to margarine and sugar mixture; bring to a boil stirring constantly (scorches easily).
Remove from heat; add coconut, pecans and graham cracker crumbs.
Spread on crackers.
Add another layer graham crackers, making sure they're all going the same way as the others.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend dry ingredients; add cream.
Mix thoroughly. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 25 minutes or until center is firm.

title: sweet and sour slaw
directions: Prepare cabbage, onion and pepper for slaw.

title: marshmallow delight
directions: Mix pudding and cool whip until dissolved.
Add marshmallows. Add pineapple chunks to cool whip mixture.
Add pecans and chill at least 2 hours.

title: ham and onion dip
directions: Dice ham and onion, stir into softened cream cheese.
You will have to add a small amount of milk to mixture for the dip to be smooth.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Cook enough spaghetti for 4.
In a large casserole dish, mix all ingredients, cutting cheese into chunks.
Put in oven until cheese melts.
Stir before serving. Good served with green beans and sweet fried corn bread.

title: german potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Can add green pepper and parsley.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can refrigerate for up to 24 hours before baking.

title: spicy marinated shrimp
directions: Thaw frozen shrimp.
In bowl, combine vinegar, lemon juice, salt, mustard and pepper; set aside.
In medium skillet, cook shrimp, half of the onion slices and the garlic in hot oil over medium-high heat 4 to 5 minutes or just until shrimp are done, stirring occasionally.
Remove onion and garlic with slotted spoon; discard.
Add shrimp and remaining oil to vinegar mixture in bowl along with remaining onion and jalapeno.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.

title: texas corn bread
directions: Blend together and bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 425° for 20 minutes or until done.
Melt a stick of butter or margarine; pour over the bread when it is done.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine condensed milk and water.
Add pudding mix, and beat well.
Chill this mixture for 5 minutes. Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon 1 cup of the above mixture into a 2 1/2 quart serving bowl.
Top with 1/3 of the vanilla wafers, 1/3 of the bananas and 1/3 of the pudding.
Repeat this layering two times, ending with the pudding.
Chill thoroughly and serve. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: homemade bubbles
directions: Gently mix all ingredients together.
Store until ready to use.

title: hinamatsuri(sushi variety)
directions: Put seasoned vinegar into cooked rice.
Mix.
Slice chicken and vegetables finely.
Cook together in pot with soy sauce and sugar, then cool.
Mix vegetables into seasoned rice.
Break eggs in the bowl and pour into the hot frying pan, then turn over like crepe, then cut eggs finely and sprinkle over the rice.

title: bagel pizza
directions: Cut bagels in half.
Place on broiling pan.
Put sauce on all halves of bagels.
Place shredded cheese on top of sauce. Sprinkle with oregano and garlic powder or any of your favorite spices.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Cover bottom of 13 x 9 x 2 pan with bread slices. Mix other ingredients and pour over bread. Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Bake next day at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken and pasta soup
directions: Saute onion, garlic and olive oil in saucepan.
Add other ingredients, except rotini, bring to boil and stir in pasta. Reduce heat and simmer until tender, about 12 minutes.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar, salt and cocoa together and then flour, soda and baking powder alternately with water then add vanilla. Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes.

title: cortney's twinkie cake
directions: Split Twinkies in half; layer in bottom of pan.
Prepare pudding as directed; mix all ingredients.
Spread on top of Twinkies.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook fryer until boiled tender.
Cool and take all meat off bones.
Add meat, onion, cut up boiled eggs and rice to juice from chicken.
Cook until rice is done.
Stir occasionally.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzel crumbs, oleo and sugar. Reserve 1/4 cup for the top.
Pat the rest in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Add all the ingredients except milk.
Simmer on low until onion is tender. Add milk and simmer.
Top with a teaspoon of butter per serving. Serve with oyster crackers or bread.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook the chicken and save the liquid.
Mix soup and the broth (liquid from cooking of chicken).
Remove chicken from bones.
Put layer of chicken, then layer of soup-broth mix, then 1/2 herb stuffing.
Repeat the layers again.
Sprinkle with melted margarine.
Bake in 350° oven until top is brown and mix bubbling.

title: garlic bread sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk and stir with a fork only until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board or pastry cloth and knead until smooth.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut dough into 1/2-inch strips with floured knife. Cut strips into 3-inch sticks.
Dip sticks into melted butter and roll into mixture of Parmesan cheese, oregano and garlic salt. Place on lightly greased baking sheet, about 3/4-inch apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 3 dozen sticks.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Store in large airtight container.

title: mom and dad's lumberjack salad
directions: Shred the first 3 ingredients 3 times.
Bring the last 6 items to a rolling boil for about 3 minutes. Remove from heat and pour over vegetables immediately. Stir until all cabbage is equal in color.
Let stand overnight and stir again.
Refrigerate until used.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar and corn syrup.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved. Cool. Add eggs, vanilla and salt. Blend well.
Pour filling into pastry shell. Top with pecans. Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes. Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: green fluff
directions: Do not drain juice from crushed pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: beef wrap-ups
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, cheeses, 1/4 teaspoon salt, garlic salt and egg white.
Reserve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute squash in oleo.
When nearly done, add onions.
Remove from heat; add bacon, soup, cheese, egg, bread crumbs and seasonings.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, onion and butter in frypan until tender.
Do not add any water.
Mix soup, milk, rice and cheese.
Mix two mixtures together.
Put in oblong casserole.
Cover with Pepperidge Farm stuffing as you would add bread crumbs.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mother's brownies
directions: Combine butter and sugar in large bowl; stir in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt; stir into butter mixture. Add nuts; mix well.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Spread Chocolate Frosting over top.

title: basque beef stew(guisado de vaca)
directions: Roll beef chunks in flour and brown in oil, using a heavy casserole or Dutch oven.
Add all ingredients except carrots and potatoes and cook over slow heat for 3 to 4 hours until meat is tender.
Add carrots and potatoes 45 minutes before stew is tender.

title: one bowl shoofly pie
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and shortening together and reserve 1 cup for tops and pies.
Add to remainder molasses, eggs, 1 1/2 cups hot water and mix.
Add soda to 1/2 cup of hot water and add promptly to mixture. Makes 2 (8-inch) pies.
Bake until crumbs are brown at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: mill st. deli chicken salad
directions: Mix all together and serve on lettuce or between your favorite bread.
Makes real good finger sandwiches.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Blend sugar and cake mix. Add oil and sour cream. Then add eggs, one at a time. Beat after each one. Pour 1/2
of batter in a greased tube pan. Top with cinnamon, nuts and
raisings. Then add remaining batter to pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar; beat at medium speed until smooth.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; beat well and set aside. Beat whipping cream until soft peaks form.
Fold into peanut butter mixture.

title: party hot dogs
directions: Melt jelly and stir in mustard.
Add hot dogs.
Keep over low heat and serve with toothpicks.

title: chicken del sur
directions: Cut chicken breast pieces in half; brown lightly in oil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Combine mushroom soup, sour cream and sherry.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fudge meltaways
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, coconut, cocoa and sugar.
Stir in 1/2 cup of margarine and water; mix well.
Press mixture in bottom of ungreased square baking pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Refrigerate while making frosting.

title: dainty biscuits
directions: Mix butter and flour with pastry blender.
Add sour cream. Drop 1/2 teaspoon pastry into tiny muffin pan.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 45 to 50 very small biscuits.

title: caramel apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add flour already mixed with soda and salt.
Add nuts and apples.
Put in 9 X 13 pan.
Place in cold 350° oven for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: homemade pastes
directions: Mix flour and cold water in a mixing bowl.
Add this mixture to the 2 cups of boiling water.
Cook it until mixture is clear. Store in an airtight container.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and refrigerate several hours.
Serve with carrots, celery, cauliflower, etc.

title: chow chow
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Let cook down for 1 to 2 hours.
Freeze or can in pints.

title: oowee gooey buttercakes
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix next 3 ingredients.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add oats, coconut and gumdrops.
Roll into small balls; put on greased cookie sheet.
Press flat with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: clear borsch
directions: Cover the meat with the water.
Add the salt, bring slowly to a boil and skim.
Cover and simmer for about 1 hour.
Add the vegetables and continue simmering for another hour.
Pour in the tomato juice.
Use enough lemon juice to get desired tartness. The garlic may or may not be added.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
If time permits, let the borsch stand for a while to blend the flavors.
Strain through a sieve.
Serve the clear borsch hot or cold with sour cream.

title: easy eggnog
directions: Combine pudding mix with 2 cups of the milk. Stir until slightly thickened. Stir in remaining 6 cups milk and eggnog until well blended.
Stir in brandy. Chill until ready to serve.
Top with whipped topping and sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired. Preparation time:
10 minutes.
Makes about 18 cups or 36 servings.

title: cucumber soup
directions: Place the cucumber, scallions and butter in a saucepan.
Cover with a circle of wax paper cut to fit the inside of the pan exactly.
Simmer over low heat for 19 minutes.
Discard the paper and add flour.
Stir in the chicken broth and lemon juice.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add salt if necessary.
Puree the soup in the blender and chill in the refrigerator for 4 hours.
Garnish each bowl with sour cream and dill weed.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pea salad
directions: Chop carrot, celery, and green pepper.
Add to other ingredients.
Leave overnight covered.
Can slice boiled egg on top.

title: diet fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit together.
Mix cottage cheese and orange juice together and pour over fruit just before serving.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of a 9-inch square pan; sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine dry cake mix, nuts and melted butter. (Mixture will be crumbly.)
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown. Top with whipped cream to serve.

title: meat balls and tomatoes with rice
directions: Mix meat and seasonings together and shape into balls.
Roll in uncooked rice and place in baking dish.
Add butter and tomatoes and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: betty's baked beef stew
directions: Cut beef into bite-sized pieces.
Combine all ingredients in greased casserole.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: barbara's apple spice frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix until smooth, and frost.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Clean broccoli and cut into 1/2 inch pieces.
Steam in 1/2 cup water until tender.
Do not drain; set aside.
Melt butter in large pan over medium heat.
Add flour, stirring constantly, to make sauce.
Cook 2 to 4 minutes.
Add chicken stock; still stirring, bring to a boil.
Turn heat on low.
Add broccoli, half and half, salt and pepper.
Heat slowly; do not let boil again.
Serves 8.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a greased bread pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry-rhubarb cobbler
directions: Drain cherries; save juice.
Drain rhubarb.
Combine tapioca, sugar, salt, cherries, juice and rhubarb in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil; remove from heat.
Combine sifted flour, baking powder, sugar and salt; sift together.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk gradually, stirring, until soft dough is formed.
Turn out on lightly floured board; knead 30 seconds or enough to shape.
Roll dough to fit dish; make several cuts near center.
Pour mixture into greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish; dot with butter.
Cover with dough.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Use cream, if desired.

title: chili con carne
directions: Cook ground beef and onion together until meat is brown and onion is yellow.
Add the beans and soup and cook for 10 minutes. Make a paste of the chili powder, flour, water and salt and add to mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, for about 45 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers or hot fried corn meal mush. Serves 8.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Bring to boil and serve.

title: bavarian kielbasa with noodles
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
In a large skillet, over medium heat, cook kielbasa and onion until browned, stirring often. Drain off fat.
Add soup and stir until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk. Add beans and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add cooked noodles.
Heat 2 minutes, stirring often.
Serve with mustard.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix well.
Thin with salad dressing if you desire or sour cream.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown beef and sausage in oil.
Simmer first 8 ingredients for 1 hour.
Mix together the cottage cheese, eggs, salt, pepper, parsley flakes and Parmesan cheese and set aside.
Cook and drain noodles.
Rinse in cold water and place half the noodles in pan. Spread half the cottage cheese mixture over the noodles and top with half the mozzarella cheese, then half the meat.
Repeat this process.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan at 375° for 30 minutes. Makes 15 servings.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Stir together and heat.
Serve warm with large Fritos or Doritos for dipping.

title: sirloin steak salad
directions: Season steak to taste with garlic powder, pepper and seasoned salt.
Grill to desired doneness.
Chill in fridge and trim. Slice thinly across grain into strips.
Combine salad dressing mix, mayonnaise and sour cream; mix well.
Chill.
Toss steak with enough dressing to coat.
Add tomatoes and mushrooms.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt stick of butter in bottom of pan.
Mix together sugar, flour, and milk.
Stir well.
Pour over butter in baking dish. Pour peaches over batter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: nut crisp
directions: In a heavy skillet, mix sugar, butter and nuts. Stir over low heat until nuts are
toasted and syrup is caramel coated. Mix in vanilla. Pour onto foil and sprinkle with salt. Let cool completely. Break into pieces.

title: nanny's pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat.
Stir in flour and salt, then add crushed pineapple.
Drop onto cookie sheets and bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Put cornmeal and flour in bowl. Toss to mix. Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well. Pour oil into 8 or 9-inch black skillet. Put in 425° oven to heat while mixing cornmeal/flour. Pour hot oil into cornmeal mix; stir well. Pour mixture back into skillet. Bake 25 minutes in 425° oven. (Flip cornbread over the last 5 minutes to brown the top side.)

title: ham spread
directions: Chop green onions very fine.
Mix softened cream cheese and mayo together, then add ham and onions and mix well.
Makes great party sandwiches or can be used as a dip.

title: bean dip
directions: Boil together first 3 ingredients. Mix in remaining ingredients. Serve with corn chips. If doubling, don't double the onion.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over cabbage leaves.
Let stand 5 minutes. Drain.
Heat ground beef until brown.
Add onion, rice and egg. Roll a portion of filling into each leaf.
Fasten ends with toothpicks.
Place cabbage rolls in cooker.
Pour tomato soup and water over rolls.
Cook 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: oven baked herb chicken
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a plastic bag. Coat chicken with butter-flavored cooking spray and place in bag, shaking to coat.
Place chicken on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray and lightly coat chicken with cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add berries, pineapple, banana and nuts.
Pour half of mixture into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Let congeal leaving rest of mixture at room temperature.
Spoon sour cream over set gelatin, then pour remaining gelatin on top; chill.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix together and finish filling churn with milk and fruit.

title: nebraska stew via depression era(aunt ruth's mother-in-law)
directions: Cook hamburger and beef bouillon in 2 quarts water. Cool and put in refrigerator overnight. Remove fat from pot and discard. In stew pot, add stewed tomatoes, tomato juice, onions and garlic. Cook as you prepare the rest of the vegetables. Add cabbage last as it cooks quickly.

title: beer
directions: Dissolve sugar and yeast in lukewarm water.
Mix in beer. Pour in steamed, clean bottles; cork and store in cool place. Ready to drink after 4 to 5 days.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix lime Jell-O and hot water.
Add crushed pineapple and sugar.
Let stand until it starts to jell.
Add celery, soft cream cheese, Dream Whip and nuts, if desired; let set until firm.
(I sometimes add a few miniature marshmallows, if you wish to make a larger salad.)

title: hawaiian meat balls
directions: Combine beef, onion, salt, milk and bread crumbs; form into balls and brown.
Combine pineapple juice and water to make 1 cup. Add cornstarch, vinegar, sugar and soy sauce; cook until thick and clear.
Add green peppers and pineapple.
Pour over meat balls.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: dada's cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Melt margarine in 8-inch square pan.
Pour excess into mixture and mix.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Combine sugar and water; bring to a boil. Cook on medium for 5 minutes. Add cranberries and cook until they pop, 10 to 15 minutes (they become transparent). Remove from heat. Combine orange marmalade and lemon juice. Allow mixture to cool.

title: tea biscuits
directions: Melt margarine,
then
mix
with
flour and sour cream. Fill small muffin
tin
about full.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes. Yields 2 dozen.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together.
Roll into balls.
Let chill for 4 hours. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: low calorie hot dish
directions: Cut cabbage in 1/2-inch wedges and place in bottom of casserole.
Brown hamburger and onions and drain off excess fat. Add rice and place on top of cabbage.
Mix tomato soup with can of water and heat.
Pour over all and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: aunt sheryl's strawberry bread
directions: Beat oil and eggs; add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts and strawberries.
Mix together.
Grease and flour six mini loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: german brown stew and noodles
directions: Brown meat in Crisco; drain.
Add apple, carrots, onion, 1/2 cup water, salt, pepper, garlic and bouillon cubes.
Place in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Simmer about 2 hours.
Combine cornstarch with 1/4 cup cold water and Kitchen Bouquet.
Add to meat mixture.
Stir until thick and serve over hot noodles.

title: payday bar cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together cake mix, 1/3 c. butter or margarine and egg.
Press into the bottom of a 9x13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 18 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with marshmallows.
Return to oven for 1 to 2 minutes or until marshmallows begin to puff.
In a saucepan over medium heat cook corn syrup, 1/4 c. butter, vanilla and peanut butter chips until melted.
Remove from heat, stir in rice cereal and peanuts.
Spoon mixture over marshmallow topped cake and spread to cover.
Allow to cool before serving.

title: fritters
directions: Stir until thick.
Get a tablespoon and get out the mix.
You can get a pouring pitcher.
Fix the mix; make little pancakes on top of the stove on high heat.
Serves 1.

title: ice cream topping
directions: Melt butter in medium sauce pan; add sugar, corn syrup and flour, stirring well.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, stirring constantly for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Spread pecans on baking sheet.
Bake at 300 degrees for 15 minutes.
Gradually stir milk, candy pieces and pecans into syrup mixture.
Serve over ice cream.

title: crab casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix and bake 30 minutes, until top is golden brown.

title: swedish pastry
directions: Place yeast in large bowl.
Mix in a little milk and make a paste. Smash any lumps!
Add sugar, salt, remaining milk and eggs, beating well after each addition.
Fill sifter with flour and sift into mix.
Make just past sticky stage.
Pour out onto board and knead.
Roll dough out and place 3 cubes of margarine on it.
Fold dough over margarine and smash.
Margarine will come through flour a little.
Roll out again and fold.
Repeat.
Place in refrigerator for 15 minutes.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; stir in marshmallows until they start to dissolve.
Add orange sherbet and fold in oranges, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: cheddar-scallion soda bread(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a cookie sheet. Coarsely chop scallions.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken bonne femme
directions: Pound chicken to 1/4-inch; set aside. In double boiler over hot (not boiling) water, beat egg yolks, wine and lemon with whisk until thickened. Add 1/4 cup butter, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating constantly until it thickens. Add tarragon, red pepper and 1/4 teaspoon salt; cover and keep warm.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening, brown sugar and white sugar.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together; add to sugar-egg mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in M&M's and chocolate chips.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and set aside.
Mix last 5 ingredients and then add to liquid.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Check with a toothpick.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: There are two ways to make this.
The second way is dietetic.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add pumpkin, egg and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 375° oven.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let set a little while before cooking. Drop by small spoonfuls in deep fry.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Set aside.
Mix together milk and pudding mix well.
Add cream cheese mixture.
Fold in whipped topping.
Using 8-inch diameter plastic flowerpot, layer ingredients.
Begin and end with Oreos.
(May also use 9 x 13-inch dish.)

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Make the day before using. Store in refrigerator. Serve over salad of fresh spinach, sliced water chestnuts, bean sprouts, mushrooms, sliced hard-boiled eggs and bacon bits.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Sift flour once.
Measure; add baking powder, salt, granulated sugar and 1 tablespoon cocoa.
Sift again.
Add milk, shortening and vanilla.
Mix only until smooth.
Then add nuts.
Pour into greased casserole or small baking dish.

title: broiled soft shell crabs
directions: Preheat broiler.
Combine butter, lemon juice and pepper. Roll crab in butter mixture and then lightly in flour.
Put on rack, 2-inches from heat and broil for 10 minutes.
Turn once.

title: chicken noodle and chinese cabbage quick soup
directions: Boil chicken noodle soup with 2 cups water, kamaboko and mushrooms for 3 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium and add cabbage until cooked.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle green onion for garnish.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and buttermilk and stir well.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to batter.
Mix well and add 1 cup jam. Line pan and bake 1 hour in 300° oven.

title: blueberry swirl cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs and pour into pie crust.
Spoon 1/4 can pie filling on top.
Gently swirl with toothpick.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Serve topped with remaining pie filling.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute celery, onion and mushrooms in oleo.
Cook broccoli according to box; drain and add to sauteed mixture, then add soup. Melt cheese, add to broccoli mixture.
Mix well.
Serve warm with chips or crackers.

title: pork chops and corn dressing
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine eggs, corn, butter, celery, onions, bread cubes, paprika, salt and pepper.
Spoon into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange pork chops over dressing.
Sprinkle with additional paprika and salt.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes or until chops are tender. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan the pie filling and pineapple with juice mix. Sprinkle cake mix and walnuts on top. Slice butter and place randomly over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grandma's caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Over medium heat, combine first 4 ingredients and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in baking soda.
Stir well.
Pour over 8 quarts popped corn.
Stir to coat well.
Bake in large roaster or pan 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on waxed paper to dry.

title: orange salad
directions: Empty cool whip into bowl. Add cottage cheese, oranges and jello. Mix well and place in refrigerator.

title: norwegian fatigmann' butter cookie
directions: Beat eggs 10 minutes, add sugar to eggs and beat.
Add cream, vanilla or cardemon and enough flour to make a soft dough and roll very thin on pastry cloth with covered rolling pin.
Use flour generously on cloth and rolling pin cover if desired.
Cut into diamond shapes with knife or pastry wheel cutter.
Fry in deep fat until barely brown.
Dust with powdered sugar when still warm. Makes a large batch.
Store in covered box, not in tight container.

title: praline graham crackers
directions: Line jelly roll pan with crackers.
Boil sugar and butter for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour over crackers and spread.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan to cool.
Break in half if you want.

title: seafood kebabs
directions: In a shallow dish, let six 12-inch wooden skewers soak in water to cover for 2 hours and let them drain on paper towel.
Cut each salmon fillet crosswise into six 1-inch thick slices.
Discard any small bones and beginning with the thicker end of each slice, roll the slice into a coil.
Thread one of the shrimp and one scallop onto a skewer, add 2 salmon coils and add another scallop and shrimp.
Make 5 more kebabs with remaining shrimp, scallops and salmon coils in same manner.
Can be prepared and chilled for several hours.

In a small bowl, stir brown sugar and lemon juice. Salt and pepper the kebabs; brush with brown sugar mixture and grill over glowing coals, basting often for 4 to 5 minutes on each side until salmon just flakes and shrimp are pink and firm.
Brush with remaining brown sugar mix.
Garnish with lemon wedges and dill sprigs.

title: pan fried trout
directions: Mix buttermilk and egg in a bowl.
Mix oat bran, flour, salt and pepper in shallow bowl.
Dip trout first in buttermilk mixture, then in oat bran mixture.
Shake off excess.
Heat oil and butter in large skillet on medium heat.
Add trout.
Reduce heat.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes on each side.
Garnish with lemon (use nonstick pan).

title: bourbon balls
directions: Sift together cocoa and sugar.
Combine and stir in whiskey and corn syrup.
Add and mix thoroughly the vanilla wafers and pecans.
Roll mixture into small balls and dredge in powdered sugar.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream first 2 and gradually add sugar. Beat well.
Add flour, egg and vanilla.
Blend well.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Press cherry or pecan into each.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs; add vanilla, apples, raisins and nuts.
Add sifted dry ingredients, mixing well after each addition.
Makes 2 large loaves and 1 small loaf.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown meat, onion and peppers.
Drain.
Add corn, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Mix cornbread mix according to package; add meat mixture.
Mix well.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: trifle
directions: Spread the sponge cakes with jam and cut into small pieces. Add the sherry or fruit juice.
Cover the cake with the fruit, slicing the banana and peach and dividing the orange in sections. Pour the custard over the cake and fruit; leave in a cool place until completely set.
Decorate as desired with whipped cream, ratafia biscuits, cut angelica, glazed cherries, etc.
A glass dish makes this an attractive dessert.

title: mamie's meat loaf
directions: Save 1/4 cup tomato sauce, mix remaining ingredients well. Shape into loaves and put on a broiler pan sprayed with pam. Top with remaining tomato sauce.
Bake in a 375 degree oven for 1 hour.

title: shirley's easy broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli in salted water for 5 minutes; drain well.
Add soup, mayonnaise, egg, cheese, mushrooms, onion and pepper to taste to cooked broccoli.
Pour into baking dish; dot with butter. Top with crushed saltine or Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; longer if you double or triple recipe.

title: potatoes florentine
directions: Thinly slice potatoes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease rectangular baking dish, 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch.
Layer potatoes in dish; top with onion.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over top.
Bake until potatoes are tender, about 35 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix the three beans together and drain.
Add onion and green pepper.
Heat together until blended vinegar, salad oil, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour liquid over the beans and refrigerate overnight.
Good 24 hours, excellent 36 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Shake quartered biscuits in a plastic bag, a few at a time. Arrange on bottom of a loaf pan.
Sprinkle a layer at a time with the butter, brown sugar and walnuts crumbled together.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Cook ground beef and onions until tender.
Stir in taco seasoning, spread in a quiche pan and top with peppers.
Beat milk, Bisquick mix and eggs until smooth.
Pour over meat mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until firm.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: cheesy chili bake
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of greased baking dish.
Spread chili over cream cheese.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: cheesy macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Rinse with hot water; drain.
Add the package of cheese that came with the macaroni. Let cool.
Add the onion and green pepper.
Stir in as much mayonnaise as desired.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients. Stir well. Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Steam cauliflower until tender.
Arrange in a casserole.
Mix soup, mayo and cheese; pour over casserole.
Melt butter in bread crumbs until crumbly.
Sprinkle over cauliflower.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: cinnamon flops
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle top with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Dot with butter; top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix juice, margarine, powdered sugar and vanilla wafers well. Add chopped nuts.
Grease hands.
Form into balls.
Roll in coconut and powdered sugar.
Store, covered, in refrigerator. Also may be frozen.

title: ham delights
directions: To cut rolls, completely slice through the middle, separating the top from the bottom.
Cream margarine, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and onion.
Spread tops and bottoms with creamed mixture.
Then add boiled ham and Swiss cheese, divided evenly over the rolls.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
To serve, cut into individual rolls.
Yields 60.

title: fruited sweet potatoes
directions: Combine cherry pie filling, orange juice, butter and salt in saucepan; cook slowly for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: homemade soup
directions: Fry hamburger or boil stew meat until done.
Pour vegetables and liquids into crock-pot.
Add meat.
Simmer until you are ready to enjoy.

title: cherry surprise
directions: Spray an oblong pan with Pam.
Put cherry pie filling on bottom.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans. Spoon crushed pineapple for next layer.
Melt butter for topping. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: lizzie's meat balls with corn and green peppers
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, onion, egg and seasonings.
Mix thoroughly.
Form into small balls and roll in flour.
Brown balls in lard or oil.
Saute slowly until meat is cooked through.
Heat corn and green pepper rings.
Transfer to hot serving platter. Arrange meat balls on top of corn and green pepper rings.
Serve. Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Combine crumbs, butter, peanut butter and sugar.
Work together until smooth.
Press mixture into a 9 x 9-inch pan or larger for small squares.
Melt chips over boiling water.
Spread melted chips over mixture in pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: applesauce cake bars
directions: In large bowl, put first 8 ingredients.
Add lard, applesauce and eggs.
Mix on low then 3 to 5 minutes on medium.
Stir in raisins.
Bake in 15 x 10-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost or leave plain.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Boil water; dissolve Jell-O.
Add 7-Up and fold in container of Cool Whip or spread on top of Jell-O.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Combine gelatin and water.
Place in refrigerator.
When slightly set, fold in sherbet and orange segment.
Chill until cool.

title: apple nut pudding with hot rum sauce
directions: Combine sugar, butter, eggs, vanilla and flavoring.
Beat until fluffy.
Add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and water.
Beat 2 minutes with mixer.
Stir in apples and pecans.
Spoon into greased 13 x 9 baking pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Mix lime and two gallons water and pour over sliced cucumbers. Soak 24 hours.
Rinse three times in cool water.
Soak 3 hours in ice water.
Drain.
Mix vinegar, sugar and salt.
Pour over cucumbers and let set overnight.
Add pickling spice to taste. Then boil 35 minutes and jar.

title: brown gravy
directions: Heat fat in a skillet.
Add flour and season with salt and pepper.
Stir until mixture is dark brown.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients.
Spread into pan (round pizza pan). Top with next 4 ingredients.
Sprinkle with remaining taco mix. Use as a dip for chips or taco chips.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry onion with hamburger.
Cook noodles until soft; drain excess water, then mix all ingredients together in big roaster. Put bread crumbs on top.
Put in oven until bread is browned and serve.

title: honey carrots
directions: Melt margarine in frying pan.
Add orange juice and honey. Toss in carrots until well coated.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour or until fork tender.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and peppers.
Drain.
Add mushrooms, olives, spaghetti sauce and oregano.
Simmer all together.
Cook small box of spaghetti, break into small pieces.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, sour cream and eggs until creamy.
Pour 1/2 in pan.
In separate bowl, mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on mixture in pan.
Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: diana's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars and shortening.
Beat in the eggs and vanilla.
Stir in the flour, soda and salt.
Then stir in the oatmeal, then the raisins.
Bake on ungreased baking sheets at 350°.
Drop by large spoonfuls, 2 inches apart, or spread in jelly roll pan for bars.
Bake just until golden and set, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: whole green chilies
directions: In quart baking dish, layer Jack cheese, split green chilies and Cheddar cheese.
Gradually add milk to flour, mixing until well blended.
Add eggs; mix well.
Pour over cheese.
Cover and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and allow to stand for 10 minutes.
Serve with Del Monte taco sauce and sour cream if desired.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: oreo cookies dessert
directions: Crush cookies until very fine.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save approximately 1/4 cup cookies.
Pour 1/2 cup melted butter over cookies.
Put in freezer for 15 minutes.
Combine 1 bowl Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Set aside.
Mix pudding.
Spread cream cheese layer over cookies, pudding over cream cheese layer. Put 1 bowl Cool Whip on top of cream cheese layer.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup cookies over top.
Refrigerate.

title: spirited apricot slush(serves 34 half cup servings)
directions: In large nonmetal container, combine all ingredients, except 1 liter of lemon-lime flavored beverage; blend well.
Freeze 1 to 2 days until firm.
Remove slush from freezer 1 1/2 to 2 hours before serving.
To serve, place slush mixture in punch bowl. Stir gently.
Garnish with lemon, lime and orange slices.

title: old fashioned peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients until well mixed.
Roll into small balls and flatten tenderly with your fingers or a fork.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Yield:
45 to 50 cookies.

title: pecan cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in order listed.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Pour mixture into an ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Invert pan and cool cake completely.
Remove from pan.
Sprinkle top of cake with powdered sugar.
May use walnuts instead of pecans.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: In a medium-sized saucepan, heat soup.
Add cream cheese and gelatin which has been softened in 1/2 cup cold water.
Beat until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour into an oiled mold; chill until set.
Unmold 1 hour before serving; garnish with fresh parsley.
Serve with melba toast or sesame seed wafers.
Yield: 1 (5-cup) mold.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Melt butter and broth; mix with soups and pour over chicken.
Spoon on cooked veggies; salt and pepper.
Mix milk and Bisquick until smooth; spoon over veggies.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until bubbly and brown.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump the pineapple (without draining) into pan and spread over bottom.
Add the cherry pie filling and spread that, too.
Sift the cake mix over the fruit as evenly as possible.
Sprinkle with pecans over the cake mix.
Distribute butter pats evenly over the mixture, then sprinkle evenly with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for an hour.
Serve hot with ice cream or cold with whipped cream.

title: popcorn caramel corn
directions: Place popcorn and peanuts on a large jelly roll pan.
In saucepan, combine sugar, oleo and corn syrup; boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and soda.
(This foams up a lot, so use a good size pan.)
Pour over popcorn and mix well.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes, stirring twice while baking.
Remove from pan immediately and cool on wax paper.

title: zesty chicken romano
directions: Marinate peppers, onion and mushrooms in Italian salad dressing. In a separate dish, marinate chicken breasts using more salad dressing for 1 hour. Place vegetables including dressing and chicken without dressing into a deep casserole dish. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Remove from oven. Remove chicken and set aside. Stir in cooked linguine. Replace chicken and bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: fettuccine florentine
directions: Cook fettuccine in boiling water.
Drain and keep warm.
Place frozen spinach in a pan of boiling water for 3 minutes, drain well and squeeze dry.
Heat oil in frying pan over medium heat; add onion and saute until translucent.
Add spinach and cook, stirring frequently.
Add spinach mixture to fettuccine.
Add Ricotta cheese, milk, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring lightly until well mixed.
Transfer to a serving bowl and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening with sugars.
In a small bowl, beat together vanilla and eggs.
Add to shortening/sugar mixture.
In another bowl, sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add 1/2 cup of M&M's.
Drop dough onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Place remainder of M&M's on each cookie before baking.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: plain layer cake
directions: Cream shortening with 3/4 cup sugar.
Add flavoring and egg yolks; cream again.
Sift and measure flour; add baking powder and salt and sift again.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to first mixture, adding about 1/3 at a time.
Fold in egg whites, beaten stiffly into which remaining 1/4 cup of sugar has been beaten.
Pour batter into lightly greased and floured pans (or pan).
Good plain or you can frost.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour salad dressing over mix.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
Serve with Fritos or corn chips.

title: pumpkin pound cake
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients; set aside. Blend oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, to oil and sugar mixture.
Beat well after each addition. Add pumpkin and mix well. Blend in dry ingredients and pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lasagne meat loaf
directions: Combine hamburger, crumbs, 1/2 cup tomato sauce, 1 egg, oregano and salt.
Press mixture evenly in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.

title: mama's peanut butter candy
directions: Put
peanut butter and butter in double boiler and heat so it will
spread easily.
Put 3 cups sugar, 1 cup water and Karo syrup in one vessel to cook.
Put other cup of sugar and 1 cup
water in	another
vessel.
When	first vessel is done enough to	crack against
a glass when dropped in cold water, pour
slowly over stiffly beaten egg whites.	Beat until other vessel gets done, then pour it in, beating constantly.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and other ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Cook in a 350° preheated oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until set.

title: fruit crunch
directions: Put fruit in dish; sprinkle with sugar.
Mix flour, sugar and egg until lumpy.
Sprinkle over fruit and pour melted margarine on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and cook for 5 minutes.
Mix the flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut shortening into the flour mixture with a pastry cutter.
Mix in milk with fork.
Divide into 6 pieces.
Roll out on floured wax paper.
Fill with 1 apple, dotted with butter and a small amount of cinnamon and nutmeg. Fold dough over apples and put into a glass baking dish.
Pour sugar mixture over all dumplings and sprinkle each with a small amount of cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Sprinkle mixed vegetables in bottom of greased 2-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Over this, sprinkle onion, then the ground chuck, salt and pepper to taste.
Over this, pour cream of celery soup, mixed with 1/4 cup water.
Arrange Tater Tots over entire casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Remove from oven; top with cheese and bake uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: heavenly orange fluff
directions: Mix jello and water.
Add frozen orange juice.
Drain pineapple and oranges.
Add to jello mixture.
Put in fridge to set.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.
Stir mixture 2 to 3 times as it freezes.
Serve salad barely thawed.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off grease.
Put meat back into skillet and add onion.
Cook until tender.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes, salt and seasoning and simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook lasagne noodles and drain.

title: mushroom squares
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add mushrooms and onion, sauteed in lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Press dough in sheet pan. Spread with cream cheese.
Top with sausage, mushrooms, onion and Parmesan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: now that's chili!!
directions: Cook beef, garlic, onion and green pepper in heavy skillet over medium high heat, stirring to break up meat.
Cook until onion is soft and meat has lost its pink color.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes, stirring frequently.
Do not substitute or leave out any ingredients.
Truly delicious chili!

title: hot sauce(satan's sauce)
directions: 1. Grind peppers in blender until fine. 2. Mix everything and simmer for 27 minutes.
Allow to cool and bottle up.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: mimosas
directions: Prepare one can orange juice concentrate according to can directions.
Pour into ice cube trays. Place a cherry in each cube. Freeze 8 hours or overnight.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix oil, sugars and vanilla.
Beat in the eggs.
Stir in flour and cinnamon, then oatmeal.
Spoon out onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° until a golden brown.

title: poppy surprise roll
directions: Scald milk; cool 1/4 c. to lukewarm; add yeast and 1 tsp. sugar and let stand in warm place to rise for 30 minutes.
To remainder of milk, add butter, sugar and salt.
Keep lukewarm.
Add egg yolk and beat well.
Stir in yeast and half of flour; beat well.
Add rest of flour and knead until smooth and elastic.
Cover and let rise until double.
Roll and spread with poppy seed filling.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: kelvey's taco salad
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Put all ingredients in a crock-pot; mix well.
Cook slowly for 2 or 3 hours.
Serve over nacho chips; top with tossed salad.
Very good.

title: strips of beef casserole
directions: Brown meat in shortening and add all ingredients except flour, 1/2 cup of water and sour cream.
Cook slowly until tender.
Mix flour and 1/2 cup water; stir slowly into meat mixture.
Add sour cream and stir.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with Sour Cream Puffs.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Melt over hot water, 1/2 cup peanut butter morsels.
Stir until smooth.
Set aside.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine butter and sugar; beat until creamy.
Blend in melted morsels. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Alternately blend in flour and milk. Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch round pans.
Bake at 350° approximately 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Remove from pans.
Fill layers and frost sides and top with Peanut Butter Frosting.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Combine eggs and sugar.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and add to egg mixture.
Stir in dates, cherries, chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour batter into two well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove and cool completely.
Let stand overnight before serving.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Slice top 1/3 of French bread loaf long way.
Make a boat by hollowing out part of lower part. Line boat with Saran Wrap prior to filling.
Cut top part and remove part of loaf into small pieces.
Spread dip on to bread pieces.

title: corn flake drop cookies
directions: Mix sugar and light corn syrup over medium burner.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
(Do not cook to "strings".) Add peanut butter and stir.
Add corn flakes and stir gently, coating evenly. (You can add nuts or nutty peanut butter if you want.)
Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.
Let cool.
Keep in airtight container or Ziploc bags.

title: orange mandarin salad
directions: Heat two cups of water to boil.
Pour in jello and dissolve. Mix in cream cheese.
Add juice from oranges plus cold water to make 2 cups.
Refrigerate until set.
Take out and add Cool Whip, oranges and pecans. Mix well with a mixer.
Return to fridge and let set until firm.

title: marinated summer salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, except radishes.
Cover and chill 12 hours or overnight.
Stir occasionally.
Add radishes before serving. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Melt butter or margarine and chocolate and remove from heat. Add vanilla and sugar.
Add 1 egg and beat 5 minutes.
Add next egg and beat 5 more minutes.
Pour in pie shell and let set 3 to 4 hours in refrigerator.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: Chop or grind peppers, onions and celery.
Pour boiling water over mixture; let stand 10 minutes.
Drain off all juices.
Put in a large kettle and add sugar, vinegar and spices.
Boil this mixture for 10 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
Makes 9 pints. Very good.

title: quick-n-easy southern biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease baking sheet.
Put flour in a bowl and "hollow out" by pushing it to sides of bowl.
Add milk and shortening and pull flour down from edges.
Mix together, forming a ball
of dough.
Shape quickly; less kneading will form fluffier biscuits.
Sprinkle flour on hands and pinch off desired amount.
Roll and pat into shape with least amount of patting for fluffy, tasty biscuits.
Bake approximately 12 to 15 minutes. Remove from oven and butter biscuit tops generously.
Biscuits may be returned to oven if not fully cooked; watch for golden brown color.
Yields approximately 16 biscuits.

title: artichoke appetizer
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon into a lightly greased pan, casserole or souffle dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Serve with Ritz crackers or Melba rounds.
Yield:
3 cups.

title: apple casserole
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together, then add milk in a long Pyrex dish.
Place apple slices.
Pour the cheese mixture over apples and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cook only until hot and bubbly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove from container and cook egg noodles in chicken broth until tender 7 to 10 minutes.
Remove chicken from bones and cut up small.
Mix chicken, noodles, soup and sour cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put in casserole dish and crumble bread on top.
Melt margarine and pour over bread crumbs.

title: peanut butter and oatmeal cookies
