directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat margarine or butter and peanut butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed about 30 seconds or until margarine or butter is softened.
Add sugar and brown sugar to margarine mixture.
Beat until thoroughly combined, scraping sides of bowl occasionally.
Add egg whites and vanilla. Beat until well mixed.
Add flour and baking soda.
Beat on low speed until combined.
Stir in oats.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoons 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375 degree oven about 8 minutes or until edges are golden. Transfer cookies to a wire rack.
Cool completely.
If you bake at 350 degrees, add a few minutes to cook time.
Makes about 36 cookies.

title: sausage and peppers
directions: In a large skillet, saute sausage (first, prick with fork) for approximately 10 minutes.
Remove fat; place in baking pan.
Seed and core peppers; cut into 1-inch strips.
Peel and slice onion. Dice tomatoes.
Place sausage, peppers, onion, tomatoes, salt and pepper in pan; bake in a 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.

title: cranberry-apple relish
directions: Finely chop all ingredients in food processor.
Cover. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Makes 3 cups.

title: chocolate chip tarts
directions: Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on shells.
Mix eggs, melted butter, Karo syrup and vanilla together.
Pour over pecans and chips in shells.
Bake 350 for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cowboy stew
directions: In Dutch oven brown ground beef.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder.
Stir well.
Add tomatoes, corn, beans and potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt butter; beat eggs lightly.
Add sugar, milk, melted butter, coconut and lemon extract.
Pour into uncooked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until brown.
Makes 2 to 3 pies.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil sugar, water and cornstarch until clear.
Add jello.
Let cool and then add strawberries.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter a 9-inch glass pie dish.
Mix sugar and apples together and put them in the pie dish.
Mix flour, brown sugar, butter, cinnamon and nutmeg to form a crumbly mixture.
Put on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: grandma b's green tomato pie
directions: Bring tomatoes and lemon to boil over medium heat.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and water.
Stir into tomato mix.
Add sugar, margarine, cinnamon and salt.
Stir.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Place in 9-inch pie plate with pie crust and cover with another crust.
Cut vents to allow steam to escape. Heat oven to 425°.
Bake 35 minutes until golden brown.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash in boiling, salted water, about10 minutes.
Drain thoroughly.
Add soup, sour cream, carrots and onion.
Mix stuffing with margarine.
Place half stuffing in bottom of 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole.
Pour in zucchini mixture.
Top with rest of stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until light brown on top.

title: heavenly hash salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and milk until smooth.
Drain pineapple juice (1 cup) and bring to a boil; remove from stove.
Add jello.
Add this to cream cheese and milk mixture.
Add pineapple and nuts. Refrigerate.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Place green peppers, red peppers, sugar and vinegar in a large pot.
Bring to a full, rolling boil over high heat.
Reduce to medium-low heat and let mixture simmer 10 minutes.
Assemble and attache fruit/vegetable strainer.
Turn to speed 4; strain peppers and liquid.
Return strained liquid to pot and add food coloring as desired.
Add liquid pectin.
Bring to a full boil (rolling) over high heat.
Reduce heat slightly and boil 1 minute.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut and wash thoroughly.
Combine kraut with rest of ingredients and blend.
Chill before serving.

title: stuffed minute steaks
directions: Combine stuffing mix and green pepper in bowl.
Add mixture of hot water and margarine; mix well.
Spoon 1/2 cup onto each steak. Roll to enclose filling; secure with toothpicks.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Pour mixture of honey and soy sauce over top. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough in 1/4-inch slices and place on a cookie sheet.
Pinch together.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese and sugar thoroughly.
Spread over cookie dough and arrange assorted fruit on top.

title: compota de valencia
directions: Simmer the prunes or figs in the sherry and apricot syrup for several minutes.
Add the cinnamon, allspice (if used) and orange rind.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add the drained apricots and orange sections.
Chill.
Serve in goblets.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix together all ingredients except mushrooms, soup and water. Make thick hamburger patties, about 5 to a pound.
Roll patties in flour; lightly sear in small amount of shortening.
Place in a greased baking dish and pour over with mushrooms, soup and water. Bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: potatoes romaine
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients; pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut cream pie supreme
directions: In a small bowl, beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat at medium speed 2 to 3 minutes.
Blend in melted chocolate and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spread 1 cup chocolate filling evenly into Keebler extra 2 servings graham cracker crust.
Reserve remaining chocolate filling for top of pie.
Sprinkle with peanuts.

title: executive power dinner
directions: Call home first.
If your wife, daughter, neighbor or anyone else answers the phone, try talking them into cooking a real supper for you.
If no answer, try leaving a message as a last resort.
If the phone rings 12 times, assume no one is home and drive to the commissary.
Once inside, see if any company is passing out free cooked food samples.
If not, proceed to the frozen food section and select your microwave meal for the evening.
Do your best to pick a "healthy" meal by checking the back of the box (good luck). Pay.
Leave fast.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cut fruit in small pieces.
Leave pecans in halves.
Sift flour, salt and soda over fruit and pecans.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in vanilla and cinnamon. Stir in flour-covered fruit.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 300° for about 25 minutes.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice with juice of cherries and pineapple and enough water so you have 2 cups cooked rice.
Combine pineapple and marshmallows; set aside.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and mayonnaise. Chop cherries and mix all together with Cool Whip and nuts. Chill.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients except cheese.
Grease casserole dish.
Place mixture in dish and top with grated cheese.
Cover and bake thoroughly for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: uncle joe's punch
directions: Mix sodas in a large bowl.
Slice 1 whole orange into punch. Add cherries if using blackberry soda or strawberries if using strawberry soda.
Add ice.
Makes one gallon.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Blanch leaves in boiling salted water about 2 minutes; remove and drain.
Combine next 7 ingredients.
Divide mixture into 12 portions.
Wrap each portion in a cabbage leaf and tie with string.
In a large skillet or fryer, brown cabbage lightly in oil, adding more oil if needed.
Reduce heat; add tomato sauce and water.
Cover and cook for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: kool-aid play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Add oil and water.
Stir until mixed.
Knead with your hands until soft and firm.
Let cool.
(If dough seems too oily, add some flour and knead.)

title: carrot hot dish
directions: Mix drained carrots with onion, butter, soup, salt and Cheddar cheese which has been heated in a pan.
Toss together the 1/2 cup melted butter and croutons and spoon over carrot mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: dilled cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers in food processor. Mix together next 5 ingredients and pour over cukes. Chill for 4 hours before serving. 20 calories per 1/2 cup serving.

title: roast veal dinner
directions: Wash veal. Place in roasting pan. Add the rest of the ingredients. Stir well. Roast at 350° for 2 to 3 hours.
Check and stir periodically. Add water if getting too thick.
Serve with cooked egg noodles (wide), peas and tossed salad.
Easy and good.

title: chicken salad for two
directions: Shred 1/2 teaspoon peel from orange.
Peel and section orange over bowl to catch juice.
Reserve 1 teaspoon juice.
Set sections aside.
Combine peel, reserved juice, sour cream, honey and poppy seed.
Cover and chill.
Toss together orange sections, chicken, grapes, pecans and celery.
To serve, spoon onto spinach lined plates.
Spoon 1 tablespoon dressing over top of each.
Cover and chill remaining dressing.

title: depression plant(coal plant)
directions: Pour water, bluing and ammonia over lump of coal, then sprinkle the salt.
Put a few drops of food coloring over the salt (any color).
Watch it grow.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips together in a big pan.
Pour the Corn Chex.
Pour chocolate and butter over Corn Chex and mix well.
In one big grocery bag, pour confectioners sugar.
Pour in mixture and shake well.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need a medium-size flowerpot.

title: green bean salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all the drained cans of beans and add oil, vinegar, sugar, garlic powder, pepper, sliced onion and parsley. Mix well. Let beans marinate (soak) for at least 2 hours. You do not have to refrigerate it. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: cheese cake
directions: Crust:
Melt 1 stick butter, added to 20 to 30 graham crackers and 1 teaspoon powdered sugar.
Set aside.

title: jimmy's brownies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Place in 9 x 9-inch pan and cook in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until done.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix and chill.
Shape into balls and roll in coconut.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook quick rice as directed on package in electric frypan.
Put in 1/2 stick butter and melt.
Add onion (cut up), one green pepper (cut small) and one small can mushrooms (cut and drained).
Cook all ingredients until tender.
Then add La Choy sauce, brown gravy and La Choy soy sauce.
Stir quickly and add rice.
Mix well. Cover and simmer about 10 minutes.
Do not make it boil.

title: toasted chili pecans
directions: Toss pecans in butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with chili powder and salt; toss to coat.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add taco mix and stir.
Add tomatoes, corn, beans and chopped onions.
Heat through and serve.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: punch delicious
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients as directed, then add pineapple juice.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: In crock-pot, combine all ingredients; cook, uncovered, stirring often on high setting until desired thickness.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Melt
peanut butter and butterscotch bits.
Remove from heat. Stir in Rice Krispies until coated.
Pat 1/2 of mixture in buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Simmer until thickened.
Pour into shell and bake until brown.

title: baked cod with tomatoes, zucchini and lemons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In an ovenproof baking dish, make a layer of onions on the bottom.
Drizzle with half the oil and thyme, and season with salt and pepper.
Place the fish over the onions and layer the tomatoes and zucchini.
Pour in the stock and wine to fill the dish halfway.
Sprinkle the remaining oil and thyme on top.
Cover with lemon slices.

title: quick and easy peach cobbler
directions: In a rectangular glass baking dish, place can of peaches.
Make sure the peaches fill up 1/2 of the dish.
If you need more peaches, add 1 small can.
Cover peaches and juice with as much of the cake mix as you can to bring level just under the top of the rim of the dish.
Slice stick of butter lengthwise into quarters. Place at 1/4 intervals side to side in the dish.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugars.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt and pumpkin pie spice.
Add this to creamed mixture, alternating with milk and vanilla.
Add apples. Put into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Before baking, sprinkle with the last sugars.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry-chocolate cake
directions: In large bowl combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir by hand. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
In small bowl combine sugar, butter and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in chips; let melt.
Pour over cake.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Soften margarine.
Add sugar and beat until creamy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each. Next add vanilla, then add flour and milk, starting with flour and ending with flour.
Mix well after each addition.
Pour batter into a lined and greased tube pan.
Bake for approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: orange bavarian salad
directions: Let jello jell to soft stage.
Then beat at least 5 or 6 minutes until it is thick and frosty.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients gradually to mixture.
Stir in mincemeat.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool.
Makes 6 1/2 dozen.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Bring syrup to a boil.
Take off heat.
Put coconut flakes into syrup.
Make into balls.
Chill 1 hour.
Melt wax and bits. Keep hot on low heat.
Dip balls with toothpick.
Let cool.

title: butter sugar cookies
directions: Beat together butter,
sugar,
powdered
sugar and oil. Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat
until
fluffy.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Add
to creamed mixture.
Form into 5 rolls. Chill or freeze; slice.
Press down with bottom of a glass; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake
at
for
10 minutes. Remove from cookie sheets immediately.
Cool on racks.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Place popcorn, peanuts and gum drops in a large bowl.
Cook butter, cooking oil and marshmallows over medium heat until marshmallows are melted.
Pour over popcorn mixture and mix well. Press into buttered Bundt pan.
Turn pan upside down.
Remove cake from pan immediately.
Let stand for a while before slicing.

title: sweet and pungent fish
directions: Brown onion in cooking oil in a heavy skillet.
Remove.
Brown fish in same skillet, add browned onions and remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until fish is done.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk together until lumps are dissolved.
Boil on low heat.
Add oleo, peanut butter and vanilla.
When it begins to thicken, pour in buttered pan.
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini (don't peel); cook in small amount of water until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Cook beef in skillet until lightly browned.
Add onion; cover and cook over low heat until onion is tender.
Season to taste.
Lightly butter a 2-quart casserole. Arrange layers of zucchini, meat and cheese; repeat, ending with cheese.
Combine mushrooms and milk.
Pour over all.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: pigs in blanket
directions: Season hamburger well with salt and pepper.
Add the egg.
Mix well.
Mix in rice.
To make sauce, melt the butter and add onion and cook for several minutes.
Combine tomato soup and an equal amount of water and add to onion.
Add the parsley, celery, lemon juice, sugar, salt and pepper and cook for 10 minutes.
Wash the cabbage leaves and boil until tender.
Put 2 tablespoons of meat mixture in each leaf and roll tightly.
Secure each roll with a toothpick.
Place in a saucepan and pour sauce over rolls.
Cover pan tightly and cook slowly for 3 hours.
Serve very hot.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: In saucepan mix 3 tablespoons flour, 1 cup brown sugar, molasses, beaten egg and hot water.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in baking soda.
Cool.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl with the eggs.
Bake at 400° in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan until brown, approximately 25 minutes.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs, one at a time. Sift dry ingredients. Add alternately with milk. Mix well. Add vanilla. Bake in long pan in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Leave cream cheese at room temperature. Using scissors, cut up chipped beef.
Sprinkle in 1/2 of chipped beef.
Add Accent and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well and form into ball.
Roll in remainder of chipped beef.
Chill.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in saucepan over medium heat. Bring to a boil for 3 to 4 minutes. Remove from heat; add vanilla. Pour over vanilla wafers and sliced bananas.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
In a casserole dish, add your hamburger, envelope of Lipton onion soup, water, ketchup, mustard, vinegar, B&M beans and red beans.
Stir all together.
Heat in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Great for a side dish for summer cookouts!

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add flour, alternating with buttermilk in which soda has been dissolved.
Add extracts.
Add beaten egg whites to which 1/2 cup sugar has been added.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in a Bundt pan, greased.

title: lasagna
directions: Grease a large, deep baking dish or pan.
Cook noodles according to package directions and set aside.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown hamburger and sausage.
Mince garlic cloves and add to meat.
Chop onion, pepper and add to meat; cook until tender. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Then add sliced mushrooms and dry seasonings.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Layer in deep dish pan:
meat sauce, noodles, meat sauce, both kinds of cheese, noodles, meat sauce, cheeses, noodles, meat sauce, etc. until all is gone (2 to 3 layers).
End with cheese on top.
Bake until top is brown, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: impossible pina colada pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Beat all except coconut for 30 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with a hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Sprinkle with coconut. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 40 to 45 minutes.
Garnish with sliced pineapple and whipped cream, if desired.
Refrigerate any remaining pie.

title: oreo pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and Cool Whip together with mixer until smooth.
Add sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in 3/4 cup Oreo crumbs.
Pour mixture into crust.
Garnish with rest of Oreo crumbs.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve well chilled.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread into an ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Sometimes I add some ham.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Pour in mixture and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool on rack.

title: peach sherbet
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and process at a high speed until smooth and creamy.
Pour mixture into ice cream tray or pan and freeze until solid.
Remove from freezer and break into chunks.
Return mixture to blender and process at a high speed to ice cream consistency.
Pour back into pan and freeze until firm. Allow to soften slightly in the refrigerator before serving.

title: kid's famous macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook the macaroni according to the package directions.
Drain and pour into a large casserole dish. In a large saucepan, melt the margarine.
Add the milk and heat through.
Add both cheeses.
Mix over the cooked macaroni.
Pour the warm cheese mixture over the cooked macaroni.
Mix until all the noodles are coated with sauce.
Bake until hot, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine chicken, celery, oranges, pineapple and almonds.
Chill well.
In a small mixing bowl, blend together mayonnaise, salt and marjoram.
Add mayonnaise dressing to the chicken mixture.
Toss together lightly to coat all ingredients.
Chill if time permits.
Serve in an attractive serving dish, garnished with extra oranges, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: meal salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together, saving 1/4 cup of nuts.
Press into a ball and roll into nuts.

title: hot beef cracker spread
directions: Mix milk and cream cheese until smooth. Mix dried beef, onion, mango and pepper together and mix into cheese mixture. Add sour cream and stir. Top with chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 15-20 minutes. Serve warm with crackers.

title: reuben meat loaf
directions: Mix 1/2 can tomato sauce and first 6 ingredients.
Press on 15 x 10-inch pan covered with Saran Wrap.
Mix sauerkraut, shredded cheese and caraway seed and press into meat mixture.
With aid of Saran Wrap, roll jelly roll fashion from narrow end.
Bake in shallow baking dish with 1/3 cup of water at 350° for 45 minutes. Mix 1/2 can tomato sauce and horseradish.
Spoon over loaf.
Bake 15 minutes.
Arrange cheese slices over loaf.
Bake until cheese melts.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Pare and slice potatoes; cook in water to which salt has been added until just barely tender.
Place a layer of potatoes in bottom of casserole dish.
Add some of margarine, grated cheese and chopped onion.
Continue until all ingredients except bacon have been added.
Place strips of bacon on top of casserole.
Place in 400° oven for about 30 minutes or until bacon has been browned.

title: tasty sesame chicken wings
directions: Cut wing tips off.
Combine all
ingredients;
marinate wings overnight.	Deep fry until golden brown.
Drummettes may be used instead of wings.

title: sausage bread
directions: Thaw bread dough and flatten.
Sprinkle sausage onto dough. Smooth egg over sausage.
Sprinkle cheese over egg.

title: peanut butter cheweys
directions: Melt over medium heat, butter, peanut butter and sugar.
Blend well.
Remove from heat and add flour and eggs.
Blend into ball. Spoon into pan or cookie sheet and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lohl family's broiled cake frosting
directions: Mix together and spread over a hot chocolate 9-inch layer cake.
Broil until hot and bubbly.
Great on the Stir Crazy Wacky Cake.

title: honey-mustard dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate.

title: sandy's microwave fudge
directions: Sift powdered sugar and cocoa together into microwave-safe bowl.
Pour milk over sugar and cocoa; put butter pieces on top. Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir well; then stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan and refrigerate for 2 hours before cutting.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add strawberries and pineapple, including juice.
Add mashed bananas.
Let half of jello mixture set up in an 8 x 8-inch pan or dish.
After it's set, spread on Dream Whip carefully and let it set awhile.
Add the remaining jello mixture for top layer and let set.

title: margrethe's krumkake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, butter and vanilla.
Beat.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Bake in krumkake iron on medium heat. Spoon about 1 teaspoon of batter in center of iron.
Close and turn iron.
Bake krumkake light golden brown.
Remove krumkake quickly with wooden spatula.
Immediately roll on cone shape.
Remove cone and cool krumkake (seam down).
Store airtight.
Makes 98 or 102.

title: chicken with peanut sauce
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil and cook chicken over medium heat for 30 to 40 minutes, turning once, until cooked through, adding oil as needed.
Set aside.

title: chocolate sauce for ice cream
directions: Cook cocoa, corn syrup and water until blended.
Stir in sugar, canned milk and margarine; boil gently for 10 minutes.
Add 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Take off burner and pour into jar or right on ice cream.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal.
Cover and let set 20 minutes.
Stir in sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, nutmeg and cinnamon; mix together.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix hamburg, some salt and pepper and some finely cut onions. Form into balls the size of a walnut.
Brown in oil about 15 minutes.
Add tomato juice and a little shoyu sauce and simmer about 45 minutes or until done.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil noodles 15 minutes.
Let stand in cold water until used. Brown meat.
Add sauce.
Line baking dish with noodles.
Mix cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, onion tops and green pepper.
Spread over noodles.
Add another layer of noodles and then cheese.
Add hamburger mixture over cheese.
Sprinkle heavy with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients together until smooth. Add eggs, room temperature, one at a time and beat well after each addition. Bake in lightly greased loaf pan at 325° or angel food cake pan. After taking out of oven, take 1 cup of powdered sugar and enough lemon juice to make it slightly runny (about 1 lemon) and mix well. Punch holes in cake with toothpick; pour topping on cake. Leave in cake pan until cool before removing.

title: chess pie
directions: Make up your own biscuit recipe.
Roll dough thin and sprinkle with Hershey's cocoa and sugar.
Pat down.
Roll up dough and slice.
Stand on end in 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with milk. Sprinkle with sugar and vanilla flavor.
Place chips of butter on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Baste occasionally with juice.

title: venison steak
directions: Mix oil and vinegar.
Marinate steak for 4 to 6 hours.
Remove from marinade and saute in hot skillet in additional cooking oil. Remove browned steaks to foil-covered cookie sheet.
Place about 1/4 cup stuffing on each steak and flatten.
Cover with 1 to 2 tablespoons spaghetti sauce and top with Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: caldillo "mexican stew"
directions: Cooking time: 27 to 33 minutes.
Servings of: 4.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Arrange in order listed; sprinkle with cheese, eggs and bacon (eggs may be sliced or chopped).
Cover and refrigerate at least 36 hours.
May add fresh mushrooms or pimentos.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix and simmer 35 minutes.
Pour into hot jars.
Seal at once.

title: fleish kueckla
directions: Mix together flour, salt and milk and roll dough into thin circles 6 inches in diameter.
Mix remaining ingredients well and spread on half of each circle.
Fold dough over, seal edges and deep-fry.

title: boiled cookies
directions: *May use 1/2 cup butter and omit peanut butter.

title: stir-fried broccoli
directions: Heat oil in 12 inch skillet.
Add ginger root and garlic. Stir-fry until light brown or for about 1 minute.
Add broccoli, carrots and onion.
Stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add chicken broth and salt.
Cover and cook until carrots are tender.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Stir into vegetable mixture. Cook until thickened. Add water chestnut, mushrooms and oyster sauce and cook for 30 seconds.
Serve while hot.

title: nachos
directions: Cook meat done, drain and combine all other ingredients in crock-pot.
Turn on low for 2 hours, then serve.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in rest; mix, then pour in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: smothered chicken
directions: In deep saucepan or Dutch oven, brown chicken parts in oil. Pour off excess oil; add onion, garlic and spices.
Cover chicken with water.
Cover pot and bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer for approximately 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add carrots and peas. Cover pot; bring back to a boil.
Then lower the heat and simmer for another 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Cut into cubes.
Place in dish. Mix soup, sour cream and 1/2 poppy seed.
Pour over chicken. Crush crackers and sprinkle over chicken mixture.
Melt butter and 1/2 poppy seed and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: one pot meal for 12
directions: In Dutch oven, brown hamburger and drain off fat.
Add onions, sweet peppers, tomato soup, salt and pepper.
Then add ingredients for variations.

title: emergency barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ketchup, small amount of sugar and chili pepper.
Adjust to your taste.
You can also add to prepared barbecue sauce to make it go further.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, margarine, milk and cocoa to a boil, stirring constantly.
Take off heat and add peanut butter, vanilla, nuts or coconut and oatmeal.
Stir well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan, or drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: see's fudge
directions: Mix milk and sugar in pan; boil 10 minutes.
In large bowl, mix Marshmallow Creme, chocolate chips, nuts, butter and vanilla. Add boiled mixture and stir until smooth.
Pour into two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Makes about 6 pounds.

title: laura jane's layer cake and caramel icing
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, flour and milk alternately. Add vanilla last.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix as listed.
Beat well.
Bake for 1 hour in a greased bread pan at 350°.

title: tangy cucumber salad
directions: Place cucumbers in a strainer; sprinkle with 1/2 tsp. of salt and toss.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Rinse and drain well.
Place in a large bowl; add tomatoes and onion.
In small bowl, whisk together the remaining ingredients; pour over cucumber mixture and toss.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.

title: salt dough cookie ornaments
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Mix together the flour and salt.
Make a well in the mixture; pour in the water.
Knead the mixture until it forms a ball.
Pull off a tablespoon of dough and shape it. Put ornament on a cookie sheet; bake for 1 1/2 hours.
When cooled, paint and decorate as desired.

title: soup to nuts cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and eggs until soft and fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients and alternately add dry ingredients and applesauce and soup mixture to the egg, sugar and margarine mixture.
Mix thoroughly and fold in raisins and nuts.
Turn into buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: peanutty pear slaw
directions: In a small bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in sour cream; mix well.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Yields 4 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: spanakopita - spinach pie
directions: Saute the finely chopped onion in the 6 tablespoons melted butter until tender.
Combine with all the ingredients except 3 sticks butter, phyllo pastry, 1 egg and 3 tablespoons cottage cheese.
Choose a baking pan, either 9 x 13-inch or 12 x 16-inch to fit the phyllo pastry sheets.
Brush pan well with melted butter.
Count the sheets of phyllo in the package.
Put 1/3 of the phyllo in the bottom of the pan; brush each sheet with butter as you put in the pan.
Put 1/2 of filling on top of the phyllo; top with 1/3 of the phyllo, each sheet buttered as you put them on the mixture, then put remaining spinach mixture in the pan.
Top with remaining phyllo pastry; don't forget to butter! Combine the beaten egg and cottage cheese and brush over top of pastry.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown, about 30 to 40 minutes.
To serve as an appetizer, cut into small diamond shapes or cut into larger servings for a main dish.

title: cheese roll
directions: Cream together all ingredients and roll in chili powder. Chill.

title: candied fruit cake
directions: Use two loaf pans.
Grease pans well with butter and line bottom and sides with wax paper cut to fit, then grease paper. Preheat oven to 275°.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Steam cabbage.
Place cabbage in buttered casserole dish. Spread soup over cabbage.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix butter and crackers.
Spread over casserole.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: spice cake
directions: Stir shortening to soften.
Add dry ingredients.
Add milk and stir until flour is dampened, then beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and molasses and beat one minute longer.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: potato dish
directions: Fry onion, garlic, thyme and salt in 1 teaspoon oil until onion is clear and soft.
Place a layer of thinly sliced potatoes in bottom of ovenproof serving dish.
Pour fried mixture in layers with potatoes.
Pour 1/2 cup stock over completed layers.
Place foil on top and bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: elmer's cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Use Bundt pan, greased lightly.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat thoroughly in microwave or conventional oven.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: spirited honey mustard salad dressing
directions: Whisk together all the ingredients in a small bowl until smooth.
May be used over salad or as a dip with shrimp, breadsticks, or vegetables.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: ham and cheese chicken rolls
directions: Flatten chicken to even thickness.
Place 1 ham slice and 1 cheese slice on each breast half.
Roll up chicken from narrow end, jelly roll fashion.
Tuck in ham and cheese; secure with toothpick.
In a skillet over medium-high heat, in hot oil, cook chicken rolls 10 minutes or until browned on all sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, milk, onions and thyme.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat and cover.
Cook 10 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, stirring occasionally.
To serve, remove toothpicks. Spoon sauce over roll up.

title: hishey hash
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add salt, pepper and onions.
When done, add kidney beans, spaghetti and 1 can water.
Cook until beans and spaghetti are done.

title: jamasetta
directions: Fry pork and set aside.
Saute onions.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Place pork in sauce and simmer 20 minutes.
In oblong baking dish place layer of cooked noodles, layer of meat sauce, layer of cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan. Repeat layers.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for a few minutes to melt cheese.

title: good lipton meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: orange blossoms
directions: Soften gelatin in small amount of water.
Bring to boil. Remove from heat, pour into measuring cup, add 2 tablespoons frozen orange juice concentrate and enough ice water to make 2/3 cup liquid.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Fill casserole with 1 layer of potatoes, then one layer cheese, onions, salt and pepper.
Repeat until all is used.
Bake at 350° until tender and brown.

title: chuckwagon carrots
directions: Microwave:
In a 2-quart casserole, combine 1/2 cup water and carrots.
Cover; microwave on High, stirring halfway, for 6 to 8 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute.
Drain; set aside.

title: hamburger spins
directions: Cook onion in hot fat until brown.
Add green pepper, celery, ground beef, salt and pepper.
Cook slightly.
Sprinkle with flour and mix well.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Use a large pan.
Boil all of the vegetables until almost done.
Brown meat and drain.
Add meat and juice to the other ingredients.
Let cook until done.

title: raspberry mousse pie
directions: In a heavy saucepan combine the gelatin, sugar and raspberries. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.

title: baked nutmeg sweet potatoes
directions: Peel sweet potatoes. Slice 1/4 thick lengthwise. Place lengthwise in a casserole dish. Dot with margarine. Sprinkle with sugar and nutmeg. Don't add any water or liquid. Cover tightly with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
